<usx version="2.0">
    <book code="PSA" style="id">The Book of Psalms</book>
    <para style="mt">The Book of Psalms</para>
    <chapter number="1" style="c" />
	<para style="s">BOOK ONE: Psalms 1—41</para>
	<para style="s">The Way of the Righteous and the End of the Ungodly</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Blessed <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 4:14</char></note><char style="it">is</char> the man</para>
	<para style="q2">Who walks not in the counsel of the ungodly,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor stands in the path of sinners,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 26:4, 5; Jer. 15:17</char></note>Nor sits in the seat of the scornful;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:14, 16, 35</char></note>his delight <char style="it">is</char> in the law of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Josh. 1:8)</char></note>And in His law he meditates day and night.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />He shall be like a tree</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 92:12–14); Jer. 17:8; Ezek. 19:10</char></note>Planted by the rivers of water,</para>
	<para style="q2">That brings forth its fruit in its season,</para>
	<para style="q2">Whose leaf also shall not wither;</para>
	<para style="q2">And whatever he does shall <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 39:2, 3, 23; Ps. 128:2</char></note>prosper.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />The ungodly <char style="it">are</char> not so,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <char style="it">are</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 21:18; Ps. 35:5; Is. 17:13</char></note>like the chaff which the wind drives away.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Therefore the ungodly shall not stand in the judgment,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor sinners in the congregation of the righteous.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:18; (Nah. 1:7; John 10:14; 2 Tim. 2:19)</char></note>the <char style="sc">Lord</char> knows the way of the righteous,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the way of the ungodly shall perish.</para>
	<chapter number="2" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Messiah’s Triumph and Kingdom</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Why <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Acts 4:25, 26</char></note>do the nations rage,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the people plot a vain thing?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />The kings of the earth set themselves,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Matt. 12:14; 26:3, 4, 59–66; 27:1, 2; Mark 3:6; 11:18)</char></note>rulers take counsel together,</para>
	<para style="q2">Against the <char style="sc">Lord</char> and against His <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(John 1:41)</char></note>Anointed, <char style="it">saying,</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />“Let <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Luke 19:14</char></note>us break Their bonds in pieces</para>
	<para style="q2">And cast away Their cords from us.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />He who sits in the heavens <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:13</char></note>shall laugh;</para>
	<para style="q2">The Lord shall hold them in derision.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Then He shall speak to them in His wrath,</para>
	<para style="q2">And distress them in His deep displeasure:</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />“Yet I have set My King</para>
	<para style="q2">On My holy hill of Zion.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />“I will declare the decree:</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> has said to Me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 3:17; Mark 1:1, 11; Luke 3:22; John 1:18; Acts 13:33; (Heb. 1:5; 5:5)</char></note>‘You <char style="it">are</char> My Son,</para>
	<para style="q2">Today I have begotten You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Ask of Me, and I will give <char style="it">You</char></para>
	<para style="q2">The nations <char style="it">for</char> Your inheritance,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the ends of the earth <char style="it">for</char> Your possession.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 89:23; 110:5, 6; (Rev. 2:26, 27; 12:5; 19:15)</char></note>You shall break them with a rod of iron;</para>
	<para style="q2">You shall dash them to pieces like a potter’s vessel.’ ”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />Now therefore, be wise, O kings;</para>
	<para style="q2">Be instructed, you judges of the earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />Serve the <char style="sc">Lord</char> with fear,</para>
	<para style="q2">And rejoice with trembling.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" /> Kiss the Son, lest  He be angry,</para>
	<para style="q2">And you perish <char style="it">in</char> the way,</para>
	<para style="q2">When <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Rev. 6:16, 17)</char></note>His wrath is kindled but a little.</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 5:11; 34:22)</char></note>Blessed <char style="it">are</char> all those who put their trust in Him.</para>
	<chapter number="3" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> Helps His Troubled People</para>
	<para style="d">A Psalm of David <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 15:13–17</char></note>when he fled from Absalom his son.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" /><char style="sc">Lord</char>, how they have increased who trouble me!</para>
	<para style="q2">Many <char style="it">are</char> they who rise up against me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Many <char style="it">are</char> they who say of me,</para>
	<para style="q2">“<char style="it">There</char> <char style="it">is</char> no help for him in God.”</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />But You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <char style="it">are</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 5:12; 28:7</char></note>a shield for me,</para>
	<para style="q2">My glory and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 9:13; 27:6</char></note>the One who lifts up my head.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />I cried to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> with my voice,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 4:3; 34:4</char></note>He heard me from His <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 2:6; 15:1; 43:3</char></note>holy hill.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 26:6; Ps. 4:8; Prov. 3:24</char></note>I lay down and slept;</para>
	<para style="q2">I awoke, for the <char style="sc">Lord</char> sustained me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 23:4; 27:3</char></note>I will not be afraid of ten thousands of people</para>
	<para style="q2">Who have set <char style="it">themselves</char> against me all around.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />Arise, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">Save me, O my God!</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 16:10</char></note>For You have struck all my enemies on the cheekbone;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have broken the teeth of the ungodly.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 28:8; 35:3; (Is. 43:11)</char></note>Salvation <char style="it">belongs</char> to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q2">Your blessing <char style="it">is</char> upon Your people.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<chapter number="4" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Safety of the Faithful</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. With stringed instruments. A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Hear me when I call, O God of my righteousness!</para>
	<para style="q2">You have relieved me in <char style="it">my</char> distress;</para>
	<para style="q2">Have mercy on me, and hear my prayer.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" />How long, O you sons of men,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Will</char> <char style="it">you</char> <char style="it">turn</char> my glory to shame?</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">How</char> <char style="it">long</char> will you love worthlessness</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> seek falsehood?</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />But know that <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(2 Tim. 2:19)</char></note>the <char style="sc">Lord</char> has set apart for Himself him who is godly;</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> will hear when I call to Him.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 119:11; Eph. 4:26)</char></note>Be angry, and do not sin.</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 77:6</char></note>Meditate within your heart on your bed, and be still.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Offer <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 33:19; Ps. 51:19</char></note>the sacrifices of righteousness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:3, 5; 62:8</char></note>put your trust in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" /><char style="it">There</char> <char style="it">are</char> many who say,</para>
	<para style="q2">“Who will show us <char style="it">any</char> good?”</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 6:26; Ps. 80:3, 7, 19</char></note><char style="sc">Lord</char>, lift up the light of Your countenance upon us.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />You have put <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 97:11, 12; Is. 9:3; Acts 14:17</char></note>gladness in my heart,</para>
	<para style="q2">More than in the season that their grain and wine increased.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 11:19; Ps. 3:5</char></note>I will both lie down in peace, and sleep;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Lev. 25:18); Deut. 12:10</char></note>For You alone, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, make me dwell in safety.</para>
	<chapter number="5" style="c" />
	<para style="s">A Prayer for Guidance</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. With flutes. A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Give <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 4:1</char></note>ear to my words, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Consider my meditation.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Give heed to the voice of my cry,</para>
	<para style="q2">My King and my God,</para>
	<para style="q2">For to You I will pray.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />My voice You shall hear in the morning, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 55:17; 88:13</char></note>In the morning I will direct <char style="it">it</char> to You,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I will look up.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />For You <char style="it">are</char> not a God who takes pleasure in wickedness,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor shall evil dwell with You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />The <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Hab. 1:13)</char></note>boastful shall not <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 1:5</char></note>stand in Your sight;</para>
	<para style="q2">You hate all workers of iniquity.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />You shall destroy those who speak falsehood;</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> abhors the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 55:23</char></note>bloodthirsty and deceitful man.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />But as for me, I will come into Your house in the multitude of Your mercy;</para>
	<para style="q2">In fear of You I will worship toward Your holy temple.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 25:4, 5; 27:11; 31:3</char></note>Lead me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, in Your righteousness because of my enemies;</para>
	<para style="q2">Make Your way straight before my face.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />For <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> no faithfulness in their mouth;</para>
	<para style="q2">Their inward part <char style="it">is</char> destruction;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rom. 3:13</char></note>Their throat <char style="it">is</char> an open tomb;</para>
	<para style="q2">They flatter with their tongue.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />Pronounce them guilty, O God!</para>
	<para style="q2">Let them fall by their own counsels;</para>
	<para style="q2">Cast them out in the multitude of their transgressions,</para>
	<para style="q2">For they have rebelled against You.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" />But let all those rejoice who put their trust in You;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let them ever shout for joy, because You defend them;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let those also who love Your name</para>
	<para style="q2">Be joyful in You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />For You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, will bless the righteous;</para>
	<para style="q2">With favor You will surround him as <char style="it">with</char> a shield.</para>
	<chapter number="6" style="c" />
	<para style="s">A Prayer of Faith in Time of Distress</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. With stringed instruments. <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 12:title</char></note>On an eight-stringed harp. A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 38:1; 118:18; (Jer. 10:24)</char></note>do not rebuke me in Your anger,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor chasten me in Your hot displeasure.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Have mercy on me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, for I <char style="it">am</char> weak;</para>
	<para style="q2">O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 41:4; 147:3; (Hos. 6:1)</char></note>heal me, for my bones are troubled.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />My soul also is greatly <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 88:3; John 12:27</char></note>troubled;</para>
	<para style="q2">But You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>—how long?</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />Return, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, deliver me!</para>
	<para style="q2">Oh, save me for Your mercies’ sake!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 30:9; 88:10–12; 115:17; (Eccl. 9:10); Is. 38:18</char></note>For in death <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> no remembrance of You;</para>
	<para style="q2">In the grave who will give You thanks?</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />I am weary with my groaning;</para>
	<para style="q2">All night I make my bed swim;</para>
	<para style="q2">I drench my couch with my tears.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 17:7; Ps. 31:9</char></note>My eye wastes away because of grief;</para>
	<para style="q2">It grows old because of all my enemies.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Matt. 25:41)</char></note>Depart from me, all you workers of iniquity;</para>
	<para style="q2">For the <char style="sc">Lord</char> has <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 3:4; 28:6</char></note>heard the voice of my weeping.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> has heard my supplication;</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> will receive my prayer.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />Let all my enemies be ashamed and greatly troubled;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let them turn back <char style="it">and</char> be ashamed suddenly.</para>
	<chapter number="7" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Prayer and Praise for Deliverance from Enemies</para>
	<para style="d">A <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Hab. 3:1</char></note>Meditation of David, which he sang to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 16</char></note>concerning the words of Cush, a Benjamite.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />O <char style="sc">Lord</char> my God, in You I put my trust;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 31:15</char></note>Save me from all those who persecute me;</para>
	<para style="q2">And deliver me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 57:4; Is. 38:13</char></note>Lest they tear me like a lion,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 50:22</char></note>Rending <char style="it">me</char> in pieces, while <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> none to deliver.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />O <char style="sc">Lord</char> my God, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 16:7</char></note>if I have done this:</para>
	<para style="q2">If there is <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 24:11</char></note>iniquity in my hands,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />If I have repaid evil to him who was at peace with me,</para>
	<para style="q2">Or <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 24:7; 26:9</char></note>have plundered my enemy without cause,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Let the enemy pursue me and overtake <char style="it">me;</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Yes, let him trample my life to the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2">And lay my honor in the dust.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />Arise, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, in Your anger;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 94:2</char></note>Lift Yourself up because of the rage of my enemies;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:23; 44:23</char></note>Rise up for me <char style="it">to</char> the judgment You have commanded!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />So the congregation of the peoples shall surround You;</para>
	<para style="q2">For their sakes, therefore, return on high.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> shall judge the peoples;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 26:1; 35:24; 43:1</char></note>Judge me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 18:20; 35:24</char></note>according to my righteousness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And according to my integrity within me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />Oh, let the wickedness of the wicked come to an end,</para>
	<para style="q2">But establish the just;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Sam. 16:7)</char></note>For the righteous God tests the hearts and minds.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />My defense <char style="it">is</char> of God,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who saves the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 97:10, 11; 125:4</char></note>upright in heart.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" />God <char style="it">is</char> a just judge,</para>
	<para style="q2">And God is angry <char style="it">with</char> <char style="it">the</char> <char style="it">wicked</char> every day.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />If he does not turn back,</para>
	<para style="q2">He will <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 32:41</char></note>sharpen His sword;</para>
	<para style="q2">He bends His bow and makes it ready.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />He also prepares for Himself instruments of death;</para>
	<para style="q2">He makes His arrows into fiery shafts.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 15:35; Is. 59:4; (James 1:15)</char></note>Behold, <char style="it">the</char> <char style="it">wicked</char> brings forth iniquity;</para>
	<para style="q2">Yes, he conceives trouble and brings forth falsehood.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />He made a pit and dug it out,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Job 4:8); Ps. 57:6</char></note>And has fallen into the ditch <char style="it">which</char> he made.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Esth. 9:25; Ps. 140:9</char></note>His trouble shall return upon his own head,</para>
	<para style="q2">And his violent dealing shall come down on his own crown.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="17" style="v" />I will praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char> according to His righteousness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And will sing praise to the name of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> Most High.</para>
	<chapter number="8" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Glory of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> in Creation</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. On the instrument of Gath. A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, our Lord,</para>
	<para style="q2">How <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 148:13</char></note>excellent <char style="it">is</char> Your name in all the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 113:4</char></note>set Your glory above the heavens!</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 21:16; (1 Cor. 1:27)</char></note>Out of the mouth of babes and nursing infants</para>
	<para style="q2">You have ordained strength,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because of Your enemies,</para>
	<para style="q2">That You may silence <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 44:16</char></note>the enemy and the avenger.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />When I <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 111:2</char></note>consider Your heavens, the work of Your fingers,</para>
	<para style="q2">The moon and the stars, which You have ordained,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 7:17, 18; (Heb. 2:6–8)</char></note>What is man that You are mindful of him,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the son of man that You <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Job 10:12)</char></note>visit him?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />For You have made him a little lower than the angels,</para>
	<para style="q2">And You have crowned him with glory and honor.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Gen. 1:26, 28)</char></note>You have made him to have dominion over the works of Your hands;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Cor. 15:27; Eph. 1:22; Heb. 2:8)</char></note>You have put all <char style="it">things</char> under his feet,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />All sheep and oxen—</para>
	<para style="q2">Even the beasts of the field,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />The birds of the air,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the fish of the sea</para>
	<para style="q2">That pass through the paths of the seas.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 8:1</char></note>O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, our Lord,</para>
	<para style="q2">How excellent <char style="it">is</char> Your name in all the earth!</para>
	<chapter number="9" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Prayer and Thanksgiving for the <char style="sc">Lord</char>’s Righteous Judgments</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. To <char style="it">the</char> <char style="it">tune</char> <char style="it">of</char> “Death of the Son.” A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />I will praise <char style="it">You,</char> O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, with my whole heart;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will tell of all Your marvelous works.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />I will be glad and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 5:11; 104:34</char></note>rejoice in You;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will sing praise to Your name, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 83:18; 92:1)</char></note>O Most High.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />When my enemies turn back,</para>
	<para style="q2">They shall fall and perish at Your presence.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />For You have maintained my right and my cause;</para>
	<para style="q2">You sat on the throne judging in righteousness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />You have rebuked the nations,</para>
	<para style="q2">You have destroyed the wicked;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:7</char></note>blotted out their name forever and ever.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />O enemy, destructions are finished forever!</para>
	<para style="q2">And you have destroyed cities;</para>
	<para style="q2">Even their memory has <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 34:16)</char></note>perished.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 102:12, 26; Heb. 1:11</char></note>But the <char style="sc">Lord</char> shall endure forever;</para>
	<para style="q2">He has prepared His throne for judgment.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 96:13; 98:9; Acts 17:31)</char></note>He shall judge the world in righteousness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And He shall administer judgment for the peoples in uprightness.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> also will be a <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 32:7; 46:1; 91:2</char></note>refuge for the oppressed,</para>
	<para style="q2">A refuge in times of trouble.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />And those who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 91:14</char></note>know Your name will put their trust in You;</para>
	<para style="q2">For You, <char style="sc">Lord</char>, have not forsaken those who seek You.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" />Sing praises to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, who dwells in Zion!</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 66:16; 107:22</char></note>Declare His deeds among the people.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Gen. 9:5; Ps. 72:14)</char></note>When He avenges blood, He remembers them;</para>
	<para style="q2">He does not forget the cry of the humble.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" />Have mercy on me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q2">Consider my trouble from those who hate me,</para>
	<para style="q2">You who lift me up from the gates of death,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />That I may tell of all Your praise</para>
	<para style="q2">In the gates of the daughter of Zion.</para>
	<para style="q2">I will <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 13:5; 20:5; 35:9</char></note>rejoice in Your salvation.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 7:15, 16</char></note>The nations have sunk down in the pit <char style="it">which</char> they made;</para>
	<para style="q2">In the net which they hid, their own foot is caught.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> is <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 7:5</char></note>known <char style="it">by</char> the judgment He executes;</para>
	<para style="q2">The wicked is snared in the work of his own hands.</para>
	<para style="pc"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 92:3</char></note>Meditation.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="17" style="v" />The wicked shall be turned into hell,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> all the nations <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 8:13; Ps. 50:22</char></note>that forget God.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 9:12; 12:5</char></note>For the needy shall not always be forgotten;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 62:5; 71:5); Prov. 23:18</char></note>The expectation of the poor shall <char style="it">not</char> perish forever.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" />Arise, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not let man prevail;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let the nations be judged in Your sight.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />Put them in fear, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">That</char> the nations may know themselves <char style="it">to</char> <char style="it">be</char> <char style="it">but</char> men.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<chapter number="10" style="c" />
	<para style="s">A Song of Confidence in God’s Triumph over Evil</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Why do You stand afar off, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>?</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Why</char> do You hide in times of trouble?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />The wicked in <char style="it">his</char> pride persecutes the poor;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 7:16; 9:16</char></note>Let them be caught in the plots which they have devised.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />For the wicked <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 49:6; 94:3, 4</char></note>boasts of his heart’s desire;</para>
	<para style="q2">He <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 28:4</char></note>blesses the greedy <char style="it">and</char> renounces the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />The wicked in his proud countenance does not seek <char style="it">God;</char></para>
	<para style="q2">God <char style="it">is</char> in none of his <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 14:1; 36:1</char></note>thoughts.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />His ways are always prospering;</para>
	<para style="q2">Your judgments <char style="it">are</char> far above, out of his sight;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">As</char> <char style="it">for</char> all his enemies, he sneers at them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 49:11; (Eccl. 8:11)</char></note>He has said in his heart, “I shall not be moved;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rev. 18:7</char></note>I shall never be in adversity.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Rom. 3:14)</char></note>His mouth is full of cursing and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 55:10, 11</char></note>deceit and oppression;</para>
	<para style="q2">Under his tongue <char style="it">is</char> trouble and iniquity.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />He sits in the lurking places of the villages;</para>
	<para style="q2">In the secret places he murders the innocent;</para>
	<para style="q2">His eyes are secretly fixed on the helpless.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />He lies in wait secretly, as a lion in his den;</para>
	<para style="q2">He lies in wait to catch the poor;</para>
	<para style="q2">He catches the poor when he draws him into his net.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />So he crouches, he lies low,</para>
	<para style="q2">That the helpless may fall by his strength.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />He has said in his heart,</para>
	<para style="q2">“God has forgotten;</para>
	<para style="q2">He hides His face;</para>
	<para style="q2">He will never see.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />Arise, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q2">O God, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 17:7; 94:2; Mic. 5:9</char></note>lift up Your hand!</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not forget the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 9:12</char></note>humble.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />Why do the wicked renounce God?</para>
	<para style="q2">He has said in his heart,</para>
	<para style="q2">“You will not require <char style="it">an</char> <char style="it">account.</char>”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" />But You have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 11:4)</char></note>seen, for You observe trouble and grief,</para>
	<para style="q2">To repay <char style="it">it</char> by Your hand.</para>
	<para style="q2">The helpless <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(2 Tim. 1:12)</char></note>commits himself to You;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 68:5; Hos. 14:3</char></note>You are the helper of the fatherless.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />Break the arm of the wicked and the evil <char style="it">man;</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Seek out his wickedness <char style="it">until</char> You find none.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 29:10</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> King forever and ever;</para>
	<para style="q2">The nations have perished out of His land.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><char style="sc">Lord</char>, You have heard the desire of the humble;</para>
	<para style="q2">You will prepare their heart;</para>
	<para style="q2">You will cause Your ear to hear,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />To do justice to the fatherless and the oppressed,</para>
	<para style="q2">That the man of the earth may oppress no more.</para>
	<chapter number="11" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Faith in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>’s Righteousness</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. <char style="it">A</char> <char style="it">Psalm</char> of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />In <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 56:11</char></note>the <char style="sc">Lord</char> I put my trust;</para>
	<para style="q2">How can you say to my soul,</para>
	<para style="q2">“Flee <char style="it">as</char> a bird to your mountain”?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />For look! <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 64:3, 4</char></note>The wicked bend <char style="it">their</char> bow,</para>
	<para style="q2">They make ready their arrow on the string,</para>
	<para style="q2">That they may shoot secretly at the upright in heart.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 82:5; 87:1; 119:152</char></note>If the foundations are destroyed,</para>
	<para style="q2">What can the righteous do?</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> in His holy temple,</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char>’s <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 2:4; (Is. 66:1); Matt. 5:34; 23:22; (Acts 7:49); Rev. 4:2</char></note>throne <char style="it">is</char> in heaven;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 33:18; 34:15, 16)</char></note>His eyes behold,</para>
	<para style="q2">His eyelids test the sons of men.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 22:1; (James 1:12)</char></note>tests the righteous,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the wicked and the one who loves violence His soul hates.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Upon the wicked He will rain coals;</para>
	<para style="q2">Fire and brimstone and a burning wind</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 1:4; Ps. 75:8; Ezek. 38:22</char></note><char style="it">Shall</char> <char style="it">be</char> the portion of their cup.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />For the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> righteous,</para>
	<para style="q2">He <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 33:5; 45:7</char></note>loves righteousness;</para>
	<para style="q2">His countenance beholds the upright.</para>
	<chapter number="12" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Man’s Treachery and God’s Constancy</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 6:title</char></note>On an eight-stringed harp. A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Help, <char style="sc">Lord</char>, for the godly man <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 57:1); Mic. 7:2</char></note>ceases!</para>
	<para style="q2">For the faithful disappear from among the sons of men.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 10:7; 41:6</char></note>They speak idly everyone with his neighbor;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">With</char> flattering lips <char style="it">and</char> a double heart they speak.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />May the <char style="sc">Lord</char> cut off all flattering lips,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> the tongue that speaks proud things,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Who have said,</para>
	<para style="q2">“With our tongue we will prevail;</para>
	<para style="q2">Our lips <char style="it">are</char> our own;</para>
	<para style="q2">Who <char style="it">is</char> lord over us?”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />“For the oppression of the poor, for the sighing of the needy,</para>
	<para style="q2">Now I will arise,” says the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">“I will set <char style="it">him</char> in the safety for which he yearns.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />The words of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">are</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 22:31; Ps. 18:30; 119:140; Prov. 30:5</char></note>pure words,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Like</char> silver tried in a furnace of earth,</para>
	<para style="q2">Purified seven times.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />You shall keep them, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">You shall preserve them from this generation forever.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />The wicked prowl on every side,</para>
	<para style="q2">When vileness is exalted among the sons of men.</para>
	<chapter number="13" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Trust in the Salvation of the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />How long, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>? Will You forget me forever?</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 13:24; Ps. 89:46</char></note>How long will You hide Your face from me?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />How long shall I take counsel in my soul,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Having</char> sorrow in my heart daily?</para>
	<para style="q2">How long will my enemy be exalted over me?</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />Consider <char style="it">and</char> hear me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char> my God;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 14:29; Ezra 9:8; Job 33:30; Ps. 18:28</char></note>Enlighten my eyes,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 51:39</char></note>Lest I sleep the <char style="it">sleep</char> <char style="it">of</char> death;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Lest my enemy say,</para>
	<para style="q2">“I have prevailed against him”;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Lest</char> those who trouble me rejoice when I am moved.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />But I have trusted in Your mercy;</para>
	<para style="q2">My heart shall rejoice in Your salvation.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />I will sing to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because He has dealt bountifully with me.</para>
	<chapter number="14" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Folly of the Godless, and God’s Final Triumph</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. <char style="it">A</char> <char style="it">Psalm</char> of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />The <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 10:4; 53:1</char></note>fool has said in his heart,</para>
	<para style="q2">“<char style="it">There</char> <char style="it">is</char> no God.”</para>
	<para style="q2">They are corrupt,</para>
	<para style="q2">They have done abominable works,</para>
	<para style="q2">There is none who does good.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 33:13, 14; 102:19; Rom. 3:11</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> looks down from heaven upon the children of men,</para>
	<para style="q2">To see if there are any who understand, who seek God.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rom. 3:12</char></note>They have all turned aside,</para>
	<para style="q2">They have together become corrupt;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">There</char> <char style="it">is</char> none who does good,</para>
	<para style="q2">No, not one.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />Have all the workers of iniquity no knowledge,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who eat up my people <char style="it">as</char> they eat bread,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 79:6; Is. 64:7; Jer. 10:25; Amos 8:4; Mic. 3:3</char></note>do not call on the <char style="sc">Lord</char>?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />There they are in great fear,</para>
	<para style="q2">For God <char style="it">is</char> with the generation of the righteous.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />You shame the counsel of the poor,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> his <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 9:9; 40:17; 46:1; 142:5</char></note>refuge.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 53:6; (Rom. 11:25–27)</char></note>Oh, that the salvation of Israel <char style="it">would</char> <char style="it">come</char> out of Zion!</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 30:3; Job 42:10</char></note>When the <char style="sc">Lord</char> brings back the captivity of His people,</para>
	<para style="q2">Let Jacob rejoice <char style="it">and</char> Israel be glad.</para>
	<chapter number="15" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Character of Those Who May Dwell with the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="d">A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" /><char style="sc">Lord</char>, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 24:3–5</char></note>who may abide in Your tabernacle?</para>
	<para style="q2">Who may dwell in Your holy hill?</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" />He who walks uprightly,</para>
	<para style="q2">And works righteousness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And speaks the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Zech. 8:16; (Eph. 4:25)</char></note>truth in his heart;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />He <char style="it">who</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Lev. 19:16–18)</char></note>does not backbite with his tongue,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor does evil to his neighbor,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 23:1</char></note>Nor does he take up a reproach against his friend;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Esth. 3:2</char></note>In whose eyes a vile person is despised,</para>
	<para style="q2">But he honors those who fear the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">He <char style="it">who</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 5:4</char></note>swears to his own hurt and does not change;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />He <char style="it">who</char> does not put out his money at usury,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor does he take a bribe against the innocent.</para>
	<para style="q1">He who does these <char style="it">things</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Pet. 1:10</char></note>shall never be moved.</para>
	<chapter number="16" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Hope of the Faithful, and the Messiah’s Victory</para>
	<para style="d">A <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 56—60</char></note>Michtam of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Preserve me, O God, for in You I put my trust.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" /><char style="it">O</char> <char style="it">my</char> <char style="it">soul,</char> you have said to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">“You <char style="it">are</char> my Lord,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 35:7</char></note>My goodness is nothing apart from You.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />As for the saints who <char style="it">are</char> on the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2">“They are the excellent ones, in <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:63</char></note>whom is all my delight.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />Their sorrows shall be multiplied who hasten <char style="it">after</char> another <char style="it">god;</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Their drink offerings of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 106:37, 38</char></note>blood I will not offer,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 23:13); Josh. 23:7</char></note>Nor take up their names on my lips.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <char style="it">You</char> <char style="it">are</char> the portion of my inheritance and my cup;</para>
	<para style="q2">You maintain my lot.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />The lines have fallen to me in pleasant <char style="it">places;</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Yes, I have a good inheritance.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />I will bless the <char style="sc">Lord</char> who has given me counsel;</para>
	<para style="q2">My heart also instructs me in the night seasons.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Acts 2:25–28)</char></note>I have set the <char style="sc">Lord</char> always before me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Because <char style="it">He</char> <char style="it">is</char> at my right hand I shall not be moved.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />Therefore my heart is glad, and my glory rejoices;</para>
	<para style="q2">My flesh also will rest in hope.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 49:15; 86:13; Acts 2:31, 32; Heb. 13:20</char></note>For You will not leave my soul in Sheol,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor will You allow Your Holy One to see corruption.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />You will show me the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 139:24; (Matt. 7:14)</char></note>path of life;</para>
	<para style="q2">In Your presence <char style="it">is</char> fullness of joy;</para>
	<para style="q2">At Your right hand <char style="it">are</char> pleasures forevermore.</para>
	<chapter number="17" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Prayer with Confidence in Final Salvation</para>
	<para style="d">A Prayer of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Hear a just cause, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Attend to my cry;</para>
	<para style="q2">Give ear to my prayer <char style="it">which</char> <char style="it">is</char> not from deceitful lips.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Let my vindication come from Your presence;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let Your eyes look on the things that are upright.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />You have tested my heart;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have visited <char style="it">me</char> in the night;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 23:10; Ps. 66:10; Zech. 13:9; (1 Pet. 1:7)</char></note>You have tried me and have found nothing;</para>
	<para style="q2">I have purposed that my mouth shall not <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 39:1</char></note>transgress.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Concerning the works of men,</para>
	<para style="q2">By the word of Your lips,</para>
	<para style="q2">I have kept away from the paths of the destroyer.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 23:11; Ps. 44:18; 119:133</char></note>Uphold my steps in Your paths,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">That</char> my footsteps may not slip.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 86:7; 116:2</char></note>I have called upon You, for You will hear me, O God;</para>
	<para style="q2">Incline Your ear to me, <char style="it">and</char> hear my speech.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Show Your marvelous lovingkindness by Your right hand,</para>
	<para style="q2">O You who save those who trust <char style="it">in</char> <char style="it">You</char></para>
	<para style="q2">From those who rise up <char style="it">against</char> <char style="it">them.</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Keep me as the apple of Your eye;</para>
	<para style="q2">Hide me under the shadow of Your wings,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />From the wicked who oppress me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">From</char> my deadly enemies who surround me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />They have closed up their <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ezek. 16:49</char></note>fat <char style="it">hearts;</char></para>
	<para style="q2">With their mouths they <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Sam. 2:3)</char></note>speak proudly.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />They have now surrounded us in our steps;</para>
	<para style="q2">They have set their eyes, crouching down to the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />As a lion is eager to tear his prey,</para>
	<para style="q2">And like a young lion lurking in secret places.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" />Arise, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Confront him, cast him down;</para>
	<para style="q2">Deliver my life from the wicked with Your sword,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />With Your hand from men, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">From men of the world <char style="it">who</char> <char style="it">have</char> their portion in <char style="it">this</char> life,</para>
	<para style="q2">And whose belly You fill with Your hidden treasure.</para>
	<para style="q2">They are satisfied with children,</para>
	<para style="q2">And leave the rest of their <char style="it">possession</char> for their babes.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" />As for me, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 John 3:2)</char></note>I will see Your face in righteousness;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 4:6, 7; 16:11</char></note>I shall be satisfied when I <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 26:19)</char></note>awake in Your likeness.</para>
	<chapter number="18" style="c" />
	<para style="s">God the Sovereign Savior</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. <char style="it">A</char> <char style="it">Psalm</char> of David <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 36:title</char></note>the servant of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, who spoke to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> the words of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 22</char></note>this song on the day that the <char style="sc">Lord</char> delivered him from the hand of all his enemies and from the hand of Saul. And he said:</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />I <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 144:1</char></note>will love You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, my strength.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> is my rock and my fortress and my deliverer;</para>
	<para style="q2">My God, my strength, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Heb. 2:13</char></note>in whom I will trust;</para>
	<para style="q2">My shield and the horn of my salvation, my stronghold.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />I will call upon the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 76:4; Rev. 5:12</char></note><char style="it">who</char> <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">worthy</char> to be praised;</para>
	<para style="q2">So shall I be saved from my enemies.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 116:3</char></note>The pangs of death surrounded me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the floods of ungodliness made me afraid.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />The sorrows of Sheol surrounded me;</para>
	<para style="q2">The snares of death confronted me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />In my distress I called upon the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And cried out to my God;</para>
	<para style="q2">He heard my voice from His temple,</para>
	<para style="q2">And my cry came before Him, <char style="it">even</char> to His ears.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Acts 4:31</char></note>Then the earth shook and trembled;</para>
	<para style="q2">The foundations of the hills also quaked and were shaken,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because He was angry.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Smoke went up from His nostrils,</para>
	<para style="q2">And devouring fire from His mouth;</para>
	<para style="q2">Coals were kindled by it.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 144:5</char></note>He bowed the heavens also, and came down</para>
	<para style="q2">With darkness under His feet.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 80:1; 99:1</char></note>And He rode upon a cherub, and flew;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 104:3)</char></note>He flew upon the wings of the wind.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />He made darkness His secret place;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 97:2</char></note>His canopy around Him <char style="it">was</char> dark waters</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> thick clouds of the skies.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 97:3; 140:10; Hab. 3:11</char></note>From the brightness before Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">His thick clouds passed with hailstones and coals of fire.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> thundered from heaven,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the Most High uttered <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 29:3–9; 104:7)</char></note>His voice,</para>
	<para style="q2">Hailstones and coals of fire.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Josh. 10:10; Ps. 144:6; Is. 30:30; Hab. 3:11</char></note>He sent out His arrows and scattered the foe,</para>
	<para style="q2">Lightnings in abundance, and He vanquished them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />Then the channels of the sea were seen,</para>
	<para style="q2">The foundations of the world were uncovered</para>
	<para style="q2">At Your rebuke, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">At the blast of the breath of Your nostrils.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 144:7</char></note>He sent from above, He took me;</para>
	<para style="q2">He drew me out of many waters.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />He delivered me from my strong enemy,</para>
	<para style="q2">From those who hated me,</para>
	<para style="q2">For they were too strong for me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />They confronted me in the day of my calamity,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the <char style="sc">Lord</char> was my support.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 4:1; 31:8; 118:5</char></note>He also brought me out into a broad place;</para>
	<para style="q2">He delivered me because He delighted in me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="20" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 24:19; (Job 33:26); Ps. 7:8</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> rewarded me according to my righteousness;</para>
	<para style="q2">According to the cleanness of my hands</para>
	<para style="q2">He has recompensed me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />For I have kept the ways of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And have not wickedly departed from my God.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" />For all His judgments <char style="it">were</char> before me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I did not put away His statutes from me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" />I was also blameless before Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I kept myself from my iniquity.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 26:23; Ps. 18:20</char></note>Therefore the <char style="sc">Lord</char> has recompensed me according to my righteousness,</para>
	<para style="q2">According to the cleanness of my hands in His sight.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="25" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Kin. 8:32; Ps. 62:12); Matt. 5:7</char></note>With the merciful You will show Yourself merciful;</para>
	<para style="q2">With a blameless man You will show Yourself blameless;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="26" style="v" />With the pure You will show Yourself pure;</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Lev. 26:23–28); Prov. 3:34</char></note>with the devious You will show Yourself shrewd.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="27" style="v" />For You will save the humble people,</para>
	<para style="q2">But will bring down <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 101:5); Prov. 6:17</char></note>haughty looks.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="28" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 15:4; Job 18:6; (Ps. 119:105)</char></note>For You will light my lamp;</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> my God will enlighten my darkness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="29" style="v" />For by You I can run against a troop,</para>
	<para style="q2">By my God I can leap over a wall.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="30" style="v" /><char style="it">As</char> <char style="it">for</char> God, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 32:4); Rev. 15:3</char></note>His way <char style="it">is</char> perfect;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 12:6; 119:140; (Prov. 30:5)</char></note>The word of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> is proven;</para>
	<para style="q2">He <char style="it">is</char> a shield <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 17:7)</char></note>to all who trust in Him.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="31" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 32:31, 39; 1 Sam. 2:2; Ps. 86:8–10; Is. 45:5)</char></note>For who <char style="it">is</char> God, except the <char style="sc">Lord</char>?</para>
	<para style="q2">And who <char style="it">is</char> a rock, except our God?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="32" style="v" /><char style="it">It</char> <char style="it">is</char> God who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 91:2)</char></note>arms me with strength,</para>
	<para style="q2">And makes my way perfect.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="33" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 2:18; Hab. 3:19</char></note>He makes my feet like the <char style="it">feet</char> <char style="it">of</char> deer,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 32:13; 33:29</char></note>sets me on my high places.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="34" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 144:1</char></note>He teaches my hands to make war,</para>
	<para style="q2">So that my arms can bend a bow of bronze.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="35" style="v" />You have also given me the shield of Your salvation;</para>
	<para style="q2">Your right hand has held me up,</para>
	<para style="q2">Your gentleness has made me great.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="36" style="v" />You enlarged my path under me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 66:9; Prov. 4:12</char></note>So my feet did not slip.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="37" style="v" />I have pursued my enemies and overtaken them;</para>
	<para style="q2">Neither did I turn back again till they were destroyed.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="38" style="v" />I have wounded them,</para>
	<para style="q2">So that they could not rise;</para>
	<para style="q2">They have fallen under my feet.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="39" style="v" />For You have armed me with strength for the battle;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have subdued under me those who rose up against me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="40" style="v" />You have also given me the necks of my enemies,</para>
	<para style="q2">So that I destroyed those who hated me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="41" style="v" />They cried out, but <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">was</char> none to save;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 27:9; Prov. 1:28; Is. 1:15; Ezek. 8:18; Zech. 7:13</char></note><char style="it">Even</char> to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, but He did not answer them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="42" style="v" />Then I beat them as fine as the dust before the wind;</para>
	<para style="q2">I <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Zech. 10:5</char></note>cast them out like dirt in the streets.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="43" style="v" />You have delivered me from the strivings of the people;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 8; Ps. 89:27</char></note>You have made me the head of the nations;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 52:15</char></note>A people I have not known shall serve me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="44" style="v" />As soon as they hear of me they obey me;</para>
	<para style="q2">The foreigners submit to me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="45" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Mic. 7:17</char></note>The foreigners fade away,</para>
	<para style="q2">And come frightened from their hideouts.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="46" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> lives!</para>
	<para style="q2">Blessed <char style="it">be</char> my Rock!</para>
	<para style="q2">Let the God of my salvation be exalted.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="47" style="v" /><char style="it">It</char> <char style="it">is</char> God who avenges me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 47:3</char></note>And subdues the peoples under me;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="48" style="v" />He delivers me from my enemies.</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 27:6; 59:1</char></note>You also lift me up above those who rise against me;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have delivered me from the violent man.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="49" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 22:50; Rom. 15:9</char></note>Therefore I will give thanks to You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, among the Gentiles,</para>
	<para style="q2">And sing praises to Your name.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="50" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 7:12; Ps. 21:1; 144:10</char></note>Great deliverance He gives to His king,</para>
	<para style="q2">And shows mercy to His anointed,</para>
	<para style="q2">To David and his descendants forevermore.</para>
	<chapter number="19" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Perfect Revelation of the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />The <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 40:22; (Rom. 1:19, 20)</char></note>heavens declare the glory of God;</para>
	<para style="q2">And the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 1:6, 7</char></note>firmament shows His handiwork.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Day unto day utters speech,</para>
	<para style="q2">And night unto night reveals knowledge.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><char style="it">There</char> <char style="it">is</char> no speech nor language</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Where</char> their voice is not heard.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rom. 10:18</char></note>Their line has gone out through all the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2">And their words to the end of the world.</para>
	<para style="q1">In them He has set a tabernacle for the sun,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Which <char style="it">is</char> like a bridegroom coming out of his chamber,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Eccl. 1:5</char></note><char style="it">And</char> rejoices like a strong man to run its race.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Its rising <char style="it">is</char> from one end of heaven,</para>
	<para style="q2">And its circuit to the other end;</para>
	<para style="q2">And there is nothing hidden from its heat.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 111:7; (Rom. 7:12)</char></note>The law of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> perfect, converting the soul;</para>
	<para style="q2">The testimony of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> sure, making <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:130</char></note>wise the simple;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />The statutes of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">are</char> right, rejoicing the heart;</para>
	<para style="q2">The commandment of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> pure, enlightening the eyes;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />The fear of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> clean, enduring forever;</para>
	<para style="q2">The judgments of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">are</char> true <char style="it">and</char> righteous altogether.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />More to be desired <char style="it">are</char> <char style="it">they</char> than <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:72, 127; Prov. 8:10, 11, 19</char></note>gold,</para>
	<para style="q2">Yea, than much fine gold;</para>
	<para style="q2">Sweeter also than honey and the honeycomb.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />Moreover by them Your servant is warned,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> in keeping them <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> great reward.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />Who can understand <char style="it">his</char> errors?</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 51:1, 2)</char></note>Cleanse me from secret <char style="it">faults.</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />Keep back Your servant also from <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 15:30</char></note>presumptuous <char style="it">sins;</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Let them not have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:133; (Rom. 6:12–14)</char></note>dominion over me.</para>
	<para style="q2">Then I shall be blameless,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I shall be innocent of great transgression.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 51:15</char></note>Let the words of my mouth and the meditation of my heart</para>
	<para style="q2">Be acceptable in Your sight,</para>
	<para style="q2">O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, my strength and my <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 31:5; Is. 47:4</char></note>Redeemer.</para>
	<chapter number="20" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Assurance of God’s Saving Work</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />May the <char style="sc">Lord</char> answer you in the day of trouble;</para>
	<para style="q2">May the name of the God of Jacob defend you;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />May He send you help from the sanctuary,</para>
	<para style="q2">And strengthen you out of Zion;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />May He remember all your offerings,</para>
	<para style="q2">And accept your burnt sacrifice.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />May He grant you according to your heart’s <char style="it">desire,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 21:2</char></note>fulfill all your purpose.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />We will rejoice in your salvation,</para>
	<para style="q2">And in the name of our God we will set up <char style="it">our</char> banners!</para>
	<para style="q2">May the <char style="sc">Lord</char> fulfill all your petitions.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />Now I know that the <char style="sc">Lord</char> saves His anointed;</para>
	<para style="q2">He will answer him from His holy heaven</para>
	<para style="q2">With the saving strength of His right hand.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />Some <char style="it">trust</char> in chariots, and some in <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 20:1; Ps. 33:16, 17; Prov. 21:31; Is. 31:1</char></note>horses;</para>
	<para style="q2">But we will remember the name of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> our God.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />They have bowed down and fallen;</para>
	<para style="q2">But we have risen and stand upright.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />Save, <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q2">May the King answer us when we call.</para>
	<chapter number="21" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Joy in the Salvation of the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />The king shall have joy in Your strength, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">And in Your salvation how greatly shall he rejoice!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />You have given him his heart’s desire,</para>
	<para style="q2">And have not withheld the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 7:26–29</char></note>request of his lips.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />For You meet him with the blessings of goodness;</para>
	<para style="q2">You set a crown of pure gold upon his head.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 61:5, 6; 133:3</char></note>He asked life from You, <char style="it">and</char> You gave <char style="it">it</char> to him—</para>
	<para style="q2">Length of days forever and ever.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />His glory <char style="it">is</char> great in Your salvation;</para>
	<para style="q2">Honor and majesty You have placed upon him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />For You have made him most blessed forever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 16:11; 45:7</char></note>You have made him exceedingly glad with Your presence.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />For the king trusts in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And through the mercy of the Most High he shall not be moved.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />Your hand will find all Your enemies;</para>
	<para style="q2">Your right hand will find those who hate You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />You shall make them as a fiery oven in the time of Your anger;</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> shall swallow them up in His wrath,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the fire shall devour them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />Their offspring You shall destroy from the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2">And their descendants from among the sons of men.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />For they intended evil against You;</para>
	<para style="q2">They devised a plot <char style="it">which</char> they are not able <char style="it">to</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 2:1–4</char></note>perform.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />Therefore You will make them turn their back;</para>
	<para style="q2">You will make ready <char style="it">Your</char> <char style="it">arrows</char> on Your string toward their faces.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" />Be exalted, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, in Your own strength!</para>
	<para style="q2">We will sing and praise Your power.</para>
	<chapter number="22" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Suffering, Praise, and Posterity of the Messiah</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. Set to “The Deer of the Dawn.” A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />My <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Matt. 27:46; Mark 15:34)</char></note>God, My God, why have You forsaken Me?</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Why</char> <char style="it">are</char> <char style="it">You</char> <char style="it">so</char> far from helping Me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> <char style="it">from</char> the words of My groaning?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />O My God, I cry in the daytime, but You do not hear;</para>
	<para style="q2">And in the night season, and am not silent.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />But You <char style="it">are</char> holy,</para>
	<para style="q2">Enthroned in the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 10:21; Ps. 148:14</char></note>praises of Israel.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Our fathers trusted in You;</para>
	<para style="q2">They trusted, and You delivered them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />They cried to You, and were delivered;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 49:23</char></note>They trusted in You, and were not ashamed.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />But I <char style="it">am</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 25:6; Is. 41:14</char></note>a worm, and no man;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 109:25; (Is. 53:3); Matt. 27:39–44</char></note>A reproach of men, and despised by the people.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 27:39; Mark 15:29</char></note>All those who see Me ridicule Me;</para>
	<para style="q2">They shoot out the lip, they shake the head, <char style="it">saying,</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />“He<note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 27:43; Luke 23:35</char></note> trusted in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, let Him rescue Him;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 91:14</char></note>Let Him deliver Him, since He delights in Him!”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 71:5, 6)</char></note>But You <char style="it">are</char> He who took Me out of the womb;</para>
	<para style="q2">You made Me trust <char style="it">while</char> on My mother’s breasts.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />I was cast upon You from birth.</para>
	<para style="q2">From My mother’s womb</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 46:3; 49:1); Luke 1:35</char></note>You <char style="it">have</char> <char style="it">been</char> My God.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />Be not far from Me,</para>
	<para style="q2">For trouble <char style="it">is</char> near;</para>
	<para style="q2">For <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> none to help.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 22:21; 68:30</char></note>Many bulls have surrounded Me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Strong <char style="it">bulls</char> of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 32:14</char></note>Bashan have encircled Me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 16:10; Ps. 35:21; Lam. 2:16; 3:46</char></note>They gape at Me <char style="it">with</char> their mouths,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Like</char> a raging and roaring lion.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" />I am poured out like water,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 31:10; Dan. 5:6</char></note>And all My bones are out of joint;</para>
	<para style="q2">My heart is like wax;</para>
	<para style="q2">It has melted within Me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 17:22</char></note>My strength is dried up like a potsherd,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">John 19:28</char></note>My tongue clings to My jaws;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have brought Me to the dust of death.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" />For dogs have surrounded Me;</para>
	<para style="q2">The congregation of the wicked has enclosed Me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 53:7; Matt. 27:35; John 20:25</char></note>They pierced My hands and My feet;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />I can count all My bones.</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Luke 23:27, 35</char></note>They look <char style="it">and</char> stare at Me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 27:35; Mark 15:24; Luke 23:34; John 19:24</char></note>They divide My garments among them,</para>
	<para style="q2">And for My clothing they cast lots.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" />But You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, do not be far from Me;</para>
	<para style="q2">O My Strength, hasten to help Me!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />Deliver Me from the sword,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:17</char></note>My precious <char style="it">life</char> from the power of the dog.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Tim. 4:17</char></note>Save Me from the lion’s mouth</para>
	<para style="q2">And from the horns of the wild oxen!</para>
	<para style="q1"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 34:7</char></note>You have answered Me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="22" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 4:23; Mark 1:21, 39; Heb. 2:12</char></note>I will declare Your name to <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Rom. 8:29)</char></note>My brethren;</para>
	<para style="q2">In the midst of the assembly I will praise You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 135:19, 20</char></note>You who fear the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, praise Him!</para>
	<para style="q2">All you descendants of Jacob, glorify Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">And fear Him, all you offspring of Israel!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" />For He has not despised nor abhorred the affliction of the afflicted;</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor has He hidden His face from Him;</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 31:22; Heb. 5:7</char></note>when He cried to Him, He heard.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="25" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:18; 40:9, 10</char></note>My praise <char style="it">shall</char> <char style="it">be</char> of You in the great assembly;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 61:8; Eccl. 5:4</char></note>I will pay My vows before those who fear Him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="26" style="v" />The poor shall eat and be satisfied;</para>
	<para style="q2">Those who seek Him will praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q2">Let your heart live forever!</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="27" style="v" />All the ends of the world</para>
	<para style="q2">Shall remember and turn to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And all the families of the nations</para>
	<para style="q2">Shall worship before You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="28" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 47:7); Obad. 21; (Zech. 14:9); Matt. 6:13</char></note>For the kingdom <char style="it">is</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char>’s,</para>
	<para style="q2">And He rules over the nations.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="29" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 17:10; 45:12; Hab. 1:16</char></note>All the prosperous of the earth</para>
	<para style="q2">Shall eat and worship;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 28:1; (Is. 26:19)</char></note>All those who go down to the dust</para>
	<para style="q2">Shall bow before Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">Even he who cannot keep himself alive.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="30" style="v" />A posterity shall serve Him.</para>
	<para style="q2">It will be recounted of the Lord to the <char style="it">next</char> generation,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="31" style="v" />They will come and declare His righteousness to a people who will be born,</para>
	<para style="q2">That He has done <char style="it">this.</char></para>
	<chapter number="23" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> the Shepherd of His People</para>
	<para style="d">A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 78:52; 80:1; (Is. 40:11); Ezek. 34:11, 12; (John 10:11; 1 Pet. 2:25; Rev. 7:16, 17)</char></note>my shepherd;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 34:9, 10; Phil. 4:19)</char></note>I shall not want.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 65:11–13; Ezek. 34:14</char></note>He makes me to lie down in green pastures;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Rev. 7:17)</char></note>He leads me beside the still waters.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />He restores my soul;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 5:8; 31:3; Prov. 8:20</char></note>He leads me in the paths of righteousness</para>
	<para style="q2">For His name’s sake.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />Yea, though I walk through the valley of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 3:5; 10:21, 22; 24:17; Ps. 44:19</char></note>the shadow of death,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 3:6; 27:1)</char></note>I will fear no evil;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 16:8; (Is. 43:2)</char></note>For You <char style="it">are</char> with me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Your rod and Your staff, they comfort me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />You <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 104:15</char></note>prepare a table before me in the presence of my enemies;</para>
	<para style="q2">You <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 92:10; Luke 7:46</char></note>anoint my head with oil;</para>
	<para style="q2">My cup runs over.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Surely goodness and mercy shall follow me</para>
	<para style="q2">All the days of my life;</para>
	<para style="q2">And I will dwell in the house of the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Forever.</para>
	<chapter number="24" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The King of Glory and His Kingdom</para>
	<para style="d">A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />The <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Cor. 10:26, 28</char></note>earth <char style="it">is</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char>’s, and all its fullness,</para>
	<para style="q2">The world and those who dwell therein.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />For He has <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 89:11</char></note>founded it upon the seas,</para>
	<para style="q2">And established it upon the waters.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 15:1–5</char></note>Who may ascend into the hill of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>?</para>
	<para style="q2">Or who may stand in His holy place?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />He who has <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Job 17:9); Ps. 26:6</char></note>clean hands and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 51:10; 73:1; (Matt. 5:8)</char></note>a pure heart,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who has not lifted up his soul to an idol,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 15:4</char></note>sworn deceitfully.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />He shall receive blessing from the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And righteousness from the God of his salvation.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />This <char style="it">is</char> Jacob, the generation of those who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 27:4, 8</char></note>seek Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who seek Your face.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 118:20; Is. 26:2</char></note>Lift up your heads, O you gates!</para>
	<para style="q2">And be lifted up, you everlasting doors!</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 29:2, 9; 97:6; Hag. 2:7; Acts 7:2; (1 Cor. 2:8)</char></note>And the King of glory shall come in.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Who <char style="it">is</char> this King of glory?</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> strong and mighty,</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> mighty in <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rev. 19:13–16</char></note>battle.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />Lift up your heads, O you gates!</para>
	<para style="q2">Lift up, you everlasting doors!</para>
	<para style="q2">And the King of glory shall come in.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />Who is this King of glory?</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> of hosts,</para>
	<para style="q2">He <char style="it">is</char> the King of glory.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<chapter number="25" style="c" />
	<para style="s">A Plea for Deliverance and Forgiveness</para>
	<para style="d"><char style="it">A</char> <char style="it">Psalm</char> of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />To <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 86:4; 143:8</char></note>You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, I lift up my soul.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />O my God, I <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 34:8</char></note>trust in You;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let me not be ashamed;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 13:4; 41:11</char></note>Let not my enemies triumph over me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Indeed, let no one who waits on You be ashamed;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let those be ashamed who deal treacherously without cause.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 33:13; Ps. 5:8; 27:11; 86:11; 119:27; 143:8</char></note>Show me Your ways, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">Teach me Your paths.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Lead me in Your truth and teach me,</para>
	<para style="q2">For You <char style="it">are</char> the God of my salvation;</para>
	<para style="q2">On You I wait all the day.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />Remember, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 103:17; 106:1</char></note>Your tender mercies and Your lovingkindnesses,</para>
	<para style="q2">For they <char style="it">are</char> from of old.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Do not remember <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 13:26; (Jer. 3:25)</char></note>the sins of my youth, nor my transgressions;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 51:1</char></note>According to Your mercy remember me,</para>
	<para style="q2">For Your goodness’ sake, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />Good and upright <char style="it">is</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">Therefore He teaches sinners in the way.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />The humble He guides in justice,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the humble He teaches His way.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />All the paths of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">are</char> mercy and truth,</para>
	<para style="q2">To such as keep His covenant and His testimonies.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 31:3; 79:9; 109:21; 143:11</char></note>For Your name’s sake, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Pardon my iniquity, for it <char style="it">is</char> great.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />Who <char style="it">is</char> the man that fears the <char style="sc">Lord</char>?</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 25:8; 37:23)</char></note>Him shall He teach in the way He chooses.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Prov. 19:23)</char></note>He himself shall dwell in prosperity,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:11; 69:36; Matt. 5:5</char></note>his descendants shall inherit the earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Prov. 3:32; John 7:17)</char></note>The secret of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> with those who fear Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">And He will show them His covenant.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 123:2; 141:8)</char></note>My eyes <char style="it">are</char> ever toward the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">For He shall pluck my feet out of the net.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 69:16</char></note>Turn Yourself to me, and have mercy on me,</para>
	<para style="q2">For I <char style="it">am</char> desolate and afflicted.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />The troubles of my heart have enlarged;</para>
	<para style="q2">Bring me out of my distresses!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 16:12; Ps. 31:7</char></note>Look on my affliction and my pain,</para>
	<para style="q2">And forgive all my sins.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />Consider my enemies, for they are many;</para>
	<para style="q2">And they hate me with cruel hatred.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />Keep my soul, and deliver me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let me not be ashamed, for I put my trust in You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />Let integrity and uprightness preserve me,</para>
	<para style="q2">For I wait for You.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="22" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 130:8)</char></note>Redeem Israel, O God,</para>
	<para style="q2">Out of all their troubles!</para>
	<chapter number="26" style="c" />
	<para style="s">A Prayer for Divine Scrutiny and Redemption</para>
	<para style="d"><char style="it">A</char> <char style="it">Psalm</char> of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Vindicate <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 7:8</char></note>me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">For I have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Kin. 20:3; (Prov. 20:7)</char></note>walked in my integrity.</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 13:5; 28:7)</char></note>I have also trusted in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">I shall not slip.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 17:3; 139:23</char></note>Examine me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, and prove me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Try my mind and my heart.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />For Your lovingkindness <char style="it">is</char> before my eyes,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Kin. 20:3; Ps. 86:11</char></note>I have walked in Your truth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />I have not <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 1:1; Jer. 15:17</char></note>sat with idolatrous mortals,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor will I go in with hypocrites.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />I have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 31:6; 139:21</char></note>hated the assembly of evildoers,</para>
	<para style="q2">And will not sit with the wicked.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />I will wash my hands in innocence;</para>
	<para style="q2">So I will go about Your altar, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />That I may proclaim with the voice of thanksgiving,</para>
	<para style="q2">And tell of all Your wondrous works.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><char style="sc">Lord</char>, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 27:4; 84:1–4, 10</char></note>I have loved the habitation of Your house,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the place where Your glory dwells.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 28:3</char></note>Do not gather my soul with sinners,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor my life with bloodthirsty men,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />In whose hands <char style="it">is</char> a sinister scheme,</para>
	<para style="q2">And whose right hand is full of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 8:3</char></note>bribes.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" />But as for me, I will walk in my integrity;</para>
	<para style="q2">Redeem me and be merciful to me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 40:2</char></note>My foot stands in an even place;</para>
	<para style="q2">In the congregations I will bless the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<chapter number="27" style="c" />
	<para style="s">An Exuberant Declaration of Faith</para>
	<para style="d"><char style="it">A</char> <char style="it">Psalm</char> of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> my <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 18:28; 84:11; (Is. 60:19, 20; Mic. 7:8)</char></note>light and my salvation;</para>
	<para style="q2">Whom shall I fear?</para>
	<para style="q2">The <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 15:2; Ps. 62:7; 118:14; Is. 12:2; 33:2</char></note><char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> the strength of my life;</para>
	<para style="q2">Of whom shall I be afraid?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />When the wicked came against me</para>
	<para style="q2">To <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 14:4</char></note>eat up my flesh,</para>
	<para style="q2">My enemies and foes,</para>
	<para style="q2">They stumbled and fell.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 3:6</char></note>Though an army may encamp against me,</para>
	<para style="q2">My heart shall not fear;</para>
	<para style="q2">Though war may rise against me,</para>
	<para style="q2">In this I <char style="it">will</char> <char style="it">be</char> confident.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 26:8; 65:4</char></note>One <char style="it">thing</char> I have desired of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">That will I seek:</para>
	<para style="q2">That I may <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Luke 2:37</char></note>dwell in the house of the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="q2">All the days of my life,</para>
	<para style="q2">To behold the beauty of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And to inquire in His temple.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 31:20; 91:1</char></note>in the time of trouble</para>
	<para style="q2">He shall hide me in His pavilion;</para>
	<para style="q2">In the secret place of His tabernacle</para>
	<para style="q2">He shall hide me;</para>
	<para style="q2">He shall <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 40:2</char></note>set me high upon a rock.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />And now <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 3:3</char></note>my head shall be lifted up above my enemies all around me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Therefore I will offer sacrifices of joy in His tabernacle;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will sing, yes, I will sing praises to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />Hear, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <char style="it">when</char> I cry with my voice!</para>
	<para style="q2">Have mercy also upon me, and answer me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><char style="it">When</char> <char style="it">You</char> <char style="it">said,</char> “Seek My face,”</para>
	<para style="q2">My heart said to You, “Your face, <char style="sc">Lord</char>, I will seek.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 69:17; 143:7</char></note>Do not hide Your face from me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not turn Your servant away in anger;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have been my help;</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not leave me nor forsake me,</para>
	<para style="q2">O God of my salvation.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 49:15</char></note>When my father and my mother forsake me,</para>
	<para style="q2">Then the <char style="sc">Lord</char> will take care of me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 25:4; 86:11; 119:33</char></note>Teach me Your way, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And lead me in a smooth path, because of my enemies.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />Do not deliver me to the will of my adversaries;</para>
	<para style="q2">For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 19:18; Ps. 35:11; Matt. 26:60; Mark 14:56; John 19:33</char></note>false witnesses have risen against me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And such as breathe out violence.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><char style="it">I</char> <char style="it">would</char> <char style="it">have</char> <char style="it">lost</char> <char style="it">heart,</char> unless I had believed</para>
	<para style="q2">That I would see the goodness of the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 28:13; Ps. 52:5; 116:9; 142:5; Is. 38:11; Jer. 11:19; Ezek. 26:20</char></note>In the land of the living.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 25:3; 37:34; 40:1; 62:5; 130:5; Prov. 20:22; Is. 25:9; (Hab. 2:3)</char></note>Wait on the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">Be of good courage,</para>
	<para style="q2">And He shall strengthen your heart;</para>
	<para style="q2">Wait, I say, on the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<chapter number="28" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Rejoicing in Answered Prayer</para>
	<para style="d"><char style="it">A</char> <char style="it">Psalm</char> of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />To You I will cry, O <char style="sc">Lord</char> my Rock:</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:22; 39:12; 83:1</char></note>Do not be silent to me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 88:4; 143:7; Prov. 1:12</char></note>Lest, if You <char style="it">are</char> silent to me,</para>
	<para style="q2">I become like those who go down to the pit.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Hear the voice of my supplications</para>
	<para style="q2">When I cry to You,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 5:7</char></note>When I lift up my hands <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 138:2</char></note>toward Your holy sanctuary.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />Do not take me away with the wicked</para>
	<para style="q2">And with the workers of iniquity,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 12:2; 55:21; 62:4; Jer. 9:8</char></note>Who speak peace to their neighbors,</para>
	<para style="q2">But evil <char style="it">is</char> in their hearts.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 62:12); 2 Tim. 4:14; (Rev. 18:6; 22:12)</char></note>Give them according to their deeds,</para>
	<para style="q2">And according to the wickedness of their endeavors;</para>
	<para style="q2">Give them according to the work of their hands;</para>
	<para style="q2">Render to them what they deserve.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Because <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 5:12</char></note>they do not regard the works of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor the operation of His hands,</para>
	<para style="q2">He shall destroy them</para>
	<para style="q2">And not build them up.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />Blessed <char style="it">be</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because He has heard the voice of my supplications!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 18:2; 59:17</char></note>my strength and my shield;</para>
	<para style="q2">My heart <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 13:5; 112:7</char></note>trusted in Him, and I am helped;</para>
	<para style="q2">Therefore my heart greatly rejoices,</para>
	<para style="q2">And with my song I will praise Him.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> their strength,</para>
	<para style="q2">And He <char style="it">is</char> the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 20:6</char></note>saving refuge of His anointed.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />Save Your people,</para>
	<para style="q2">And bless <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 9:29; 32:9; 1 Kin. 8:51; Ps. 33:12); 106:40</char></note>Your inheritance;</para>
	<para style="q2">Shepherd them also,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 1:31; Is. 63:9</char></note>And bear them up forever.</para>
	<chapter number="29" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Praise to God in His Holiness and Majesty</para>
	<para style="d">A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Give <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 16:28, 29</char></note>unto the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, O you mighty ones,</para>
	<para style="q2">Give unto the <char style="sc">Lord</char> glory and strength.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Give unto the <char style="sc">Lord</char> the glory due to His name;</para>
	<para style="q2">Worship the <char style="sc">Lord</char> in <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Chr. 20:21; Ps. 110:3</char></note>the beauty of holiness.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />The voice of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> over the waters;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Job 37:4, 5); Ps. 18:13; Acts 7:2</char></note>The God of glory thunders;</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> over many waters.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />The voice of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> powerful;</para>
	<para style="q2">The voice of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> full of majesty.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />The voice of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> breaks <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Judg. 9:15; 1 Kin. 5:6; Ps. 104:16; Is. 2:13; 14:8</char></note>the cedars,</para>
	<para style="q2">Yes, the <char style="sc">Lord</char> splinters the cedars of Lebanon.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 114:4</char></note>He makes them also skip like a calf,</para>
	<para style="q2">Lebanon and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 3:9</char></note>Sirion like a young wild ox.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />The voice of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> divides the flames of fire.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />The voice of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> shakes the wilderness;</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> shakes the Wilderness of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 13:26</char></note>Kadesh.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />The voice of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> makes the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 39:1</char></note>deer give birth,</para>
	<para style="q2">And strips the forests bare;</para>
	<para style="q2">And in His temple everyone says, “Glory!”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />The <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 6:17; Job 38:8, 25</char></note><char style="sc">Lord</char> sat <char style="it">enthroned</char> at the Flood,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 10:16</char></note>the <char style="sc">Lord</char> sits as King forever.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 28:8; 68:35; (Is. 40:29)</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> will give strength to His people;</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> will bless His people with peace.</para>
	<chapter number="30" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Blessedness of Answered Prayer</para>
	<para style="d">A Psalm. A Song <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 20:5</char></note>at the dedication of the house of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />I will extol You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, for You have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 28:9</char></note>lifted me up,</para>
	<para style="q2">And have not let my foes <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 25:2</char></note>rejoice over me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />O <char style="sc">Lord</char> my God, I cried out to You,</para>
	<para style="q2">And You <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 6:2; 103:3; (Is. 53:5)</char></note>healed me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 86:13</char></note>You brought my soul up from the grave;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have kept me alive, that I should not go down to the pit.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 97:12</char></note>Sing praise to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, you saints of His,</para>
	<para style="q2">And give thanks at the remembrance of His holy name.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 103:9; Is. 26:20; 54:7, 8</char></note>His anger <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">but</char> <char style="it">for</char> a moment,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 63:3</char></note>His favor <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">for</char> life;</para>
	<para style="q2">Weeping may endure for a night,</para>
	<para style="q2">But joy <char style="it">comes</char> in the morning.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />Now in my prosperity I said,</para>
	<para style="q2">“I shall never be moved.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><char style="sc">Lord</char>, by Your favor You have made my mountain stand strong;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 31:17; Ps. 104:29; 143:7)</char></note>You hid Your face, <char style="it">and</char> I was troubled.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />I cried out to You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">And to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> I made supplication:</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />“What profit <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">there</char> in my blood,</para>
	<para style="q2">When I go down to the pit?</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 6:5)</char></note>Will the dust praise You?</para>
	<para style="q2">Will it declare Your truth?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />Hear, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, and have mercy on me;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="sc">Lord</char>, be my helper!”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Eccl. 3:4; Is. 61:3; Jer. 31:4</char></note>You have turned for me my mourning into dancing;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have put off my sackcloth and clothed me with gladness,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />To the end that <char style="it">my</char> glory may sing praise to You and not be silent.</para>
	<para style="q2">O <char style="sc">Lord</char> my God, I will give thanks to You forever.</para>
	<chapter number="31" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> a Fortress in Adversity</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />In <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 22:5</char></note>You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, I put my trust;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let me never be ashamed;</para>
	<para style="q2">Deliver me in Your righteousness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 17:6; 71:2; 86:1; 102:2</char></note>Bow down Your ear to me,</para>
	<para style="q2">Deliver me speedily;</para>
	<para style="q2">Be my rock of refuge,</para>
	<para style="q2">A fortress of defense to save me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 18:2)</char></note>For You <char style="it">are</char> my rock and my fortress;</para>
	<para style="q2">Therefore, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 23:3; 25:11</char></note>for Your name’s sake,</para>
	<para style="q2">Lead me and guide me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Pull me out of the net which they have secretly laid for me,</para>
	<para style="q2">For You <char style="it">are</char> my strength.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Luke 23:46</char></note>Into Your hand I commit my spirit;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have redeemed me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char> God of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 32:4); Ps. 71:22</char></note>truth.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />I have hated those <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jon. 2:8</char></note>who regard useless idols;</para>
	<para style="q2">But I trust in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />I will be glad and rejoice in Your mercy,</para>
	<para style="q2">For You have considered my trouble;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(John 10:27)</char></note>known my soul in adversities,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />And have not <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 32:30); Ps. 37:33</char></note>shut me up into the hand of the enemy;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 4:1; 18:19)</char></note>You have set my feet in a wide place.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />Have mercy on me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, for I am in trouble;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 6:7</char></note>My eye wastes away with grief,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Yes,</char> my soul and my body!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />For my life is spent with grief,</para>
	<para style="q2">And my years with sighing;</para>
	<para style="q2">My strength fails because of my iniquity,</para>
	<para style="q2">And my bones waste away.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 53:4)</char></note>I am a reproach among all my enemies,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 19:13; Ps. 38:11; 88:8, 18</char></note>especially among my neighbors,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">am</char> repulsive to my acquaintances;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 64:8</char></note>Those who see me outside flee from me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 88:4, 5</char></note>I am forgotten like a dead man, out of mind;</para>
	<para style="q2">I am like a broken vessel.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 50:20; Jer. 20:10</char></note>For I hear the slander of many;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lam. 2:22</char></note>Fear <char style="it">is</char> on every side;</para>
	<para style="q2">While they <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 62:4; Matt. 27:1</char></note>take counsel together against me,</para>
	<para style="q2">They scheme to take away my life.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" />But as for me, I trust in You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">I say, “You <char style="it">are</char> my God.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />My times <char style="it">are</char> in Your <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Job 14:5; 24:1)</char></note>hand;</para>
	<para style="q2">Deliver me from the hand of my enemies,</para>
	<para style="q2">And from those who persecute me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 4:6; 80:3</char></note>Make Your face shine upon Your servant;</para>
	<para style="q2">Save me for Your mercies’ sake.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 25:2, 20</char></note>Do not let me be ashamed, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, for I have called upon You;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let the wicked be ashamed;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Sam. 2:9); Ps. 94:17; 115:17</char></note>Let them be silent in the grave.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 109:2; 120:2</char></note>Let the lying lips be put to silence,</para>
	<para style="q2">Which <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Sam. 2:3); Ps. 94:4; (Jude 15)</char></note>speak insolent things proudly and contemptuously against the righteous.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 145:7; (Rom. 2:4; 11:22)</char></note>Oh, how great <char style="it">is</char> Your goodness,</para>
	<para style="q2">Which You have laid up for those who fear You,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Which</char> You have prepared for those who trust in You</para>
	<para style="q2">In the presence of the sons of men!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 27:5; 32:7)</char></note>You shall hide them in the secret place of Your presence</para>
	<para style="q2">From the plots of man;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 5:21</char></note>You shall keep them secretly in a pavilion</para>
	<para style="q2">From the strife of tongues.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="21" style="v" />Blessed <char style="it">be</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 17:7)</char></note>He has shown me His marvelous kindness in a strong city!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" />For I said in my haste,</para>
	<para style="q2">“I am cut off from before Your eyes”;</para>
	<para style="q2">Nevertheless You heard the voice of my supplications</para>
	<para style="q2">When I cried out to You.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="23" style="v" />Oh, love the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, all you His saints!</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">For</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char> preserves the faithful,</para>
	<para style="q2">And fully repays the proud person.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 27:14)</char></note>Be of good courage,</para>
	<para style="q2">And He shall strengthen your heart,</para>
	<para style="q2">All you who hope in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<chapter number="32" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Joy of Forgiveness</para>
	<para style="d"><char style="it">A</char> <char style="it">Psalm</char> of David. A Contemplation.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Blessed <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">he</char> <char style="it">whose</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 85:2; 103:3); Rom. 4:7, 8</char></note>transgression <char style="it">is</char> forgiven,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Whose</char> sin <char style="it">is</char> covered.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Blessed <char style="it">is</char> the man to whom the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(2 Cor. 5:19)</char></note>does not impute iniquity,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">John 1:47</char></note>in whose spirit <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> no deceit.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />When I kept silent, my bones grew old</para>
	<para style="q2">Through my groaning all the day long.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />For day and night Your <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 5:6; Ps. 38:2; 39:10</char></note>hand was heavy upon me;</para>
	<para style="q2">My vitality was turned into the drought of summer.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />I acknowledged my sin to You,</para>
	<para style="q2">And my iniquity I have not hidden.</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 12:13; Ps. 38:18; (Prov. 28:13; 1 John 1:9)</char></note>I said, “I will confess my transgressions to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,”</para>
	<para style="q2">And You forgave the iniquity of my sin.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Tim. 1:16)</char></note>For this cause everyone who is godly shall <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 69:13; Is. 55:6</char></note>pray to You</para>
	<para style="q2">In a time when You may be found;</para>
	<para style="q2">Surely in a flood of great waters</para>
	<para style="q2">They shall not come near him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 9:9</char></note>You <char style="it">are</char> my hiding place;</para>
	<para style="q2">You shall preserve me from trouble;</para>
	<para style="q2">You shall surround me with <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 15:1; Judg. 5:1; (Ps. 40:3)</char></note>songs of deliverance.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />I will instruct you and teach you in the way you should go;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will guide you with My eye.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />Do not be like the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 26:3</char></note>horse <char style="it">or</char> like the mule,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Which</char> have no understanding,</para>
	<para style="q2">Which must be harnessed with bit and bridle,</para>
	<para style="q2">Else they will not come near you.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 16:4; (Prov. 13:21; Rom. 2:9)</char></note>Many sorrows <char style="it">shall</char> <char style="it">be</char> to the wicked;</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 5:11, 12); Prov. 16:20</char></note>he who trusts in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, mercy shall surround him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 64:10; 68:3; 97:12</char></note>Be glad in the <char style="sc">Lord</char> and rejoice, you righteous;</para>
	<para style="q2">And shout for joy, all <char style="it">you</char> upright in heart!</para>
	<chapter number="33" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Sovereignty of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> in Creation and History</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Rejoice <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 32:11; 97:12; Phil. 3:1; 4:4</char></note>in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, O you righteous!</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">For</char> praise from the upright is beautiful.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char> with the harp;</para>
	<para style="q2">Make melody to Him with an instrument of ten strings.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Sing to Him a new song;</para>
	<para style="q2">Play skillfully with a shout of joy.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />For the word of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> right,</para>
	<para style="q2">And all His work <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">done</char> in truth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />He loves righteousness and justice;</para>
	<para style="q2">The earth is full of the goodness of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 1:6, 7; Ps. 148:5; (Heb. 11:3; 2 Pet. 3:5)</char></note>By the word of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> the heavens were made,</para>
	<para style="q2">And all the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 2:1</char></note>host of them <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Job 26:13)</char></note>by the breath of His mouth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 1:9; Job 26:10; 38:8</char></note>He gathers the waters of the sea together as a heap;</para>
	<para style="q2">He lays up the deep in storehouses.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />Let all the earth fear the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let all the inhabitants of the world stand in awe of Him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 1:3; Ps. 148:5</char></note>He spoke, and it was <char style="it">done;</char></para>
	<para style="q2">He commanded, and it stood fast.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 2:1–3); Is. 8:10; 19:3</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> brings the counsel of the nations to nothing;</para>
	<para style="q2">He makes the plans of the peoples of no effect.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Job 23:13; Prov. 19:21)</char></note>The counsel of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> stands forever,</para>
	<para style="q2">The plans of His heart to all generations.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />Blessed <char style="it">is</char> the nation whose God <char style="it">is</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">The people He has <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 19:5; Deut. 7:6); Ps. 28:9</char></note>chosen as His own inheritance.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 28:24; (Ps. 14:2)</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> looks from heaven;</para>
	<para style="q2">He sees all the sons of men.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />From the place of His dwelling He looks</para>
	<para style="q2">On all the inhabitants of the earth;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />He fashions their hearts individually;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(2 Chr. 16:9); Job 34:21; (Jer. 32:19)</char></note>He considers all their works.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 44:6; 60:11; (Jer. 9:23, 24)</char></note>No king <char style="it">is</char> saved by the multitude of an army;</para>
	<para style="q2">A mighty man is not delivered by great strength.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 20:7; 147:10; Prov. 21:31)</char></note>A horse <char style="it">is</char> a vain hope for safety;</para>
	<para style="q2">Neither shall it deliver <char style="it">any</char> by its great strength.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Job 36:7); Ps. 32:8; 34:15; (1 Pet. 3:12)</char></note>Behold, the eye of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> on those who fear Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">On those who hope in His mercy,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />To deliver their soul from death,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 5:20; Ps. 37:19</char></note>to keep them alive in famine.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="20" style="v" />Our soul waits for the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">He <char style="it">is</char> our help and our shield.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />For our heart shall rejoice in Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because we have trusted in His holy name.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" />Let Your mercy, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, be upon us,</para>
	<para style="q2">Just as we hope in You.</para>
	<chapter number="34" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Happiness of Those Who Trust in God</para>
	<para style="d"><char style="it">A</char> <char style="it">Psalm</char> of David <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 21:10–15</char></note>when he pretended madness before Abimelech, who drove him away, and he departed.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />I will <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Eph. 5:20; 1 Thess. 5:18)</char></note>bless the <char style="sc">Lord</char> at all times;</para>
	<para style="q2">His praise <char style="it">shall</char> continually <char style="it">be</char> in my mouth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />My soul shall make its boast in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">The humble shall hear <char style="it">of</char> <char style="it">it</char> and be glad.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Oh, magnify the <char style="sc">Lord</char> with me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And let us exalt His name together.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />I <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(2 Chr. 15:2; Ps. 9:10; Matt. 7:7; Luke 11:9)</char></note>sought the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, and He heard me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And delivered me from all my fears.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />They looked to Him and were radiant,</para>
	<para style="q2">And their faces were not ashamed.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />This poor man cried out, and the <char style="sc">Lord</char> heard <char style="it">him,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">And saved him out of all his troubles.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 91:11); Dan. 6:22</char></note>The angel of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Kin. 6:17</char></note>encamps all around those who fear Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">And delivers them.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />Oh, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:103; (Heb. 6:5); 1 Pet. 2:3</char></note>taste and see that the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> good;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 2:12</char></note>Blessed <char style="it">is</char> the man <char style="it">who</char> trusts in Him!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />Oh, fear the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, you His saints!</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">There</char> <char style="it">is</char> no want to those who fear Him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />The young lions lack and suffer hunger;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 84:11)</char></note>But those who seek the <char style="sc">Lord</char> shall not lack any good <char style="it">thing.</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" />Come, you children, listen to me;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 32:8</char></note>I will teach you the fear of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Pet. 3:10–12)</char></note>Who <char style="it">is</char> the man <char style="it">who</char> desires life,</para>
	<para style="q2">And loves <char style="it">many</char> days, that he may see good?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />Keep your tongue from evil,</para>
	<para style="q2">And your lips from speaking <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Eph. 4:25)</char></note>deceit.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:27; Is. 1:16, 17</char></note>Depart from evil and do good;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Rom. 14:19; Heb. 12:14)</char></note>Seek peace and pursue it.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 36:7; (Ps. 33:18)</char></note>The eyes of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">are</char> on the righteous,</para>
	<para style="q2">And His ears <char style="it">are</char> <char style="it">open</char> to their cry.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 17:10; Jer. 44:11; Amos 9:4</char></note>The face of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> against those who do evil,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 18:17; Ps. 9:6; 109:15; (Prov. 10:7)</char></note>To cut off the remembrance of them from the earth.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="17" style="v" /><char style="it">The</char> <char style="it">righteous</char> cry out, and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 34:6; 145:19</char></note>the <char style="sc">Lord</char> hears,</para>
	<para style="q2">And delivers them out of all their troubles.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 145:18)</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> near <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 51:17; (Is. 57:15)</char></note>to those who have a broken heart,</para>
	<para style="q2">And saves such as have a contrite spirit.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 24:16</char></note>Many <char style="it">are</char> the afflictions of the righteous,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 34:4, 6, 17</char></note>But the <char style="sc">Lord</char> delivers him out of them all.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />He guards all his bones;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">John 19:33, 36</char></note>Not one of them is broken.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 94:23; 140:11; Prov. 24:16</char></note>Evil shall slay the wicked,</para>
	<para style="q2">And those who hate the righteous shall be condemned.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 1:29</char></note>redeems the soul of His servants,</para>
	<para style="q2">And none of those who trust in Him shall be condemned.</para>
	<chapter number="35" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> the Avenger of His People</para>
	<para style="d"><char style="it">A</char> <char style="it">Psalm</char> of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Plead <char style="it">my</char> <char style="it">cause,</char> O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, with those who strive with me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Fight against those who fight against me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Take hold of shield and buckler,</para>
	<para style="q2">And stand up for my help.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Also draw out the spear,</para>
	<para style="q2">And stop those who pursue me.</para>
	<para style="q2">Say to my soul,</para>
	<para style="q2">“I <char style="it">am</char> your salvation.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 40:14, 15; 70:2, 3</char></note>Let those be put to shame and brought to dishonor</para>
	<para style="q2">Who seek after my life;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let those be <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 129:5</char></note>turned back and brought to confusion</para>
	<para style="q2">Who plot my hurt.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 21:18; Ps. 83:13; Is. 29:5</char></note>Let them be like chaff before the wind,</para>
	<para style="q2">And let the angel of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> chase <char style="it">them.</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Let their way be <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 73:18; Jer. 23:12</char></note>dark and slippery,</para>
	<para style="q2">And let the angel of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> pursue them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />For without cause they have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 9:15</char></note>hidden their net for me <char style="it">in</char> a pit,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Which</char> they have dug without cause for my life.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Let <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 55:23); Is. 47:11; (1 Thess. 5:3)</char></note>destruction come upon him unexpectedly,</para>
	<para style="q2">And let his net that he has hidden catch himself;</para>
	<para style="q2">Into that very destruction let him fall.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />And my soul shall be joyful in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">It shall rejoice in His salvation.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 51:8</char></note>All my bones shall say,</para>
	<para style="q2">“<char style="sc">Lord</char>, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 15:11); Ps. 71:19; 86:8; (Mic. 7:18)</char></note>who <char style="it">is</char> like You,</para>
	<para style="q2">Delivering the poor from him who is too strong for him,</para>
	<para style="q2">Yes, the poor and the needy from him who plunders him?”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" />Fierce witnesses rise up;</para>
	<para style="q2">They ask me <char style="it">things</char> that I do not know.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 38:20; 109:5; Jer. 18:20; John 10:32</char></note>They reward me evil for good,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">To</char> the sorrow of my soul.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />But as for me, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 30:25</char></note>when they were sick,</para>
	<para style="q2">My clothing <char style="it">was</char> sackcloth;</para>
	<para style="q2">I humbled myself with fasting;</para>
	<para style="q2">And my prayer would return to my own heart.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />I paced about as though <char style="it">he</char> <char style="it">were</char> my friend <char style="it">or</char> brother;</para>
	<para style="q2">I bowed down heavily, as one who mourns <char style="it">for</char> <char style="it">his</char> mother.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" />But in my adversity they rejoiced</para>
	<para style="q2">And gathered together;</para>
	<para style="q2">Attackers gathered against me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I did not know <char style="it">it;</char></para>
	<para style="q2">They tore <char style="it">at</char> <char style="it">me</char> and did not cease;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />With ungodly mockers at feasts</para>
	<para style="q2">They gnashed at me with their teeth.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="17" style="v" />Lord, how long will You <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 13:1; (Hab. 1:13)</char></note>look on?</para>
	<para style="q2">Rescue me from their destructions,</para>
	<para style="q2">My precious <char style="it">life</char> from the lions.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />I will give You thanks in the great assembly;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will praise You among many people.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 69:4; 109:3; Lam. 3:52; (John 15:25)</char></note>Let them not rejoice over me who are wrongfully my enemies;</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor let them wink with the eye who hate me without a cause.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />For they do not speak peace,</para>
	<para style="q2">But they devise deceitful matters</para>
	<para style="q2">Against <char style="it">the</char> quiet ones in the land.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />They also opened their mouth wide against me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> said, “Aha, aha!</para>
	<para style="q2">Our eyes have seen <char style="it">it.</char>”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="22" style="v" /><char style="it">This</char> You have seen, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not keep silence.</para>
	<para style="q2">O Lord, do not be far from me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" />Stir up Yourself, and awake to my vindication,</para>
	<para style="q2">To my cause, my God and my Lord.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" />Vindicate me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char> my God, according to Your righteousness;</para>
	<para style="q2">And let them not rejoice over me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="25" style="v" />Let them not say in their hearts, “Ah, so we would have it!”</para>
	<para style="q2">Let them not say, “We have swallowed him up.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="26" style="v" />Let them be ashamed and brought to mutual confusion</para>
	<para style="q2">Who rejoice at my hurt;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let them be <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 109:29</char></note>clothed with shame and dishonor</para>
	<para style="q2">Who exalt themselves against me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="27" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rom. 12:15</char></note>Let them shout for joy and be glad,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who favor my righteous cause;</para>
	<para style="q2">And let them say continually,</para>
	<para style="q2">“Let the <char style="sc">Lord</char> be magnified,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who has pleasure in the prosperity of His servant.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="28" style="v" />And my tongue shall speak of Your righteousness</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> of Your praise all the day long.</para>
	<chapter number="36" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Man’s Wickedness and God’s Perfections</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. <char style="it">A</char> <char style="it">Psalm</char> of David the servant of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />An oracle within my heart concerning the transgression of the wicked:</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rom. 3:18</char></note><char style="it">There</char> <char style="it">is</char> no fear of God before his eyes.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />For he flatters himself in his own eyes,</para>
	<para style="q2">When he finds out his iniquity <char style="it">and</char> when he hates.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />The words of his mouth <char style="it">are</char> wickedness and deceit;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 94:8; Jer. 4:22</char></note>He has ceased to be wise <char style="it">and</char> to do good.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 4:16; (Mic. 2:1)</char></note>He devises wickedness on his bed;</para>
	<para style="q2">He sets himself <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 65:2</char></note>in a way <char style="it">that</char> <char style="it">is</char> not good;</para>
	<para style="q2">He does not abhor <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 52:3; Rom. 12:9)</char></note>evil.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />Your mercy, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <char style="it">is</char> in the heavens;</para>
	<para style="q2">Your faithfulness <char style="it">reaches</char> to the clouds.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Your righteousness <char style="it">is</char> like the great mountains;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 11:8; Ps. 77:19; (Rom. 11:33)</char></note>Your judgments <char style="it">are</char> a great deep;</para>
	<para style="q2">O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, You preserve man and beast.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />How precious <char style="it">is</char> Your lovingkindness, O God!</para>
	<para style="q2">Therefore the children of men <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ruth 2:12; Ps. 17:8; 57:1; 91:4</char></note>put their trust under the shadow of Your wings.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 63:5; 65:4; Is. 25:6; Jer. 31:12–14</char></note>They are abundantly satisfied with the fullness of Your house,</para>
	<para style="q2">And You give them drink from <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 46:4; Rev. 22:1</char></note>the river of Your pleasures.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Jer. 2:13; John 4:10, 14)</char></note>For with You <char style="it">is</char> the fountain of life;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Pet. 2:9)</char></note>In Your light we see light.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />Oh, continue Your lovingkindness to those who know You,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Your righteousness to the upright in heart.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />Let not the foot of pride come against me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And let not the hand of the wicked drive me away.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />There the workers of iniquity have fallen;</para>
	<para style="q2">They have been cast down and are not able to rise.</para>
	<chapter number="37" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Heritage of the Righteous and the Calamity of the Wicked</para>
	<para style="d"><char style="it">A</char> <char style="it">Psalm</char> of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Do<note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 73:3; (Prov. 23:17; 24:19)</char></note> not fret because of evildoers,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor be envious of the workers of iniquity.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />For they shall soon be cut down <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 14:2; Ps. 90:5, 6; 92:7; James 1:11</char></note>like the grass,</para>
	<para style="q2">And wither as the green herb.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />Trust in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, and do good;</para>
	<para style="q2">Dwell in the land, and feed on His faithfulness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 22:26; Ps. 94:19; Is. 58:14</char></note>Delight yourself also in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And He shall give you the desires of your <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 21:2; 145:19; (Matt. 7:7, 8)</char></note>heart.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 55:22; Prov. 16:3; 1 Pet. 5:7)</char></note>Commit your way to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Trust also in Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">And He shall bring <char style="it">it</char> to pass.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 11:17; (Is. 58:8, 10)</char></note>He shall bring forth your righteousness as the light,</para>
	<para style="q2">And your justice as the noonday.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />Rest in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 40:1; 62:5; (Lam. 3:26)</char></note>and wait patiently for Him;</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not fret because of him who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 73:3–12)</char></note>prospers in his way,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because of the man who brings wicked schemes to pass.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Eph. 4:26)</char></note>Cease from anger, and forsake wrath;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 73:3</char></note>Do not fret—<char style="it">it</char> only <char style="it">causes</char> harm.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />For evildoers shall be cut off;</para>
	<para style="q2">But those who wait on the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">They shall <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 25:13; Prov. 2:21; (Is. 57:13; 60:21; Matt. 5:5)</char></note>inherit the earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Heb. 10:37)</char></note>yet a little while and the wicked <char style="it">shall</char> <char style="it">be</char> no <char style="it">more;</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Indeed, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 7:10; Ps. 37:35, 36</char></note>you will look carefully for his place,</para>
	<para style="q2">But it <char style="it">shall</char> <char style="it">be</char> no <char style="it">more.</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Matt. 5:5)</char></note>But the meek shall inherit the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2">And shall delight themselves in the abundance of peace.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />The wicked plots against the just,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:16</char></note>And gnashes at him with his teeth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 2:4; 59:8</char></note>The Lord laughs at him,</para>
	<para style="q2">For He sees that <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 26:10; Job 18:20</char></note>his day is coming.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />The wicked have drawn the sword</para>
	<para style="q2">And have bent their bow,</para>
	<para style="q2">To cast down the poor and needy,</para>
	<para style="q2">To slay those who are of upright conduct.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />Their sword shall enter their own heart,</para>
	<para style="q2">And their bows shall be broken.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 15:16; 16:8; (1 Tim. 6:6)</char></note>A little that a righteous man has</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Is</char> better than the riches of many wicked.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />For the arms of the wicked shall be broken,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the <char style="sc">Lord</char> upholds the righteous.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="18" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> knows the days of the upright,</para>
	<para style="q2">And their inheritance shall be forever.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />They shall not be ashamed in the evil time,</para>
	<para style="q2">And in the days of famine they shall be satisfied.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />But the wicked shall perish;</para>
	<para style="q2">And the enemies of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Like the splendor of the meadows, shall vanish.</para>
	<para style="q2">Into smoke they shall vanish away.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="21" style="v" />The wicked borrows and does not repay,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 112:5, 9</char></note>the righteous shows mercy and gives.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Prov. 3:33)</char></note>For <char style="it">those</char> blessed by Him shall inherit the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <char style="it">those</char> cursed by Him shall be cut off.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="23" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Sam. 2:9); Ps. 40:2; 66:9; 119:5</char></note>The steps of a <char style="it">good</char> man are ordered by the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And He delights in his way.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 24:16</char></note>Though he fall, he shall not be utterly cast down;</para>
	<para style="q2">For the <char style="sc">Lord</char> upholds <char style="it">him</char> <char style="it">with</char> His hand.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="25" style="v" />I have been young, and <char style="it">now</char> am old;</para>
	<para style="q2">Yet I have not seen the righteous forsaken,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor his descendants begging bread.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="26" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 15:8); Ps. 37:21</char></note><char style="it">He</char> <char style="it">is</char> ever merciful, and lends;</para>
	<para style="q2">And his descendants <char style="it">are</char> blessed.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="27" style="v" />Depart from evil, and do good;</para>
	<para style="q2">And dwell forevermore.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="28" style="v" />For the <char style="sc">Lord</char> loves justice,</para>
	<para style="q2">And does not forsake His saints;</para>
	<para style="q2">They are preserved forever,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the descendants of the wicked shall be cut off.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="29" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:9; Prov. 2:21</char></note>The righteous shall inherit the land,</para>
	<para style="q2">And dwell in it forever.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="30" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Matt. 12:35)</char></note>The mouth of the righteous speaks wisdom,</para>
	<para style="q2">And his tongue talks of justice.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="31" style="v" />The law of his God <char style="it">is</char> in his heart;</para>
	<para style="q2">None of his steps shall slide.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="32" style="v" />The wicked <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 10:8; 17:11</char></note>watches the righteous,</para>
	<para style="q2">And seeks to slay him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="33" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 31:8; (2 Pet. 2:9)</char></note>will not leave him in his hand,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor condemn him when he is judged.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="34" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 27:14; 37:9</char></note>Wait on the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And keep His way,</para>
	<para style="q2">And He shall exalt you to inherit the land;</para>
	<para style="q2">When the wicked are cut off, you shall see <char style="it">it.</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="35" style="v" />I have seen the wicked in great power,</para>
	<para style="q2">And spreading himself like a native green tree.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="36" style="v" />Yet he passed away, and behold, he <char style="it">was</char> no <char style="it">more;</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Indeed I sought him, but he could not be found.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="37" style="v" />Mark the blameless <char style="it">man,</char> and observe the upright;</para>
	<para style="q2">For the future of <char style="it">that</char> man <char style="it">is</char> peace.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="38" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 1:4–6; 37:20, 28)</char></note>But the transgressors shall be destroyed together;</para>
	<para style="q2">The future of the wicked shall be cut off.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="39" style="v" />But the salvation of the righteous <char style="it">is</char> from the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">He</char> <char style="it">is</char> their strength <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 9:9; 37:19</char></note>in the time of trouble.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="40" style="v" />And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 22:4; Is. 31:5; Dan. 3:17; 6:23</char></note>the <char style="sc">Lord</char> shall help them and deliver them;</para>
	<para style="q2">He shall deliver them from the wicked,</para>
	<para style="q2">And save them,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 5:20; Ps. 34:22</char></note>Because they trust in Him.</para>
	<chapter number="38" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Prayer in Time of Chastening</para>
	<para style="d">A Psalm of David. <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 70:title</char></note>To bring to remembrance.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, do not <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 6:1</char></note>rebuke me in Your wrath,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor chasten me in Your hot displeasure!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />For Your arrows pierce me deeply,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Your hand presses me down.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" /><char style="it">There</char> <char style="it">is</char> no soundness in my flesh</para>
	<para style="q2">Because of Your anger,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor <char style="it">any</char> health in my bones</para>
	<para style="q2">Because of my sin.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />For my iniquities have gone over my head;</para>
	<para style="q2">Like a heavy burden they are too heavy for me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />My wounds are foul <char style="it">and</char> festering</para>
	<para style="q2">Because of my foolishness.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />I am troubled, I am bowed down greatly;</para>
	<para style="q2">I go mourning all the day long.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />For my loins are full of inflammation,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> no soundness in my flesh.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />I am feeble and severely broken;</para>
	<para style="q2">I groan because of the turmoil of my heart.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />Lord, all my desire <char style="it">is</char> before You;</para>
	<para style="q2">And my sighing is not hidden from You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />My heart pants, my strength fails me;</para>
	<para style="q2">As for the light of my eyes, it also has gone from me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" />My loved ones and my friends <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 31:11; 88:18</char></note>stand aloof from my plague,</para>
	<para style="q2">And my relatives stand afar off.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />Those also who seek my life lay snares <char style="it">for</char> <char style="it">me;</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Those who seek my hurt speak of destruction,</para>
	<para style="q2">And plan deception all the day long.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" />But I, like a deaf <char style="it">man,</char> do not hear;</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">I</char> <char style="it">am</char> like a mute <char style="it">who</char> does not open his mouth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />Thus I am like a man who does not hear,</para>
	<para style="q2">And in whose mouth <char style="it">is</char> no response.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" />For in You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 39:7)</char></note>I hope;</para>
	<para style="q2">You will hear, O Lord my God.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />For I said, <char style="it">“Hear me,</char> lest they rejoice over me,</para>
	<para style="q2">Lest, when my foot slips, they exalt <char style="it">themselves</char> against me.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 51:3</char></note>For I <char style="it">am</char> ready to fall,</para>
	<para style="q2">And my sorrow <char style="it">is</char> continually before me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />For I will <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 32:5</char></note>declare my iniquity;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will be <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(2 Cor. 7:9, 10)</char></note>in anguish over my sin.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />But my enemies <char style="it">are</char> vigorous, <char style="it">and</char> they are strong;</para>
	<para style="q2">And those who hate me wrongfully have multiplied.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />Those also <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:12</char></note>who render evil for good,</para>
	<para style="q2">They are my adversaries, because I follow <char style="it">what</char> <char style="it">is</char> good.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="21" style="v" />Do not forsake me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">O my God, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 22:19; 35:22</char></note>be not far from me!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" />Make haste to help me,</para>
	<para style="q2">O Lord, my salvation!</para>
	<chapter number="39" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Prayer for Wisdom and Forgiveness</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. To Jeduthun. A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />I said, “I will guard my ways,</para>
	<para style="q2">Lest I sin with my <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 2:10; Ps. 34:13; (James 3:5–12)</char></note>tongue;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will restrain my mouth with a muzzle,</para>
	<para style="q2">While the wicked are before me.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 38:13</char></note>I was mute with silence,</para>
	<para style="q2">I held my peace <char style="it">even</char> from good;</para>
	<para style="q2">And my sorrow was stirred up.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />My heart was hot within me;</para>
	<para style="q2">While I was musing, the fire burned.</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Then</char> I spoke with my tongue:</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />“<char style="sc">Lord</char>, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 90:12; 119:84</char></note>make me to know my end,</para>
	<para style="q2">And what <char style="it">is</char> the measure of my days,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">That</char> I may know how frail I <char style="it">am.</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Indeed, You have made my days <char style="it">as</char> handbreadths,</para>
	<para style="q2">And my age <char style="it">is</char> as nothing before You;</para>
	<para style="q2">Certainly every man at his best state <char style="it">is</char> but <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 62:9; (Eccl. 6:12)</char></note>vapor.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Surely every man walks about like a shadow;</para>
	<para style="q2">Surely they busy themselves in vain;</para>
	<para style="q2">He heaps up <char style="it">riches,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">And does not know who will gather them.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />“And now, Lord, what do I wait for?</para>
	<para style="q2">My <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 38:15</char></note>hope <char style="it">is</char> in You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Deliver me from all my transgressions;</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not make me <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 44:13; 79:4; 119:22</char></note>the reproach of the foolish.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 39:2</char></note>I was mute, I did not open my mouth,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because it was <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 16:10; Job 2:10</char></note>You who did <char style="it">it.</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 9:34; 13:21</char></note>Remove Your plague from me;</para>
	<para style="q2">I am consumed by the blow of Your hand.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />When with rebukes You correct man for iniquity,</para>
	<para style="q2">You make his beauty <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 13:28; (Ps. 90:7); Is. 50:9</char></note>melt away like a moth;</para>
	<para style="q2">Surely every man <char style="it">is</char> vapor.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />“Hear my prayer, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And give ear to my cry;</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not be silent at my tears;</para>
	<para style="q2">For I <char style="it">am</char> a stranger with You,</para>
	<para style="q2">A sojourner, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 47:9; Lev. 25:23; 1 Chr. 29:15; Ps. 119:19; Heb. 11:13; 1 Pet. 2:11</char></note>as all my fathers <char style="it">were.</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 7:19; 10:20, 21; 14:6; Ps. 102:24</char></note>Remove Your gaze from me, that I may regain strength,</para>
	<para style="q2">Before I go away and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Job 14:10)</char></note>am no more.”</para>
	<chapter number="40" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Faith Persevering in Trial</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />I <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 25:5; 27:14; 37:7</char></note>waited patiently for the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">And He inclined to me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And heard my cry.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />He also brought me up out of a horrible pit,</para>
	<para style="q2">Out of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 69:2, 14; Jer. 38:6</char></note>the miry clay,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 27:5</char></note>set my feet upon a rock,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> established my steps.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 32:7; 33:3</char></note>He has put a new song in my mouth—</para>
	<para style="q2">Praise to our God;</para>
	<para style="q2">Many will see <char style="it">it</char> and fear,</para>
	<para style="q2">And will trust in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 34:8; 84:12</char></note>Blessed <char style="it">is</char> that man who makes the <char style="sc">Lord</char> his trust,</para>
	<para style="q2">And does not respect the proud, nor such as turn aside to lies.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 9:10</char></note>Many, O <char style="sc">Lord</char> my God, <char style="it">are</char> Your wonderful works</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Which</char> You have done;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 139:17; (Is. 55:8)</char></note>And Your thoughts toward us</para>
	<para style="q2">Cannot be recounted to You in order;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">If</char> I would declare and speak <char style="it">of</char> <char style="it">them,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">They are more than can be numbered.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Sam. 15:22); Ps. 51:16; Is. 1:11; (Jer. 6:20; 7:22, 23); Amos 5:22; (Mic. 6:6–8; Heb. 10:5–9)</char></note>Sacrifice and offering You did not desire;</para>
	<para style="q2">My ears You have opened.</para>
	<para style="q2">Burnt offering and sin offering You did not require.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Then I said, “Behold, I come;</para>
	<para style="q2">In the scroll of the book <char style="it">it</char> <char style="it">is</char> written of me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Matt. 26:39; John 4:34; 6:38); Heb. 10:7</char></note>I delight to do Your will, O my God,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Your law <char style="it">is</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 37:31; Jer. 31:33; 2 Cor. 3:3)</char></note>within my heart.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 22:22, 25</char></note>I have proclaimed the good news of righteousness</para>
	<para style="q2">In the great assembly;</para>
	<para style="q2">Indeed, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:13</char></note>I do not restrain my lips,</para>
	<para style="q2">O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, You Yourself know.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Acts 20:20, 27</char></note>I have not hidden Your righteousness within my heart;</para>
	<para style="q2">I have declared Your faithfulness and Your salvation;</para>
	<para style="q2">I have not concealed Your lovingkindness and Your truth</para>
	<para style="q2">From the great assembly.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" />Do not withhold Your tender mercies from me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 61:7; Prov. 20:28</char></note>Let Your lovingkindness and Your truth continually preserve me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />For innumerable evils have surrounded me;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 38:4; 65:3</char></note>My iniquities have overtaken me, so that I am not able to look up;</para>
	<para style="q2">They are more than the hairs of my head;</para>
	<para style="q2">Therefore my heart fails me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 70:1</char></note>Be pleased, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, to deliver me;</para>
	<para style="q2">O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, make haste to help me!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:4, 26; 70:2; 71:13</char></note>Let them be ashamed and brought to mutual confusion</para>
	<para style="q2">Who seek to destroy my life;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let them be driven backward and brought to dishonor</para>
	<para style="q2">Who wish me evil.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />Let them be <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 73:19</char></note>confounded because of their shame,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who say to me, “Aha, aha!”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 70:4</char></note>Let all those who seek You rejoice and be glad in You;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let such as love Your salvation <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:27</char></note>say continually,</para>
	<para style="q2">“The <char style="sc">Lord</char> be magnified!”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 70:5; 86:1; 109:22</char></note>But I <char style="it">am</char> poor and needy;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 40:5; 1 Pet. 5:7</char></note><char style="it">Yet</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char> thinks upon me.</para>
	<para style="q2">You <char style="it">are</char> my help and my deliverer;</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not delay, O my God.</para>
	<chapter number="41" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Blessing and Suffering of the Godly</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Blessed <char style="it">is</char> he who considers the poor;</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> will deliver him in time of trouble.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> will preserve him and keep him alive,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> he will be blessed on the earth;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 27:12</char></note>You will not deliver him to the will of his enemies.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> will strengthen him on his bed of illness;</para>
	<para style="q2">You will sustain him on his sickbed.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />I said, “<char style="sc">Lord</char>, be merciful to me;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 6:2; 103:3; 147:3</char></note>Heal my soul, for I have sinned against You.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />My enemies speak evil of me:</para>
	<para style="q2">“When will he die, and his name perish?”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />And if he comes to see <char style="it">me,</char> he speaks lies;</para>
	<para style="q2">His heart gathers iniquity to itself;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">When</char> he goes out, he tells <char style="it">it.</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />All who hate me whisper together against me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Against me they devise my hurt.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />“An evil disease,” <char style="it">they</char> <char style="it">say,</char> “clings to him.</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">now</char> that he lies down, he will rise up no more.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 15:12; Job 19:13, 19</char></note>Even my own familiar friend in whom I trusted,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 55:12–14, 20; Jer. 20:10; Obad. 7; (Mic. 7:5); Matt. 26:14–16, 21–25, 47–50; John 13:18, 21–30; Acts 1:16, 17</char></note>Who ate my bread,</para>
	<para style="q2">Has lifted up <char style="it">his</char> heel against me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />But You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, be merciful to me, and raise me up,</para>
	<para style="q2">That I may repay them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />By this I know that You are well pleased with me,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because my enemy does not triumph over me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />As for me, You uphold me in my integrity,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Job 36:7; Ps. 21:6; 34:15)</char></note>set me before Your face forever.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 72:18, 19; 89:52; 106:48; 150:6</char></note>Blessed <char style="it">be</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char> God of Israel</para>
	<para style="q2">From everlasting to everlasting!</para>
	<para style="q2">Amen and Amen.</para>
	<chapter number="42" style="c" />
	<para style="s">BOOK TWO: Psalms 42—72</para>
	<para style="s">Yearning for God in the Midst of Distresses</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. A Contemplation of the sons of Korah.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />As the deer pants for the water brooks,</para>
	<para style="q2">So pants my soul for You, O God.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 63:1; 84:2; 143:6; (Jer. 10:10)</char></note>My soul thirsts for God, for the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rom. 9:26; 1 Thess. 1:9</char></note>living God.</para>
	<para style="q2">When shall I come and appear before God?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 80:5; 102:9</char></note>My tears have been my food day and night,</para>
	<para style="q2">While they continually say to me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 79:10; 115:2; Joel 2:17; Mic. 7:10</char></note>“Where <char style="it">is</char> your God?”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />When I remember these <char style="it">things,</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 1:15; Job 30:16</char></note>I pour out my soul within me.</para>
	<para style="q2">For I used to go with the multitude;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 55:14; 122:1; Is. 30:29</char></note>I went with them to the house of God,</para>
	<para style="q2">With the voice of joy and praise,</para>
	<para style="q2">With a multitude that kept a pilgrim feast.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 42:11; 43:5</char></note>Why are you cast down, O my soul?</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">why</char> are you disquieted within me?</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 71:14; Lam. 3:24</char></note>Hope in God, for I shall yet praise Him</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">For</char> the help of His countenance.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />O my God, my soul is cast down within me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Therefore I will remember You from the land of the Jordan,</para>
	<para style="q2">And from the heights of Hermon,</para>
	<para style="q2">From the Hill Mizar.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Deep calls unto deep at the noise of Your waterfalls;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 69:1, 2; 88:7; Jon. 2:3</char></note>All Your waves and billows have gone over me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> will <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 28:8</char></note>command His lovingkindness in the daytime,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 35:10; Ps. 149:5</char></note>in the night His song <char style="it">shall</char> <char style="it">be</char> with me—</para>
	<para style="q2">A prayer to the God of my life.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />I will say to God my Rock,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 38:6</char></note>“Why have You forgotten me?</para>
	<para style="q2">Why do I go mourning because of the oppression of the enemy?”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><char style="it">As</char> with a breaking of my bones,</para>
	<para style="q2">My enemies reproach me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 42:3; Joel 2:17; Mic. 7:10</char></note>While they say to me all day long,</para>
	<para style="q2">“Where <char style="it">is</char> your God?”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 43:5</char></note>Why are you cast down, O my soul?</para>
	<para style="q2">And why are you disquieted within me?</para>
	<para style="q2">Hope in God;</para>
	<para style="q2">For I shall yet praise Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">The help of my countenance and my God.</para>
	<chapter number="43" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Prayer to God in Time of Trouble</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Vindicate <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 26:1; 35:24)</char></note>me, O God,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 24:15; Ps. 35:1</char></note>plead my cause against an ungodly nation;</para>
	<para style="q2">Oh, deliver me from the deceitful and unjust man!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />For You <char style="it">are</char> the God of my strength;</para>
	<para style="q2">Why do You cast me off?</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 42:9</char></note>Why do I go mourning because of the oppression of the enemy?</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 40:11)</char></note>Oh, send out Your light and Your truth!</para>
	<para style="q2">Let them lead me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let them bring me to <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 3:4</char></note>Your holy hill</para>
	<para style="q2">And to Your tabernacle.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Then I will go to the altar of God,</para>
	<para style="q2">To God my exceeding joy;</para>
	<para style="q2">And on the harp I will praise You,</para>
	<para style="q2">O God, my God.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 42:5, 11</char></note>Why are you cast down, O my soul?</para>
	<para style="q2">And why are you disquieted within me?</para>
	<para style="q2">Hope in God;</para>
	<para style="q2">For I shall yet praise Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">The help of my countenance and my God.</para>
	<chapter number="44" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Redemption Remembered in Present Dishonor</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. A <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 42:title</char></note>Contemplation of the sons of Korah.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />We have heard with our ears, O God,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 12:26, 27; Deut. 6:20); Judg. 6:13; Ps. 78:3</char></note>Our fathers have told us,</para>
	<para style="q2">The deeds You did in their days,</para>
	<para style="q2">In days of old:</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 15:17; 2 Sam. 7:10; Jer. 24:6; Amos 9:15</char></note>You drove out the nations with Your hand,</para>
	<para style="q2">But them You planted;</para>
	<para style="q2">You afflicted the peoples, and cast them out.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 8:17, 18); Josh. 24:12</char></note>they did not gain possession of the land by their own sword,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor did their own arm save them;</para>
	<para style="q2">But it was Your right hand, Your arm, and the light of Your countenance,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 4:37; 7:7, 8)</char></note>Because You favored them.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 74:12)</char></note>You are my King, O God;</para>
	<para style="q2">Command victories for Jacob.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Through You <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 33:17; (Dan. 8:4)</char></note>we will push down our enemies;</para>
	<para style="q2">Through Your name we will trample those who rise up against us.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Sam. 17:47); Ps. 33:16; (Hos. 1:7)</char></note>I will not trust in my bow,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor shall my sword save me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />But You have saved us from our enemies,</para>
	<para style="q2">And have put to shame those who hated us.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 34:2; (Jer. 9:24)</char></note>In God we boast all day long,</para>
	<para style="q2">And praise Your name forever.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 60:1</char></note>You have cast <char style="it">us</char> off and put us to shame,</para>
	<para style="q2">And You do not go out with our armies.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />You make us <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 26:17; Josh. 7:8, 12; Ps. 89:43</char></note>turn back from the enemy,</para>
	<para style="q2">And those who hate us have taken spoil for themselves.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 44:22; Rom. 8:36</char></note>You have given us up like sheep <char style="it">intended</char> for food,</para>
	<para style="q2">And have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 26:33; Deut. 4:27; 28:64; Ps. 106:27; Ezek. 20:23</char></note>scattered us among the nations.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 52:3, 4; Jer. 15:13</char></note>You sell Your people for <char style="it">next</char> <char style="it">to</char> nothing,</para>
	<para style="q2">And are not enriched by selling them.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 79:4; 80:6; Jer. 24:9</char></note>You make us a reproach to our neighbors,</para>
	<para style="q2">A scorn and a derision to those all around us.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 28:37</char></note>You make us a byword among the nations,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 16:4</char></note>A shaking of the head among the peoples.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />My dishonor <char style="it">is</char> continually before me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the shame of my face has covered me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />Because of the voice of him who reproaches and reviles,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 8:2</char></note>Because of the enemy and the avenger.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Dan. 9:13</char></note>All this has come upon us;</para>
	<para style="q2">But we have not forgotten You,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor have we dealt falsely with Your covenant.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />Our heart has not turned back,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 23:11</char></note>Nor have our steps departed from Your way;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />But You have severely broken us in <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 34:13</char></note>the place of jackals,</para>
	<para style="q2">And covered us <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 23:4)</char></note>with the shadow of death.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="20" style="v" />If we had forgotten the name of our God,</para>
	<para style="q2">Or <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 6:14)</char></note>stretched out our hands to a foreign god,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 31:14; (Ps. 139:1, 2; Jer. 17:10)</char></note>Would not God search this out?</para>
	<para style="q2">For He knows the secrets of the heart.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rom. 8:36</char></note>Yet for Your sake we are killed all day long;</para>
	<para style="q2">We are accounted as sheep for the slaughter.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="23" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 7:6</char></note>Awake! Why do You sleep, O Lord?</para>
	<para style="q2">Arise! Do not cast <char style="it">us</char> off forever.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 13:24</char></note>Why do You hide Your face,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> forget our affliction and our oppression?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="25" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:25</char></note>our soul is bowed down to the dust;</para>
	<para style="q2">Our body clings to the ground.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="26" style="v" />Arise for our help,</para>
	<para style="q2">And redeem us for Your mercies’ sake.</para>
	<chapter number="45" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Glories of the Messiah and His Bride</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 69:title</char></note>Set to “The Lilies.” A Contemplation of the sons of Korah. A Song of Love.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />My heart is overflowing with a good theme;</para>
	<para style="q2">I recite my composition concerning the King;</para>
	<para style="q2">My tongue <char style="it">is</char> the pen of a ready writer.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" />You are fairer than the sons of men;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Luke 4:22</char></note>Grace is poured upon Your lips;</para>
	<para style="q2">Therefore God has blessed You forever.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Gird Your <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 49:2; Heb. 4:12); Rev. 1:16</char></note>sword upon <char style="it">Your</char> thigh, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 9:6)</char></note>O Mighty One,</para>
	<para style="q2">With Your <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jude 25</char></note>glory and Your majesty.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rev. 6:2</char></note>And in Your majesty ride prosperously because of truth, humility, <char style="it">and</char> righteousness;</para>
	<para style="q2">And Your right hand shall teach You awesome things.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Your arrows <char style="it">are</char> sharp in the heart of the King’s enemies;</para>
	<para style="q2">The peoples fall under You.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 93:2); Heb. 1:8, 9</char></note>Your throne, O God, <char style="it">is</char> forever and ever;</para>
	<para style="q2">A <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Num. 24:17)</char></note>scepter of righteousness <char style="it">is</char> the scepter of Your kingdom.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />You love righteousness and hate wickedness;</para>
	<para style="q2">Therefore God, Your God, has <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 2:2</char></note>anointed You</para>
	<para style="q2">With the oil of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 21:6; Heb. 1:8, 9</char></note>gladness more than Your companions.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />All Your garments <char style="it">are</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Song 1:12, 13</char></note>scented with myrrh and aloes <char style="it">and</char> cassia,</para>
	<para style="q2">Out of the ivory palaces, by which they have made You glad.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Song 6:8</char></note>Kings’ daughters <char style="it">are</char> among Your honorable women;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 2:19</char></note>At Your right hand stands the queen in gold from Ophir.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />Listen, O daughter,</para>
	<para style="q2">Consider and incline your ear;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 21:13; Ruth 1:16, 17</char></note>Forget your own people also, and your father’s house;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />So the King will greatly desire your beauty;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 95:6; (Is. 54:5)</char></note>Because He <char style="it">is</char> your Lord, worship Him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />And the daughter of Tyre <char style="it">will</char> <char style="it">come</char> with a gift;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 49:23</char></note>The rich among the people will seek your favor.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" />The royal daughter <char style="it">is</char> all glorious within <char style="it">the</char> <char style="it">palace;</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Her clothing <char style="it">is</char> woven with gold.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Song 1:4</char></note>She shall be brought to the King in robes of many colors;</para>
	<para style="q2">The virgins, her companions who follow her, shall be brought to You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />With gladness and rejoicing they shall be brought;</para>
	<para style="q2">They shall enter the King’s palace.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" />Instead of Your fathers shall be Your sons,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Pet. 2:9; Rev. 1:6; 20:6)</char></note>Whom You shall make princes in all the earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Mal. 1:11</char></note>I will make Your name to be remembered in all generations;</para>
	<para style="q2">Therefore the people shall praise You forever and ever.</para>
	<chapter number="46" style="c" />
	<para style="s">God the Refuge of His People and Conqueror of the Nations</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. <char style="it">A</char> <char style="it">Psalm</char> of the sons of Korah. A Song <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 15:20</char></note>for Alamoth.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />God <char style="it">is</char> our <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 62:7, 8</char></note>refuge and strength,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 4:7; Ps. 145:18)</char></note>A very present help in trouble.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Therefore we will not fear,</para>
	<para style="q2">Even though the earth be removed,</para>
	<para style="q2">And though the mountains be carried into the midst of the sea;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 93:3, 4)</char></note><char style="it">Though</char> its waters roar <char style="it">and</char> be troubled,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Though</char> the mountains shake with its swelling.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><char style="it">There</char> <char style="it">is</char> a <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ezek. 47:1–12)</char></note>river whose streams shall make glad the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 48:1, 8; Is. 60:14</char></note>city of God,</para>
	<para style="q2">The holy <char style="it">place</char> of the tabernacle of the Most High.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />God <char style="it">is</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 23:14; Is. 12:6); Ezek. 43:7; Hos. 11:9; (Joel 2:27; Zeph. 3:15; Zech. 2:5, 10, 11; 8:3)</char></note>in the midst of her, she shall not be moved;</para>
	<para style="q2">God shall help her, just at the break of dawn.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 2:1, 2</char></note>The nations raged, the kingdoms were moved;</para>
	<para style="q2">He uttered His voice, the earth melted.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />The <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 14:9; 2 Chr. 13:12</char></note><char style="sc">Lord</char> of hosts <char style="it">is</char> with us;</para>
	<para style="q2">The God of Jacob <char style="it">is</char> our refuge.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />Come, behold the works of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who has made desolations in the earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 2:4</char></note>He makes wars cease to the end of the earth;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 76:3</char></note>He breaks the bow and cuts the spear in two;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ezek. 39:9</char></note>He burns the chariot in the fire.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />Be still, and know that I <char style="it">am</char> God;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 2:11, 17)</char></note>I will be exalted among the nations,</para>
	<para style="q2">I will be exalted in the earth!</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> of hosts <char style="it">is</char> with us;</para>
	<para style="q2">The God of Jacob <char style="it">is</char> our refuge.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<chapter number="47" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Praise to God, the Ruler of the Earth</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of the sons of Korah.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Oh, clap your hands, all you peoples!</para>
	<para style="q2">Shout to God with the voice of triumph!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />For the <char style="sc">Lord</char> Most High <char style="it">is</char> awesome;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">He</char> <char style="it">is</char> a great <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 7:21; Neh. 1:5; Ps. 76:12</char></note>King over all the earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 18:47</char></note>He will subdue the peoples under us,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the nations under our feet.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />He will choose our <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Pet. 1:4)</char></note>inheritance for us,</para>
	<para style="q2">The excellence of Jacob whom He loves.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 68:24, 25</char></note>God has gone up with a shout,</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> with the sound of a trumpet.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Sing praises to God, sing praises!</para>
	<para style="q2">Sing praises to our King, sing praises!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Zech. 14:9</char></note>For God <char style="it">is</char> the King of all the earth;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Cor. 14:15</char></note>Sing praises with understanding.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 16:31</char></note>God reigns over the nations;</para>
	<para style="q2">God <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 97:2</char></note>sits on His <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 48:1</char></note>holy throne.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />The princes of the people have gathered together,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Rom. 4:11, 12)</char></note>The people of the God of Abraham.</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 89:18)</char></note>For the shields of the earth <char style="it">belong</char> to God;</para>
	<para style="q2">He is greatly exalted.</para>
	<chapter number="48" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Glory of God in Zion</para>
	<para style="d">A Song. A Psalm of the sons of Korah.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Great <char style="it">is</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, and greatly to be praised</para>
	<para style="q2">In the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 46:4; 87:3; Matt. 5:35</char></note>city of our God,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">In</char> His holy mountain.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 50:2</char></note>Beautiful in elevation,</para>
	<para style="q2">The joy of the whole earth,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Is</char> Mount Zion <char style="it">on</char> the sides of the north,</para>
	<para style="q2">The city of the great King.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />God <char style="it">is</char> in her palaces;</para>
	<para style="q2">He is known as her refuge.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />For behold, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 10:6, 14</char></note>the kings assembled,</para>
	<para style="q2">They passed by together.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />They saw <char style="it">it, and</char> so they marveled;</para>
	<para style="q2">They were troubled, they hastened away.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Fear <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 15:15</char></note>took hold of them there,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> pain, as of a woman in birth pangs,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><char style="it">As</char> <char style="it">when</char> You break the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 10:22; Ezek. 27:25</char></note>ships of Tarshish</para>
	<para style="q2">With an east wind.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />As we have heard,</para>
	<para style="q2">So we have seen</para>
	<para style="q2">In the city of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> of hosts,</para>
	<para style="q2">In the city of our God:</para>
	<para style="q2">God will <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 87:5; Is. 2:2); Mic. 4:1</char></note>establish it forever.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />We have thought, O God, on <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 26:3</char></note>Your lovingkindness,</para>
	<para style="q2">In the midst of Your temple.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />According to <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 28:58); Josh. 7:9; Mal. 1:11</char></note>Your name, O God,</para>
	<para style="q2">So <char style="it">is</char> Your praise to the ends of the earth;</para>
	<para style="q2">Your right hand is full of righteousness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />Let Mount Zion rejoice,</para>
	<para style="q2">Let the daughters of Judah be glad,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because of Your judgments.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />Walk about Zion,</para>
	<para style="q2">And go all around her.</para>
	<para style="q2">Count her towers;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />Mark well her bulwarks;</para>
	<para style="q2">Consider her palaces;</para>
	<para style="q2">That you may <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 78:5–7)</char></note>tell <char style="it">it</char> to the generation following.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />For this <char style="it">is</char> God,</para>
	<para style="q2">Our God forever and ever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 58:11</char></note>He will be our guide</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Even</char> to death.</para>
	<chapter number="49" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Confidence of the Foolish</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of the sons of Korah.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Hear this, all peoples;</para>
	<para style="q2">Give ear, all inhabitants of the world,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Both low and high,</para>
	<para style="q2">Rich and poor together.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />My mouth shall speak wisdom,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the meditation of my heart <char style="it">shall</char> <char style="it">give</char> understanding.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />I will incline my ear to a proverb;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will disclose my dark saying on the harp.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />Why should I fear in the days of evil,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">When</char> the iniquity at my heels surrounds me?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Those who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 31:24; Ps. 52:7; (Prov. 11:28; Mark 10:23, 24)</char></note>trust in their wealth</para>
	<para style="q2">And boast in the multitude of their riches,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />None <char style="it">of</char> <char style="it">them</char> can by any means redeem <char style="it">his</char> brother,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 36:18, 19</char></note>give to God a ransom for him—</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Matt. 16:26)</char></note>the redemption of their souls <char style="it">is</char> costly,</para>
	<para style="q2">And it shall cease forever—</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />That he should continue to live eternally,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 89:48</char></note>not see the Pit.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />For he sees wise men die;</para>
	<para style="q2">Likewise the fool and the senseless person perish,</para>
	<para style="q2">And leave their wealth to others.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />Their inner thought <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">that</char> their houses <char style="it">will</char> <char style="it">last</char> forever,</para>
	<para style="q2">Their dwelling places to all generations;</para>
	<para style="q2">They <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 4:17; Deut. 3:14</char></note>call <char style="it">their</char> lands after their own names.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />Nevertheless man, <char style="it">though</char> in honor, does not remain;</para>
	<para style="q2">He is like the beasts <char style="it">that</char> perish.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" />This is the way of those who <char style="it">are</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Luke 12:20)</char></note>foolish,</para>
	<para style="q2">And of their posterity who approve their sayings.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />Like sheep they are laid in the grave;</para>
	<para style="q2">Death shall feed on them;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 47:3; (Dan. 7:18; 1 Cor. 6:2; Rev. 2:26)</char></note>The upright shall have dominion over them in the morning;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 4:21</char></note>And their beauty shall be consumed in the grave, far from their dwelling.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />But God <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Hos. 13:4); Mark 16:6, 7; Acts 2:31, 32</char></note>will redeem my soul from the power of the grave,</para>
	<para style="q2">For He shall <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 73:24</char></note>receive me.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" />Do not be afraid when one becomes rich,</para>
	<para style="q2">When the glory of his house is increased;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />For when he dies he shall carry nothing away;</para>
	<para style="q2">His glory shall not descend after him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />Though while he lives <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 29:19; Luke 12:19</char></note>he blesses himself</para>
	<para style="q2">(For <char style="it">men</char> will praise you when you do well for yourself),</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />He shall go to the generation of his fathers;</para>
	<para style="q2">They shall never see <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 33:30</char></note>light.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />A man <char style="it">who</char> <char style="it">is</char> in honor, yet does not understand,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Eccl. 3:19</char></note>Is like the beasts <char style="it">that</char> perish.</para>
	<chapter number="50" style="c" />
	<para style="s">God the Righteous Judge</para>
	<para style="d">A Psalm of Asaph.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />The <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 9:6</char></note>Mighty One, God the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Has spoken and called the earth</para>
	<para style="q2">From the rising of the sun to its going down.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Out of Zion, the perfection of beauty,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 33:2; Ps. 80:1</char></note>God will shine forth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Our God shall come, and shall not keep silent;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 10:2; Num. 16:35; (Ps. 97:3)</char></note>A fire shall devour before Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">And it shall be very tempestuous all around Him.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 4:26; 31:28; 32:1; Is. 1:2</char></note>He shall call to the heavens from above,</para>
	<para style="q2">And to the earth, that He may judge His people:</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />“Gather <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 33:3</char></note>My saints together to Me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 24:7</char></note>Those who have made a covenant with Me by sacrifice.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Let the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 97:6)</char></note>heavens declare His righteousness,</para>
	<para style="q2">For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 75:7</char></note>God Himself <char style="it">is</char> Judge.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />“Hear, O My people, and I will speak,</para>
	<para style="q2">O Israel, and I will testify against you;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 20:2</char></note>I <char style="it">am</char> God, your God!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 7:22</char></note>I will not rebuke you <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 1:11; (Hos. 6:6)</char></note>for your sacrifices</para>
	<para style="q2">Or your burnt offerings,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Which</char> <char style="it">are</char> continually before Me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 69:31</char></note>I will not take a bull from your house,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Nor</char> goats out of your folds.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />For every beast of the forest <char style="it">is</char> Mine,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> the cattle on a thousand hills.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />I know all the birds of the mountains,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the wild beasts of the field <char style="it">are</char> Mine.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />“If I were hungry, I would not tell you;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 19:5; (Deut. 10:14; Job 41:11); 1 Cor. 10:26</char></note>For the world <char style="it">is</char> Mine, and all its fullness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 51:15–17)</char></note>Will I eat the flesh of bulls,</para>
	<para style="q2">Or drink the blood of goats?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Hos. 14:2; Heb. 13:15</char></note>Offer to God thanksgiving,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 30:2; Deut. 23:21</char></note>pay your vows to the Most High.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 22:27; (Zech. 13:9)</char></note>Call upon Me in the day of trouble;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will deliver you, and you shall glorify Me.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" />But to the wicked God says:</para>
	<para style="q2">“What <char style="it">right</char> have you to declare My statutes,</para>
	<para style="q2">Or take My covenant in your mouth,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Neh. 9:26; Rom. 2:21</char></note>Seeing you hate instruction</para>
	<para style="q2">And cast My words behind you?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />When you saw a thief, you <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Rom. 1:32)</char></note>consented with him,</para>
	<para style="q2">And have been a <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Tim. 5:22</char></note>partaker with adulterers.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />You give your mouth to evil,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 52:2</char></note>your tongue frames deceit.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />You sit <char style="it">and</char> speak against your brother;</para>
	<para style="q2">You slander your own mother’s son.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />These <char style="it">things</char> you have done, and I kept silent;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Rom. 2:4)</char></note>You thought that I was altogether like you;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">But</char> I will rebuke you,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 90:8)</char></note>set <char style="it">them</char> in order before your eyes.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="22" style="v" />“Now consider this, you who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Job 8:13)</char></note>forget God,</para>
	<para style="q2">Lest I tear <char style="it">you</char> in pieces,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">be</char> none to deliver:</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" />Whoever offers praise glorifies Me;</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gal. 6:16</char></note>to him who orders <char style="it">his</char> conduct <char style="it">aright</char></para>
	<para style="q2">I will show the salvation of God.”</para>
	<chapter number="51" style="c" />
	<para style="s">A Prayer of Repentance</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of David <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 12:1</char></note>when Nathan the prophet went to him, after he had gone in to Bathsheba.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Have mercy upon me, O God,</para>
	<para style="q2">According to Your lovingkindness;</para>
	<para style="q2">According to the multitude of Your tender mercies,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 43:25; 44:22; Acts 3:19; Col. 2:14)</char></note>Blot out my transgressions.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 33:8; Ezek. 36:33; (Heb. 9:14; 1 John 1:7, 9)</char></note>Wash me thoroughly from my iniquity,</para>
	<para style="q2">And cleanse me from my sin.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />For I acknowledge my transgressions,</para>
	<para style="q2">And my sin <char style="it">is</char> always before me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 12:13</char></note>Against You, You only, have I sinned,</para>
	<para style="q2">And done <char style="it">this</char> evil <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Luke 5:21)</char></note>in Your sight—</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rom. 3:4</char></note>That You may be found just when You speak,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> blameless when You judge.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Job 14:4; Ps. 58:3; John 3:6; Rom. 5:12)</char></note>Behold, I was brought forth in iniquity,</para>
	<para style="q2">And in sin my mother conceived me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Behold, You desire truth in the inward parts,</para>
	<para style="q2">And in the hidden <char style="it">part</char> You will make me to know wisdom.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 12:22; Lev. 14:4; Num. 19:18; Heb. 9:19</char></note>Purge me with hyssop, and I shall be clean;</para>
	<para style="q2">Wash me, and I shall be <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 1:18)</char></note>whiter than snow.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Make me hear joy and gladness,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">That</char> the bones You have broken <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Matt. 5:4)</char></note>may rejoice.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />Hide Your face from my sins,</para>
	<para style="q2">And blot out all my iniquities.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ezek. 18:31; Eph. 2:10)</char></note>Create in me a clean heart, O God,</para>
	<para style="q2">And renew a steadfast spirit within me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />Do not cast me away from Your presence,</para>
	<para style="q2">And do not take Your <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Luke 11:13)</char></note>Holy Spirit from me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />Restore to me the joy of Your salvation,</para>
	<para style="q2">And uphold me <char style="it">by</char> <char style="it">Your</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(2 Cor. 3:17)</char></note>generous Spirit.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><char style="it">Then</char> I will teach transgressors Your ways,</para>
	<para style="q2">And sinners shall be converted to You.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" />Deliver me from the guilt of bloodshed, O God,</para>
	<para style="q2">The God of my salvation,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> my tongue shall sing aloud of Your righteousness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />O Lord, open my lips,</para>
	<para style="q2">And my mouth shall show forth Your praise.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Sam. 15:22); Ps. 50:8–14; (Mic. 6:6–8)</char></note>You do not desire sacrifice, or else I would give <char style="it">it;</char></para>
	<para style="q2">You do not delight in burnt offering.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 34:18; (Is. 57:15); 66:2</char></note>The sacrifices of God <char style="it">are</char> a broken spirit,</para>
	<para style="q2">A broken and a contrite heart—</para>
	<para style="q2">These, O God, You will not despise.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="18" style="v" />Do good in Your good pleasure to Zion;</para>
	<para style="q2">Build the walls of Jerusalem.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />Then You shall be pleased with <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 4:5</char></note>the sacrifices of righteousness,</para>
	<para style="q2">With burnt offering and whole burnt offering;</para>
	<para style="q2">Then they shall offer bulls on Your altar.</para>
	<chapter number="52" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The End of the Wicked and the Peace of the Godly</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. A Contemplation of David <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 22:9</char></note>when Doeg the Edomite went and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ezek. 22:9</char></note>told Saul, and said to him, “David has gone to the house of Ahimelech.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Why do you boast in evil, O mighty man?</para>
	<para style="q2">The goodness of God <char style="it">endures</char> continually.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Your tongue devises destruction,</para>
	<para style="q2">Like a sharp razor, working deceitfully.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />You love evil more than good,</para>
	<para style="q2">Lying rather than speaking righteousness.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />You love all devouring words,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">You</char> deceitful tongue.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />God shall likewise destroy you forever;</para>
	<para style="q2">He shall take you away, and pluck you out of <char style="it">your</char> dwelling place,</para>
	<para style="q2">And uproot you from the land of the living.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />The righteous also shall see and fear,</para>
	<para style="q2">And shall laugh at him, <char style="it">saying,</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />“Here is the man <char style="it">who</char> did not make God his strength,</para>
	<para style="q2">But trusted in the abundance of his riches,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> strengthened himself in his wickedness.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />But I <char style="it">am</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 11:16</char></note>like a green olive tree in the house of God;</para>
	<para style="q2">I trust in the mercy of God forever and ever.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />I will praise You forever,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because You have done <char style="it">it;</char></para>
	<para style="q2">And in the presence of Your saints</para>
	<para style="q2">I will wait on Your name, for <char style="it">it</char> is good.</para>
	<chapter number="53" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Folly of the Godless, and the Restoration of Israel</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. Set to “Mahalath.” A Contemplation of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />The <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 10:4</char></note>fool has said in his heart,</para>
	<para style="q2">“<char style="it">There</char> <char style="it">is</char> no God.”</para>
	<para style="q2">They are corrupt, and have done abominable iniquity;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rom. 3:10–12</char></note><char style="it">There</char> <char style="it">is</char> none who does good.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" />God looks down from heaven upon the children of men,</para>
	<para style="q2">To see if there are <char style="it">any</char> who understand, who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(2 Chr. 15:2)</char></note>seek God.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Every one of them has turned aside;</para>
	<para style="q2">They have together become corrupt;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">There</char> <char style="it">is</char> none who does good,</para>
	<para style="q2">No, not one.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />Have the workers of iniquity <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 4:22</char></note>no knowledge,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who eat up my people <char style="it">as</char> they eat bread,</para>
	<para style="q2">And do not call upon God?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 26:17, 36; Prov. 28:1</char></note>There they are in great fear</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Where</char> no fear was,</para>
	<para style="q2">For God has scattered the bones of him who encamps against you;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have put <char style="it">them</char> to shame,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because God has despised them.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 14:7</char></note>Oh, that the salvation of Israel would come out of Zion!</para>
	<para style="q2">When God brings back the captivity of His people,</para>
	<para style="q2">Let Jacob rejoice <char style="it">and</char> Israel be glad.</para>
	<chapter number="54" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Answered Prayer for Deliverance from Adversaries</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. With stringed instruments. A Contemplation of David <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 23:19</char></note>when the Ziphites went and said to Saul, “Is David not hiding with us?”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Save me, O God, by Your name,</para>
	<para style="q2">And vindicate me by Your strength.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Hear my prayer, O God;</para>
	<para style="q2">Give ear to the words of my mouth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />For strangers have risen up against me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And oppressors have sought after my life;</para>
	<para style="q2">They have not set God before them.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />Behold, God <char style="it">is</char> my helper;</para>
	<para style="q2">The Lord <char style="it">is</char> with those who uphold my life.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />He will repay my enemies for their evil.</para>
	<para style="q2">Cut them off in Your truth.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />I will freely sacrifice to You;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will praise Your name, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, for <char style="it">it</char> <char style="it">is</char> good.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />For He has delivered me out of all trouble;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 59:10</char></note>And my eye has seen <char style="it">its</char> <char style="it">desire</char> upon my enemies.</para>
	<chapter number="55" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Trust in God Concerning the Treachery of Friends</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. With stringed instruments. A Contemplation of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Give ear to my prayer, O God,</para>
	<para style="q2">And do not hide Yourself from my supplication.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Attend to me, and hear me;</para>
	<para style="q2">I <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 38:14; 59:11; Ezek. 7:16</char></note>am restless in my complaint, and moan noisily,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Because of the voice of the enemy,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because of the oppression of the wicked;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 16:7, 8</char></note>For they bring down trouble upon me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And in wrath they hate me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 116:3</char></note>My heart is severely pained within me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the terrors of death have fallen upon me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Fearfulness and trembling have come upon me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And horror has overwhelmed me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />So I said, “Oh, that I had wings like a dove!</para>
	<para style="q2">I would fly away and be at rest.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Indeed, I would wander far off,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> remain in the wilderness.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />I would hasten my escape</para>
	<para style="q2">From the windy storm <char style="it">and</char> tempest.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />Destroy, O Lord, <char style="it">and</char> divide their tongues,</para>
	<para style="q2">For I have seen <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 6:7</char></note>violence and strife in the city.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />Day and night they go around it on its walls;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 10:7</char></note>Iniquity and trouble <char style="it">are</char> also in the midst of it.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />Destruction <char style="it">is</char> in its midst;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 10:7</char></note>Oppression and deceit do not depart from its streets.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 41:9</char></note>For <char style="it">it</char> <char style="it">is</char> not an enemy <char style="it">who</char> reproaches me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Then I could bear <char style="it">it.</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Nor <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">it</char> one <char style="it">who</char> hates me who has <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:26; 38:16</char></note>exalted <char style="it">himself</char> against me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Then I could hide from him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />But <char style="it">it</char> <char style="it">was</char> you, a man my equal,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 15:12</char></note>My companion and my acquaintance.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />We took sweet counsel together,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 42:4</char></note>walked to the house of God in the throng.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" />Let death seize them;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let them <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 16:30, 33</char></note>go down alive into hell,</para>
	<para style="q2">For wickedness <char style="it">is</char> in their dwellings <char style="it">and</char> among them.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" />As for me, I will call upon God,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the <char style="sc">Lord</char> shall save me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Dan. 6:10; Luke 18:1; Acts 3:1; 10:3, 30</char></note>Evening and morning and at noon</para>
	<para style="q2">I will pray, and cry aloud,</para>
	<para style="q2">And He shall hear my voice.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />He has redeemed my soul in peace from the battle <char style="it">that</char> <char style="it">was</char> against me,</para>
	<para style="q2">For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Chr. 32:7, 8</char></note>there were many against me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />God will hear, and afflict them,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 33:27)</char></note>Even He who abides from of old.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Because they do not change,</para>
	<para style="q2">Therefore they do not fear God.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="20" style="v" />He has <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Acts 12:1</char></note>put forth his hands against those who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 7:4</char></note>were at peace with him;</para>
	<para style="q2">He has broken his covenant.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 28:3; 57:4; (Prov. 5:3, 4; 12:18)</char></note><char style="it">The</char> <char style="it">words</char> of his mouth were smoother than butter,</para>
	<para style="q2">But war <char style="it">was</char> in his heart;</para>
	<para style="q2">His words were softer than oil,</para>
	<para style="q2">Yet they <char style="it">were</char> drawn swords.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="22" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 37:5; Matt. 6:25–34; Luke 12:22–31; 1 Pet. 5:7)</char></note>Cast your burden on the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:24</char></note>He shall sustain you;</para>
	<para style="q2">He shall never permit the righteous to be moved.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="23" style="v" />But You, O God, shall bring them down to the pit of destruction;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 5:6</char></note>Bloodthirsty and deceitful men <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:27</char></note>shall not live out half their days;</para>
	<para style="q2">But I will trust in You.</para>
	<chapter number="56" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Prayer for Relief from Tormentors</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. Set to “The Silent Dove in Distant Lands.” A Michtam of David when the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 21:11</char></note>Philistines captured him in Gath.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Be <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 57:1</char></note>merciful to me, O God, for man would swallow me up;</para>
	<para style="q2">Fighting all day he oppresses me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />My enemies would <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 57:3</char></note>hound <char style="it">me</char> all day,</para>
	<para style="q2">For <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">are</char> many who fight against me, O Most High.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />Whenever I am afraid,</para>
	<para style="q2">I will trust in You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />In God (I will praise His word),</para>
	<para style="q2">In God I have put my trust;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 118:6; Is. 31:3; (Heb. 13:6)</char></note>I will not fear.</para>
	<para style="q2">What can flesh do to me?</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />All day they twist my words;</para>
	<para style="q2">All their thoughts <char style="it">are</char> against me for evil.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />They gather together,</para>
	<para style="q2">They hide, they mark my steps,</para>
	<para style="q2">When they lie in wait for my life.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Shall they escape by iniquity?</para>
	<para style="q2">In anger cast down the peoples, O God!</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />You number my wanderings;</para>
	<para style="q2">Put my tears into Your bottle;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Mal. 3:16)</char></note><char style="it">Are</char> <char style="it">they</char> not in Your book?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />When I cry out <char style="it">to</char> <char style="it">You,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Then my enemies will turn back;</para>
	<para style="q2">This I know, because <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 118:6; Rom. 8:31)</char></note>God <char style="it">is</char> for me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />In God (I will praise <char style="it">His</char> word),</para>
	<para style="q2">In the <char style="sc">Lord</char> (I will praise <char style="it">His</char> word),</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />In God I have put my trust;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will not be afraid.</para>
	<para style="q2">What can man do to me?</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />Vows <char style="it">made</char> to You <char style="it">are</char> <char style="it">binding</char> upon me, O God;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will render praises to You,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 116:8, 9</char></note>For You have delivered my soul from death.</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Have</char> <char style="it">You</char> not <char style="it">kept</char> my feet from falling,</para>
	<para style="q2">That I may walk before God</para>
	<para style="q2">In the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 33:30</char></note>light of the living?</para>
	<chapter number="57" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Prayer for Safety from Enemies</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. Set to “Do Not Destroy.” A Michtam of David <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 22:1</char></note>when he fled from Saul into the cave.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Be merciful to me, O God, be merciful to me!</para>
	<para style="q2">For my soul trusts in You;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ruth 2:12; Ps. 17:8; 63:7</char></note>And in the shadow of Your wings I will make my refuge,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 26:20</char></note>Until <char style="it">these</char> calamities have passed by.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" />I will cry out to God Most High,</para>
	<para style="q2">To God <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 138:8)</char></note>who performs <char style="it">all</char> <char style="it">things</char> for me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 144:5, 7</char></note>He shall send from heaven and save me;</para>
	<para style="q2">He reproaches the one who would swallow me up.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q2">God <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 43:3</char></note>shall send forth His mercy and His truth.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />My soul <char style="it">is</char> among lions;</para>
	<para style="q2">I lie <char style="it">among</char> the sons of men</para>
	<para style="q2">Who are set on fire,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 30:14</char></note>Whose teeth <char style="it">are</char> spears and arrows,</para>
	<para style="q2">And their tongue a sharp sword.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 108:5</char></note>Be exalted, O God, above the heavens;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Let</char> Your glory <char style="it">be</char> above all the earth.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 9:15</char></note>They have prepared a net for my steps;</para>
	<para style="q2">My soul is bowed down;</para>
	<para style="q2">They have dug a pit before me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Into the midst of it they <char style="it">themselves</char> have fallen.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 108:1–5</char></note>My heart is steadfast, O God, my heart is steadfast;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will sing and give praise.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Awake, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 16:9</char></note>my glory!</para>
	<para style="q2">Awake, lute and harp!</para>
	<para style="q2">I will awaken the dawn.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 108:3</char></note>I will praise You, O Lord, among the peoples;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will sing to You among the nations.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 103:11</char></note>For Your mercy reaches unto the heavens,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Your truth unto the clouds.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 57:5</char></note>Be exalted, O God, above the heavens;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Let</char> Your glory <char style="it">be</char> above all the earth.</para>
	<chapter number="58" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Just Judgment of the Wicked</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. Set to “Do Not Destroy.” A Michtam of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Do you indeed speak righteousness, you silent ones?</para>
	<para style="q2">Do you judge uprightly, you sons of men?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />No, in heart you work wickedness;</para>
	<para style="q2">You weigh out the violence of your hands in the earth.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 53:3; Is. 48:8)</char></note>The wicked are estranged from the womb;</para>
	<para style="q2">They go astray as soon as they are born, speaking lies.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Eccl. 10:11</char></note>Their poison <char style="it">is</char> like the poison of a serpent;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">They</char> <char style="it">are</char> like the deaf cobra <char style="it">that</char> stops its ear,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Which will not <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 8:17</char></note>heed the voice of charmers,</para>
	<para style="q2">Charming ever so skillfully.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 4:10</char></note>Break their teeth in their mouth, O God!</para>
	<para style="q2">Break out the fangs of the young lions, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Josh. 2:11; 7:5; Ps. 112:10; Is. 13:7; Ezek. 21:7</char></note>Let them flow away as waters <char style="it">which</char> run continually;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">When</char> he bends <char style="it">his</char> <char style="it">bow,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Let his arrows be as if cut in pieces.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><char style="it">Let</char> <char style="it">them</char> <char style="it">be</char> like a snail which melts away as it goes,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 3:16</char></note><char style="it">Like</char> a stillborn child of a woman, that they may not see the sun.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />Before your <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 118:12; Eccl. 7:6</char></note>pots can feel <char style="it">the</char> <char style="it">burning</char> thorns,</para>
	<para style="q2">He shall take them away <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 27:21; Prov. 10:25</char></note>as with a whirlwind,</para>
	<para style="q2">As in His living and burning wrath.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />The righteous shall rejoice when he sees the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 32:43); Jer. 11:20</char></note>vengeance;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 68:23</char></note>He shall wash his feet in the blood of the wicked,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 92:15; Prov. 11:18; (2 Cor. 5:10)</char></note>So that men will say,</para>
	<para style="q2">“Surely <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> a reward for the righteous;</para>
	<para style="q2">Surely He is God who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 50:6; 75:7</char></note>judges in the earth.”</para>
	<chapter number="59" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Assured Judgment of the Wicked</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. Set to “Do Not Destroy.” A Michtam of David <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 19:11</char></note>when Saul sent men, and they watched the house in order to kill him.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Deliver me from my enemies, O my God;</para>
	<para style="q2">Defend me from those who rise up against me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Deliver me from the workers of iniquity,</para>
	<para style="q2">And save me from bloodthirsty men.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />For look, they lie in wait for my life;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 56:6</char></note>The mighty gather against me,</para>
	<para style="q2">Not <char style="it">for</char> my transgression nor <char style="it">for</char> my sin, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />They run and prepare themselves through no fault <char style="it">of</char> <char style="it">mine.</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:23</char></note>Awake to help me, and behold!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />You therefore, O <char style="sc">Lord</char> God of hosts, the God of Israel,</para>
	<para style="q2">Awake to punish all the nations;</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not be merciful to any wicked transgressors.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 59:14</char></note>At evening they return,</para>
	<para style="q2">They growl like a dog,</para>
	<para style="q2">And go all around the city.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Indeed, they belch with their mouth;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 57:4; Prov. 12:18</char></note>Swords <char style="it">are</char> in their lips;</para>
	<para style="q2">For <char style="it">they</char> <char style="it">say,</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 22:13; Ps. 10:11</char></note>“Who hears?”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 1:26</char></note>You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, shall laugh at them;</para>
	<para style="q2">You shall have all the nations in derision.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />I will wait for You, O You his Strength;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 62:2)</char></note>For God <char style="it">is</char> my defense.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />My God of mercy shall <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 21:3</char></note>come to meet me;</para>
	<para style="q2">God shall let <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 54:7</char></note>me see <char style="it">my</char> <char style="it">desire</char> on my enemies.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" />Do not slay them, lest my people forget;</para>
	<para style="q2">Scatter them by Your power,</para>
	<para style="q2">And bring them down,</para>
	<para style="q2">O Lord our shield.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 12:13</char></note><char style="it">For</char> the sin of their mouth <char style="it">and</char> the words of their lips,</para>
	<para style="q2">Let them even be taken in their pride,</para>
	<para style="q2">And for the cursing and lying <char style="it">which</char> they speak.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 104:35</char></note>Consume <char style="it">them</char> in wrath, consume <char style="it">them,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">That they <char style="it">may</char> not <char style="it">be;</char></para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 83:18</char></note>let them know that God rules in Jacob</para>
	<para style="q2">To the ends of the earth.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" />And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 59:6</char></note>at evening they return,</para>
	<para style="q2">They growl like a dog,</para>
	<para style="q2">And go all around the city.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />They <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 15:23</char></note>wander up and down for food,</para>
	<para style="q2">And howl if they are not satisfied.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" />But I will sing of Your power;</para>
	<para style="q2">Yes, I will sing aloud of Your mercy in the morning;</para>
	<para style="q2">For You have been my defense</para>
	<para style="q2">And refuge in the day of my trouble.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />To You, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 18:1</char></note>O my Strength, I will sing praises;</para>
	<para style="q2">For God <char style="it">is</char> my defense,</para>
	<para style="q2">My God of mercy.</para>
	<chapter number="60" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Urgent Prayer for the Restored Favor of God</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 80</char></note>Set to “Lily of the Testimony.” A Michtam of David. For teaching. <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 8:3, 13; 1 Chr. 18:3</char></note>When he fought against Mesopotamia and Syria of Zobah, and Joab returned and killed twelve thousand Edomites in the Valley of Salt.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />O God, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 44:9</char></note>You have cast us off;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have broken us down;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have been displeased;</para>
	<para style="q2">Oh, restore us again!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />You have made the earth tremble;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have broken it;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(2 Chr. 7:14); Is. 30:26</char></note>Heal its breaches, for it is shaking.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 71:20</char></note>You have shown Your people hard things;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 51:17, 22; Jer. 25:15</char></note>You have made us drink the wine of confusion.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 20:5; Is. 5:26; 11:12; 13:2</char></note>You have given a banner to those who fear You,</para>
	<para style="q2">That it may be displayed because of the truth.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 108:6–13</char></note>That Your beloved may be delivered,</para>
	<para style="q2">Save <char style="it">with</char> Your right hand, and hear me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />God has <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 89:35</char></note>spoken in His holiness:</para>
	<para style="q2">“I will rejoice;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Josh. 1:6</char></note>divide <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 12:6</char></note>Shechem</para>
	<para style="q2">And measure out <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Josh. 13:27</char></note>the Valley of Succoth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Gilead <char style="it">is</char> Mine, and Manasseh <char style="it">is</char> Mine;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 33:17</char></note>Ephraim also <char style="it">is</char> the helmet for My head;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Gen. 49:10)</char></note>Judah <char style="it">is</char> My lawgiver.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 8:2</char></note>Moab <char style="it">is</char> My washpot;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 8:14; Ps. 108:9</char></note>Over Edom I will cast My shoe;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 8:1</char></note>Philistia, shout in triumph because of Me.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />Who will bring me <char style="it">to</char> the strong city?</para>
	<para style="q2">Who will lead me to Edom?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><char style="it">Is</char> <char style="it">it</char> not You, O God, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 108:11</char></note><char style="it">who</char> cast us off?</para>
	<para style="q2">And You, O God, <char style="it">who</char> did <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Josh. 7:12</char></note>not go out with our armies?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />Give us help from trouble,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 118:8; 146:3</char></note>For the help of man <char style="it">is</char> useless.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />Through God <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 24:18</char></note>we will do valiantly,</para>
	<para style="q2">For <char style="it">it</char> <char style="it">is</char> He <char style="it">who</char> shall tread down our enemies.</para>
	<chapter number="61" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Assurance of God’s Eternal Protection</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. On a stringed instrument. <char style="it">A</char> <char style="it">Psalm</char> of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Hear my cry, O God;</para>
	<para style="q2">Attend to my prayer.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />From the end of the earth I will cry to You,</para>
	<para style="q2">When my heart is overwhelmed;</para>
	<para style="q2">Lead me to the rock that is higher than I.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />For You have been a shelter for me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 18:10</char></note>A strong tower from the enemy.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />I will abide in Your tabernacle forever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 91:4</char></note>I will trust in the shelter of Your wings.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />For You, O God, have heard my vows;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have given <char style="it">me</char> the heritage of those who fear Your name.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />You will prolong the king’s life,</para>
	<para style="q2">His years as many generations.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />He shall abide before God forever.</para>
	<para style="q2">Oh, prepare mercy <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 40:11</char></note>and truth, <char style="it">which</char> may preserve him!</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />So I will sing praise to Your name forever,</para>
	<para style="q2">That I may daily perform my vows.</para>
	<chapter number="62" style="c" />
	<para style="s">A Calm Resolve to Wait for the Salvation of God</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. To <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 25:1</char></note>Jeduthun. A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Truly <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 33:20</char></note>my soul silently <char style="it">waits</char> for God;</para>
	<para style="q2">From Him <char style="it">comes</char> my salvation.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />He only <char style="it">is</char> my rock and my salvation;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">He</char> <char style="it">is</char> my defense;</para>
	<para style="q2">I shall not be greatly <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 55:22</char></note>moved.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />How long will you attack a man?</para>
	<para style="q2">You shall be slain, all of you,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 30:13</char></note>Like a leaning wall and a tottering fence.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />They only consult to cast <char style="it">him</char> down from his high position;</para>
	<para style="q2">They <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 28:3</char></note>delight in lies;</para>
	<para style="q2">They bless with their mouth,</para>
	<para style="q2">But they curse inwardly.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />My soul, wait silently for God alone,</para>
	<para style="q2">For my expectation <char style="it">is</char> from Him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />He only <char style="it">is</char> my rock and my salvation;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">He</char> <char style="it">is</char> my defense;</para>
	<para style="q2">I shall not be moved.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Jer. 3:23)</char></note>In God <char style="it">is</char> my salvation and my glory;</para>
	<para style="q2">The rock of my strength,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> my refuge, <char style="it">is</char> in God.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />Trust in Him at all times, you people;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 1:15; Ps. 42:4; Lam. 2:19</char></note>Pour out your heart before Him;</para>
	<para style="q2">God <char style="it">is</char> a refuge for us.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 7:16; Ps. 39:5; Is. 40:17</char></note>Surely men of low degree <char style="it">are</char> a vapor,</para>
	<para style="q2">Men of high degree <char style="it">are</char> a lie;</para>
	<para style="q2">If they are weighed on the scales,</para>
	<para style="q2">They <char style="it">are</char> altogether <char style="it">lighter</char> than vapor.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />Do not trust in oppression,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor vainly hope in robbery;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 31:25; (Mark 10:24; Luke 12:15; 1 Tim. 6:10)</char></note>If riches increase,</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not set <char style="it">your</char> heart <char style="it">on</char> <char style="it">them.</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" />God has spoken once,</para>
	<para style="q2">Twice I have heard this:</para>
	<para style="q2">That power <char style="it">belongs</char> to God.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />Also to You, O Lord, <char style="it">belongs</char> mercy;</para>
	<para style="q2">For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Matt. 16:27); Rom. 2:6; 1 Cor. 3:8</char></note>You render to each one according to his work.</para>
	<chapter number="63" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Joy in the Fellowship of God</para>
	<para style="d">A Psalm of David <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 22:5</char></note>when he was in the wilderness of Judah.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />O God, You <char style="it">are</char> my God;</para>
	<para style="q2">Early will I seek You;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 42:2; (Matt. 5:6)</char></note>My soul thirsts for You;</para>
	<para style="q2">My flesh longs for You</para>
	<para style="q2">In a dry and thirsty land</para>
	<para style="q2">Where there is no water.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />So I have looked for You in the sanctuary,</para>
	<para style="q2">To see <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 27:4</char></note>Your power and Your glory.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 138:2</char></note>Because Your lovingkindness <char style="it">is</char> better than life,</para>
	<para style="q2">My lips shall praise You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Thus I will bless You while I live;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 28:2; 143:6</char></note>lift up my hands in Your name.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />My soul shall be satisfied as with marrow and fatness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And my mouth shall praise <char style="it">You</char> with joyful lips.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />When <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 42:8</char></note>I remember You on my bed,</para>
	<para style="q2">I meditate on You in the <char style="it">night</char> watches.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Because You have been my help,</para>
	<para style="q2">Therefore in the shadow of Your wings I will rejoice.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />My soul follows close behind You;</para>
	<para style="q2">Your right hand upholds me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />But those <char style="it">who</char> seek my life, to destroy <char style="it">it,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Shall go into the lower parts of the earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />They shall fall by the sword;</para>
	<para style="q2">They shall be a portion for jackals.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" />But the king shall rejoice in God;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 6:13; (Is. 45:23; 65:16)</char></note>Everyone who swears by Him shall glory;</para>
	<para style="q2">But the mouth of those who speak lies shall be stopped.</para>
	<chapter number="64" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Oppressed by the Wicked but Rejoicing in the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Hear my voice, O God, in my meditation;</para>
	<para style="q2">Preserve my life from fear of the enemy.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Hide me from the secret plots of the wicked,</para>
	<para style="q2">From the rebellion of the workers of iniquity,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Who sharpen their tongue like a sword,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 58:7</char></note>And bend <char style="it">their</char> <char style="it">bows</char> <char style="it">to</char> <char style="it">shoot</char> their arrows—bitter words,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />That they may shoot in secret at the blameless;</para>
	<para style="q2">Suddenly they shoot at him and do not fear.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />They encourage themselves <char style="it">in</char> an evil matter;</para>
	<para style="q2">They talk of laying snares secretly;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 10:11; 59:7</char></note>They say, “Who will see them?”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />They devise iniquities:</para>
	<para style="q2">“We have perfected a shrewd scheme.”</para>
	<para style="q2">Both the inward thought and the heart of man are deep.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />But God shall shoot at them <char style="it">with</char> an arrow;</para>
	<para style="q2">Suddenly they shall be wounded.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />So He will make them stumble over their own tongue;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 31:11</char></note>All who see them shall flee away.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />All men shall fear,</para>
	<para style="q2">And shall <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 50:28; 51:10</char></note>declare the work of God;</para>
	<para style="q2">For they shall wisely consider His doing.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 22:19; Ps. 32:11</char></note>The righteous shall be glad in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, and trust in Him.</para>
	<para style="q2">And all the upright in heart shall glory.</para>
	<chapter number="65" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Praise to God for His Salvation and Providence</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of David. A Song.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Praise is awaiting You, O God, in Zion;</para>
	<para style="q2">And to You the vow shall be performed.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />O You who hear prayer,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 66:23)</char></note>To You all flesh will come.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Iniquities prevail against me;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">As</char> <char style="it">for</char> our transgressions,</para>
	<para style="q2">You will <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 51:2; 79:9; Is. 6:7; (Heb. 9:14; 1 John 1:7, 9)</char></note>provide atonement for them.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 33:12</char></note>Blessed <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">the</char> <char style="it">man</char> You <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 4:3</char></note>choose,</para>
	<para style="q2">And cause to approach <char style="it">You,</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">That</char> he may dwell in Your courts.</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 36:8</char></note>We shall be satisfied with the goodness of Your house,</para>
	<para style="q2">Of Your holy temple.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><char style="it">By</char> awesome deeds in righteousness You will answer us,</para>
	<para style="q2">O God of our salvation,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">You</char> <char style="it">who</char> <char style="it">are</char> the confidence of all the ends of the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2">And of the far-off seas;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Who established the mountains by His strength,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 93:1</char></note><char style="it">Being</char> clothed with power;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 8:26</char></note>You who still the noise of the seas,</para>
	<para style="q2">The noise of their waves,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 17:12, 13</char></note>And the tumult of the peoples.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />They also who dwell in the farthest parts are afraid of Your signs;</para>
	<para style="q2">You make the outgoings of the morning and evening rejoice.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />You visit the earth and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 11:12); Jer. 5:24</char></note>water it,</para>
	<para style="q2">You greatly enrich it;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 46:4; 104:13; 147:8</char></note>The river of God is full of water;</para>
	<para style="q2">You provide their grain,</para>
	<para style="q2">For so You have prepared it.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />You water its ridges abundantly,</para>
	<para style="q2">You settle its furrows;</para>
	<para style="q2">You make it soft with showers,</para>
	<para style="q2">You bless its growth.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" />You crown the year with Your goodness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Your paths drip <char style="it">with</char> abundance.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />They drop <char style="it">on</char> the pastures of the wilderness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the little hills rejoice on every side.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />The pastures are clothed with flocks;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 44:23; 55:12</char></note>The valleys also are covered with grain;</para>
	<para style="q2">They shout for joy, they also sing.</para>
	<chapter number="66" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Praise to God for His Awesome Works</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. A Song. A Psalm.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Make <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 100:1</char></note>a joyful shout to God, all the earth!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Sing out the honor of His name;</para>
	<para style="q2">Make His praise glorious.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Say to God,</para>
	<para style="q2">“How <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 65:5</char></note>awesome are Your works!</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 18:44</char></note>Through the greatness of Your power</para>
	<para style="q2">Your enemies shall submit themselves to You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 117:1; Zech. 14:16</char></note>All the earth shall worship You</para>
	<para style="q2">And sing praises to You;</para>
	<para style="q2">They shall sing praises <char style="it">to</char> Your name.”</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />Come and see the works of God;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">He</char> <char style="it">is</char> awesome <char style="it">in</char> <char style="it">His</char> doing toward the sons of men.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 14:21</char></note>He turned the sea into dry <char style="it">land;</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Josh. 3:14–16</char></note>They went through the river on foot.</para>
	<para style="q2">There we will rejoice in Him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />He rules by His power forever;</para>
	<para style="q2">His eyes observe the nations;</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not let the rebellious exalt themselves.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />Oh, bless our God, you peoples!</para>
	<para style="q2">And make the voice of His praise to be heard,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />Who keeps our soul among the living,</para>
	<para style="q2">And does not allow our feet to be moved.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 23:10; Ps. 17:3</char></note>You, O God, have tested us;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 48:10; Zech. 13:9; Mal. 3:3; 1 Pet. 1:7)</char></note>You have refined us as silver is refined.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lam. 1:13; Ezek. 12:13</char></note>You brought us into the net;</para>
	<para style="q2">You laid affliction on our backs.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 51:23</char></note>You have caused men to ride over our heads;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 43:2</char></note>We went through fire and through water;</para>
	<para style="q2">But You brought us out to rich <char style="it">fulfillment.</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 100:4; 116:14, 17–19</char></note>I will go into Your house with burnt offerings;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Eccl. 5:4)</char></note>I will pay You my vows,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />Which my lips have uttered</para>
	<para style="q2">And my mouth has spoken when I was in trouble.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />I will offer You burnt sacrifices of fat animals,</para>
	<para style="q2">With the sweet aroma of rams;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will offer bulls with goats.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" />Come <char style="it">and</char> hear, all you who fear God,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I will declare what He has done for my soul.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />I cried to Him with my mouth,</para>
	<para style="q2">And He was extolled with my tongue.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 27:9; (Prov. 15:29; 28:9); Is. 1:15; (John 9:31; James 4:3)</char></note>If I regard iniquity in my heart,</para>
	<para style="q2">The Lord will not hear.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" /><char style="it">But</char> certainly God <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 116:1, 2</char></note>has heard <char style="it">me;</char></para>
	<para style="q2">He has attended to the voice of my prayer.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="20" style="v" />Blessed <char style="it">be</char> God,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who has not turned away my prayer,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor His mercy from me!</para>
	<chapter number="67" style="c" />
	<para style="s">An Invocation and a Doxology</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. On stringed instruments. A Psalm. A Song.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />God be merciful to us and bless us,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 6:25</char></note>cause His face to shine upon us,</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />That <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Acts 18:25</char></note>Your way may be known on earth,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 52:10; Titus 2:11</char></note>Your salvation among all nations.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />Let the peoples praise You, O God;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let all the peoples praise You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Oh, let the nations be glad and sing for joy!</para>
	<para style="q2">For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 96:10, 13; 98:9)</char></note>You shall judge the people righteously,</para>
	<para style="q2">And govern the nations on earth.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />Let the peoples praise You, O God;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let all the peoples praise You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 26:4; Ps. 85:12; (Ezek. 34:27); Zech. 8:12</char></note><char style="it">Then</char> the earth shall yield her increase;</para>
	<para style="q2">God, our own God, shall bless us.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />God shall bless us,</para>
	<para style="q2">And all the ends of the earth shall fear Him.</para>
	<chapter number="68" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Glory of God in His Goodness to Israel</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of David. A Song.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Let <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 10:35</char></note>God arise,</para>
	<para style="q2">Let His enemies be scattered;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let those also who hate Him flee before Him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 9:18); Hos. 13:3</char></note>As smoke is driven away,</para>
	<para style="q2">So drive <char style="it">them</char> away;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 97:5; Mic. 1:4</char></note>As wax melts before the fire,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">So</char> let the wicked perish at the presence of God.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 32:11</char></note>let the righteous be glad;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let them rejoice before God;</para>
	<para style="q2">Yes, let them rejoice exceedingly.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />Sing to God, sing praises to His name;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 33:26</char></note>Extol Him who rides on the clouds,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 6:3)</char></note>By His name Y<char style="sc">AH</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And rejoice before Him.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 10:14, 18; 146:9)</char></note>A father of the fatherless, a defender of widows,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Is</char> God in His holy habitation.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 107:4–7</char></note>God sets the solitary in families;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Acts 12:6–11</char></note>He brings out those who are bound into prosperity;</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 107:34</char></note>the rebellious dwell in a dry <char style="it">land.</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />O God, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 13:21; (Hab. 3:13)</char></note>when You went out before Your people,</para>
	<para style="q2">When You marched through the wilderness,</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />The earth shook;</para>
	<para style="q2">The heavens also dropped <char style="it">rain</char> at the presence of God;</para>
	<para style="q2">Sinai itself <char style="it">was</char> <char style="it">moved</char> at the presence of God, the God of Israel.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 26:4; Deut. 11:11; Job 5:10; Ezek. 34:26</char></note>You, O God, sent a plentiful rain,</para>
	<para style="q2">Whereby You confirmed Your inheritance,</para>
	<para style="q2">When it was weary.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />Your congregation dwelt in it;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 26:5; Ps. 74:19</char></note>You, O God, provided from Your goodness for the poor.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" />The Lord gave the word;</para>
	<para style="q2">Great <char style="it">was</char> the company of those who proclaimed <char style="it">it:</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />“Kings<note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 31:8; Josh. 10:16; Judg. 5:19</char></note> of armies flee, they flee,</para>
	<para style="q2">And she who remains at home divides the spoil.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 81:6</char></note>Though you lie down among the sheepfolds,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 105:37</char></note><char style="it">You</char> <char style="it">will</char> <char style="it">be</char> like the wings of a dove covered with silver,</para>
	<para style="q2">And her feathers with yellow gold.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Josh. 10:10</char></note>When the Almighty scattered kings in it,</para>
	<para style="q2">It was <char style="it">white</char> as snow in Zalmon.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" />A mountain of God <char style="it">is</char> the mountain of Bashan;</para>
	<para style="q2">A mountain <char style="it">of</char> <char style="it">many</char> peaks <char style="it">is</char> the mountain of Bashan.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />Why do you fume with envy, you mountains of <char style="it">many</char> peaks?</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 12:5); 1 Kin. 9:3</char></note><char style="it">This</char> <char style="it">is</char> the mountain <char style="it">which</char> God desires to dwell in;</para>
	<para style="q2">Yes, the <char style="sc">Lord</char> will dwell <char style="it">in</char> <char style="it">it</char> forever.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 33:2; Dan. 7:10</char></note>The chariots of God <char style="it">are</char> twenty thousand,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Even</char> thousands of thousands;</para>
	<para style="q2">The Lord is among them <char style="it">as</char> <char style="it">in</char> Sinai, in the Holy <char style="it">Place.</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Mark 16:19; Acts 1:9; Eph. 4:8; Phil. 2:9; Col. 3:1; Heb. 1:3</char></note>You have ascended on high,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Judg. 5:12</char></note>You have led captivity captive;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Acts 2:4, 33; 10:44–46; (1 Cor. 12:4–11; Eph. 4:7–12)</char></note>You have received gifts among men,</para>
	<para style="q2">Even <char style="it">from</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Tim. 1:13)</char></note>the rebellious,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 78:60</char></note>That the <char style="sc">Lord</char> God might dwell <char style="it">there.</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" />Blessed <char style="it">be</char> the Lord,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Who</char> daily loads us <char style="it">with</char> <char style="it">benefits,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">The God of our salvation!</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />Our God <char style="it">is</char> the God of salvation;</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 32:39)</char></note>to G<char style="sc">OD</char> the Lord <char style="it">belong</char> escapes from death.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="21" style="v" />But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Hab. 3:13</char></note>God will wound the head of His enemies,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 55:23</char></note>The hairy scalp of the one who still goes on in his trespasses.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" />The Lord said, “I will bring <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 21:33; Deut. 30:1–9; Amos 9:1–3</char></note>back from Bashan,</para>
	<para style="q2">I will bring <char style="it">them</char> back <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 14:22</char></note>from the depths of the sea,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 58:10</char></note>That your foot may crush <char style="it">them</char> in blood,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 21:19; Jer. 15:3</char></note>And the tongues of your dogs <char style="it">may</char> <char style="it">have</char> their portion from <char style="it">your</char> enemies.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="24" style="v" />They have seen Your procession, O God,</para>
	<para style="q2">The procession of my God, my King, into the sanctuary.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="25" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 13:8</char></note>The singers went before, the players on instruments <char style="it">followed</char> after;</para>
	<para style="q2">Among <char style="it">them</char> <char style="it">were</char> the maidens playing timbrels.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="26" style="v" />Bless God in the congregations,</para>
	<para style="q2">The Lord, from <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 33:28; Is. 48:1</char></note>the fountain of Israel.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="27" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Judg. 5:14; 1 Sam. 9:21</char></note>There <char style="it">is</char> little Benjamin, their leader,</para>
	<para style="q2">The princes of Judah <char style="it">and</char> their company,</para>
	<para style="q2">The princes of Zebulun <char style="it">and</char> the princes of Naphtali.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="28" style="v" />Your God has <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 42:8; Is. 26:12</char></note>commanded your strength;</para>
	<para style="q2">Strengthen, O God, what You have done for us.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="29" style="v" />Because of Your temple at Jerusalem,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 10:10, 25; 2 Chr. 32:23; Ps. 45:12; 72:10; Is. 18:7</char></note>Kings will bring presents to You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="30" style="v" />Rebuke the beasts of the reeds,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 22:12</char></note>The herd of bulls with the calves of the peoples,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Till</char> <char style="it">everyone</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 8:2</char></note>submits himself with pieces of silver.</para>
	<para style="q2">Scatter the peoples <char style="it">who</char> delight in war.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="31" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 19:19–23</char></note>Envoys will come out of Egypt;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 45:14; Zeph. 3:10</char></note>Ethiopia will quickly <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 44:20</char></note>stretch out her hands to God.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="32" style="v" />Sing to God, you <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 67:3, 4)</char></note>kingdoms of the earth;</para>
	<para style="q2">Oh, sing praises to the Lord,</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="33" style="v" />To Him <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 33:26; Ps. 18:10</char></note>who rides on the heaven of heavens, <char style="it">which</char> <char style="it">were</char> of old!</para>
	<para style="q2">Indeed, He sends out His voice, a <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 46:6; Is. 30:30</char></note>mighty voice.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="34" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 29:1</char></note>Ascribe strength to God;</para>
	<para style="q2">His excellence <char style="it">is</char> over Israel,</para>
	<para style="q2">And His strength <char style="it">is</char> in the clouds.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="35" style="v" />O God, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 76:12</char></note><char style="it">You</char> <char style="it">are</char> more awesome than Your holy places.</para>
	<para style="q2">The God of Israel <char style="it">is</char> He who gives strength and power to <char style="it">His</char> people.</para>
	<para style="q1">Blessed <char style="it">be</char> God!</para>
	<chapter number="69" style="c" />
	<para style="s">An Urgent Plea for Help in Trouble</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. Set to “The Lilies.” <char style="it">A</char> <char style="it">Psalm</char> of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Save me, O God!</para>
	<para style="q2">For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 22:11; Jon. 2:5</char></note>the waters have come up to <char style="it">my</char> neck.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 40:2</char></note>I sink in deep mire,</para>
	<para style="q2">Where <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> no standing;</para>
	<para style="q2">I have come into deep waters,</para>
	<para style="q2">Where the floods overflow me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 6:6</char></note>I am weary with my crying;</para>
	<para style="q2">My throat is dry;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 28:32; Ps. 119:82, 123; Is. 38:14</char></note>My eyes fail while I wait for my God.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />Those who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:19; John 15:25</char></note>hate me without a cause</para>
	<para style="q2">Are more than the hairs of my head;</para>
	<para style="q2">They are mighty who would destroy me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Being</char> my enemies wrongfully;</para>
	<para style="q2">Though I have stolen nothing,</para>
	<para style="q2">I <char style="it">still</char> must restore <char style="it">it.</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />O God, You know my foolishness;</para>
	<para style="q2">And my sins are not hidden from You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Let not those who wait for You, O Lord G<char style="sc">OD</char> of hosts, be ashamed because of me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let not those who seek You be confounded because of me, O God of Israel.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Because for Your sake I have borne reproach;</para>
	<para style="q2">Shame has covered my face.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 53:3; Mark 3:21; Luke 8:19; John 7:3–5</char></note>I have become a stranger to my brothers,</para>
	<para style="q2">And an alien to my mother’s children;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">John 2:17</char></note>Because zeal for Your house has eaten me up,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rom. 15:3</char></note>And the reproaches of those who reproach You have fallen on me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />When I wept <char style="it">and</char> <char style="it">chastened</char> my soul with fasting,</para>
	<para style="q2">That became my reproach.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />I also made sackcloth my garment;</para>
	<para style="q2">I became a byword to them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />Those who sit in the gate speak against me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I <char style="it">am</char> the song of the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 30:9</char></note>drunkards.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" />But as for me, my prayer <char style="it">is</char> to You,</para>
	<para style="q2">O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <char style="it">in</char> the acceptable time;</para>
	<para style="q2">O God, in the multitude of Your mercy,</para>
	<para style="q2">Hear me in the truth of Your salvation.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />Deliver me out of the mire,</para>
	<para style="q2">And let me not sink;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let me be delivered from those who hate me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And out of the deep waters.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />Let not the floodwater overflow me,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor let the deep swallow me up;</para>
	<para style="q2">And let not the pit shut its mouth on me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" />Hear me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, for Your lovingkindness <char style="it">is</char> good;</para>
	<para style="q2">Turn to me according to the multitude of Your tender mercies.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />And do not hide Your face from Your servant,</para>
	<para style="q2">For I am in trouble;</para>
	<para style="q2">Hear me speedily.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />Draw near to my soul, <char style="it">and</char> redeem it;</para>
	<para style="q2">Deliver me because of my enemies.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" />You know <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 22:6, 7; Heb. 12:2</char></note>my reproach, my shame, and my dishonor;</para>
	<para style="q2">My adversaries <char style="it">are</char> all before You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />Reproach has broken my heart,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I am full of heaviness;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 63:5</char></note>I looked <char style="it">for</char> <char style="it">someone</char> to take pity, but <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">was</char> none;</para>
	<para style="q2">And for <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 16:2</char></note>comforters, but I found none.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />They also gave me gall for my food,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 27:34, 48; Mark 15:23, 36; Luke 23:36; John 19:28–30</char></note>And for my thirst they gave me vinegar to drink.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="22" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rom. 11:9, 10</char></note>Let their table become a snare before them,</para>
	<para style="q2">And their well-being a trap.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 6:9, 10</char></note>Let their eyes be darkened, so that they do not see;</para>
	<para style="q2">And make their loins shake continually.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Jer. 10:25; 1 Thess. 2:16)</char></note>Pour out Your indignation upon them,</para>
	<para style="q2">And let Your wrathful anger take hold of them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="25" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 23:38; Luke 13:35; Acts 1:20</char></note>Let their dwelling place be desolate;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let no one live in their tents.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="26" style="v" />For they persecute the <char style="it">ones</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 53:4; 1 Pet. 2:24)</char></note>You have struck,</para>
	<para style="q2">And talk of the grief of those You have wounded.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="27" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Neh. 4:5; (Rom. 1:28)</char></note>Add iniquity to their iniquity,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 26:10)</char></note>And let them not come into Your righteousness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="28" style="v" />Let them <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 32:32); Phil. 4:3; (Rev. 3:5; 13:8)</char></note>be blotted out of the book of the living,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ezek. 13:9; Luke 10:20; Heb. 12:23</char></note>And not be written with the righteous.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="29" style="v" />But I <char style="it">am</char> poor and sorrowful;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let Your salvation, O God, set me up on high.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="30" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 28:7)</char></note>I will praise the name of God with a song,</para>
	<para style="q2">And will magnify Him with thanksgiving.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="31" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 50:13, 14, 23; 51:16</char></note><char style="it">This</char> also shall please the <char style="sc">Lord</char> better than an ox <char style="it">or</char> bull,</para>
	<para style="q2">Which has horns and hooves.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="32" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 34:2</char></note>The humble shall see <char style="it">this</char> <char style="it">and</char> be glad;</para>
	<para style="q2">And you who seek God, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 22:26</char></note>your hearts shall live.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="33" style="v" />For the <char style="sc">Lord</char> hears the poor,</para>
	<para style="q2">And does not despise <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 68:6); Eph. 3:1</char></note>His prisoners.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="34" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 96:11; Is. 44:23; 49:13</char></note>Let heaven and earth praise Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">The seas <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 55:12</char></note>and everything that moves in them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="35" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 51:18; Is. 44:26</char></note>For God will save Zion</para>
	<para style="q2">And build the cities of Judah,</para>
	<para style="q2">That they may dwell there and possess it.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="36" style="v" />Also, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 102:28</char></note>the descendants of His servants shall inherit it,</para>
	<para style="q2">And those who love His name shall dwell in it.</para>
	<chapter number="70" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Prayer for Relief from Adversaries</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. <char style="it">A</char> <char style="it">Psalm</char> of David. <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 38:title</char></note>To bring to remembrance.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" /><char style="it">Make</char> <char style="it">haste</char>, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 40:13–17</char></note>O God, to deliver me!</para>
	<para style="q2">Make haste to help me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:4, 26</char></note>Let them be ashamed and confounded</para>
	<para style="q2">Who seek my life;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let them be turned back and confused</para>
	<para style="q2">Who desire my hurt.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 40:15</char></note>Let them be turned back because of their shame,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who say, “Aha, aha!”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />Let all those who seek You rejoice and be glad in You;</para>
	<para style="q2">And let those who love Your salvation say continually,</para>
	<para style="q2">“Let God be magnified!”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 72:12, 13</char></note>But I <char style="it">am</char> poor and needy;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 141:1</char></note>Make haste to me, O God!</para>
	<para style="q2">You <char style="it">are</char> my help and my deliverer;</para>
	<para style="q2">O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, do not delay.</para>
	<chapter number="71" style="c" />
	<para style="s">God the Rock of Salvation</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />In <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 25:2, 3</char></note>You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, I put my trust;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let me never be put to shame.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 31:1</char></note>Deliver me in Your righteousness, and cause me to escape;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 17:6</char></note>Incline Your ear to me, and save me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 31:2, 3</char></note>Be my strong refuge,</para>
	<para style="q2">To which I may resort continually;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have given the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 44:4</char></note>commandment to save me,</para>
	<para style="q2">For You <char style="it">are</char> my rock and my fortress.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 140:1, 3</char></note>Deliver me, O my God, out of the hand of the wicked,</para>
	<para style="q2">Out of the hand of the unrighteous and cruel man.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />For You are <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 14:8; 17:7, 13, 17; 50:7</char></note>my hope, O Lord G<char style="sc">OD</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">You</char> <char style="it">are</char> my trust from my youth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 22:9, 10; Is. 46:3</char></note>By You I have been upheld from birth;</para>
	<para style="q2">You are He who took me out of my mother’s womb.</para>
	<para style="q2">My praise <char style="it">shall</char> <char style="it">be</char> continually of You.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 8:18; Zech. 3:8; 1 Cor. 4:9</char></note>I have become as a wonder to many,</para>
	<para style="q2">But You <char style="it">are</char> my strong refuge.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Let <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:28</char></note>my mouth be filled <char style="it">with</char> Your praise</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> <char style="it">with</char> Your glory all the day.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />Do not cast me off in the time of old age;</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not forsake me when my strength fails.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />For my enemies speak against me;</para>
	<para style="q2">And those who lie in wait for my life <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 17:1</char></note>take counsel together,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />Saying, “God has forsaken him;</para>
	<para style="q2">Pursue and take him, for <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> none to deliver <char style="it">him.”</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:22</char></note>O God, do not be far from me;</para>
	<para style="q2">O my God, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 70:1</char></note>make haste to help me!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />Let them be confounded <char style="it">and</char> consumed</para>
	<para style="q2">Who are adversaries of my life;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let them be covered <char style="it">with</char> reproach and dishonor</para>
	<para style="q2">Who seek my hurt.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" />But I will hope continually,</para>
	<para style="q2">And will praise You yet more and more.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />My mouth shall tell of Your righteousness</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> Your salvation all the day,</para>
	<para style="q2">For I do not know <char style="it">their</char> limits.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />I will go in the strength of the Lord G<char style="sc">OD</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will make mention of Your righteousness, of Yours only.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="17" style="v" />O God, You have taught me from my <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 4:5; 6:7</char></note>youth;</para>
	<para style="q2">And to this <char style="it">day</char> I declare Your wondrous works.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />Now also <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 46:4)</char></note>when <char style="it">I</char> <char style="it">am</char> old and grayheaded,</para>
	<para style="q2">O God, do not forsake me,</para>
	<para style="q2">Until I declare Your strength to <char style="it">this</char> generation,</para>
	<para style="q2">Your power to everyone <char style="it">who</char> is to come.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" />Also <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 3:24; Ps. 57:10</char></note>Your righteousness, O God, <char style="it">is</char> very high,</para>
	<para style="q2">You who have done great things;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:10</char></note>O God, who <char style="it">is</char> like You?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 60:3</char></note><char style="it">You,</char> who have shown me great and severe troubles,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Hos. 6:1, 2</char></note>Shall revive me again,</para>
	<para style="q2">And bring me up again from the depths of the earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />You shall increase my greatness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And comfort me on every side.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="22" style="v" />Also <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 92:1–3</char></note>with the lute I will praise You—</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> Your faithfulness, O my God!</para>
	<para style="q2">To You I will sing with the harp,</para>
	<para style="q2">O <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Kin. 19:22; Is. 1:4</char></note>Holy One of Israel.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" />My lips shall greatly rejoice when I sing to You,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 103:4</char></note>my soul, which You have redeemed.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" />My tongue also shall talk of Your righteousness all the day long;</para>
	<para style="q2">For they are confounded,</para>
	<para style="q2">For they are brought to shame</para>
	<para style="q2">Who seek my hurt.</para>
	<chapter number="72" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Glory and Universality of the Messiah’s Reign</para>
	<para style="d"><char style="it">A</char> <char style="it">Psalm</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 127:title</char></note>of Solomon.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Give the king Your judgments, O God,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Your righteousness to the king’s Son.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 9:7; 11:2–5; 32:1)</char></note>He will judge Your people with righteousness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Your poor with justice.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 85:10</char></note>The mountains will bring peace to the people,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the little hills, by righteousness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 11:4</char></note>He will bring justice to the poor of the people;</para>
	<para style="q2">He will save the children of the needy,</para>
	<para style="q2">And will break in pieces the oppressor.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />They shall fear You</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 72:7, 17; 89:36</char></note>As long as the sun and moon endure,</para>
	<para style="q2">Throughout all generations.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 32:2; 2 Sam. 23:4; Hos. 6:3</char></note>He shall come down like rain upon the grass before mowing,</para>
	<para style="q2">Like showers <char style="it">that</char> water the earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />In His days the righteous shall flourish,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 2:4</char></note>And abundance of peace,</para>
	<para style="q2">Until the moon is no more.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 23:31; (Is. 9:6; Zech. 9:10)</char></note>He shall have dominion also from sea to sea,</para>
	<para style="q2">And from the River to the ends of the earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 74:14; Is. 23:13</char></note>Those who dwell in the wilderness will bow before Him,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 49:23; Mic. 7:17</char></note>And His enemies will lick the dust.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 10:2; 2 Chr. 9:21</char></note>The kings of Tarshish and of the isles</para>
	<para style="q2">Will bring presents;</para>
	<para style="q2">The kings of Sheba and Seba</para>
	<para style="q2">Will offer gifts.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 49:23</char></note>Yes, all kings shall fall down before Him;</para>
	<para style="q2">All nations shall serve Him.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />For He <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 29:12</char></note>will deliver the needy when he cries,</para>
	<para style="q2">The poor also, and <char style="it">him</char> who has no helper.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />He will spare the poor and needy,</para>
	<para style="q2">And will save the souls of the needy.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />He will redeem their life from oppression and violence;</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 26:21; (Ps. 116:15)</char></note>precious shall be their blood in His sight.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" />And He shall live;</para>
	<para style="q2">And the gold of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 60:6</char></note>Sheba will be given to Him;</para>
	<para style="q2">Prayer also will be made for Him continually,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> daily He shall be praised.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" />There will be an abundance of grain in the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2">On the top of the mountains;</para>
	<para style="q2">Its fruit shall wave like Lebanon;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 4:20</char></note>And <char style="it">those</char> of the city shall flourish like grass of the earth.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 89:36)</char></note>His name shall endure forever;</para>
	<para style="q2">His name shall continue as long as the sun.</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Gen. 12:3)</char></note><char style="it">men</char> shall be blessed in Him;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Luke 1:48</char></note>All nations shall call Him blessed.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 29:10</char></note>Blessed <char style="it">be</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char> God, the God of Israel,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 15:11; Job 5:9</char></note>Who only does wondrous things!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Neh. 9:5)</char></note>blessed <char style="it">be</char> His glorious name forever!</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 14:21; Hab. 2:14</char></note>And let the whole earth be filled <char style="it">with</char> His glory.</para>
	<para style="q2">Amen and Amen.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="20" style="v" />The prayers of David the son of Jesse are ended.</para>
	<chapter number="73" style="c" />
	<para style="s">BOOK THREE: Psalms 73—89</para>
	<para style="s">The Tragedy of the Wicked, and the Blessedness of Trust in God</para>
	<para style="d">A Psalm of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 50:title</char></note>Asaph.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Truly God <char style="it">is</char> good to Israel,</para>
	<para style="q2">To such as are pure in heart.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />But as for me, my feet had almost stumbled;</para>
	<para style="q2">My steps had nearly <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 12:5</char></note>slipped.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:1, 7; (Prov. 23:17)</char></note>For I <char style="it">was</char> envious of the boastful,</para>
	<para style="q2">When I saw the prosperity of the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 21:5–16; Jer. 12:1</char></note>wicked.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />For <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">are</char> no pangs in their death,</para>
	<para style="q2">But their strength <char style="it">is</char> firm.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 21:9</char></note>They <char style="it">are</char> not in trouble <char style="it">as</char> <char style="it">other</char> men,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor are they plagued like <char style="it">other</char> men.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Therefore pride serves as their necklace;</para>
	<para style="q2">Violence covers them <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 109:18</char></note><char style="it">like</char> a garment.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 15:27; Jer. 5:28</char></note>Their eyes bulge with abundance;</para>
	<para style="q2">They have more than heart could wish.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 53:1</char></note>They scoff and speak wickedly <char style="it">concerning</char> oppression;</para>
	<para style="q2">They <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Pet. 2:18; Jude 16</char></note>speak loftily.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />They set their mouth <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rev. 13:6</char></note>against the heavens,</para>
	<para style="q2">And their tongue walks through the earth.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />Therefore his people return here,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 75:8)</char></note>And waters of a full <char style="it">cup</char> are drained by them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />And they say, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 22:13</char></note>“How does God know?</para>
	<para style="q2">And is there knowledge in the Most High?”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />Behold, these <char style="it">are</char> the ungodly,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who are always at ease;</para>
	<para style="q2">They increase <char style="it">in</char> riches.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />Surely I have cleansed my heart <char style="it">in</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 21:15; 35:3; Mal. 3:14</char></note>vain,</para>
	<para style="q2">And washed my hands in innocence.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />For all day long I have been plagued,</para>
	<para style="q2">And chastened every morning.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" />If I had said, “I will speak thus,”</para>
	<para style="q2">Behold, I would have been untrue to the generation of Your children.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />When I thought <char style="it">how</char> to understand this,</para>
	<para style="q2">It <char style="it">was</char> too painful for me—</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />Until I went into the sanctuary of God;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Then</char> I understood their <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 37:38; 55:23)</char></note>end.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="18" style="v" />Surely <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:6</char></note>You set them in slippery places;</para>
	<para style="q2">You cast them down to destruction.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />Oh, how they are <char style="it">brought</char> to desolation, as in a moment!</para>
	<para style="q2">They are utterly consumed with terrors.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />As a dream when <char style="it">one</char> awakes,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">So,</char> Lord, when You awake,</para>
	<para style="q2">You shall despise their image.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="21" style="v" />Thus my heart was grieved,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I was vexed in my mind.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 92:6</char></note>I <char style="it">was</char> so foolish and ignorant;</para>
	<para style="q2">I was <char style="it">like</char> a beast before You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" />Nevertheless I <char style="it">am</char> continually with You;</para>
	<para style="q2">You hold <char style="it">me</char> by my right hand.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 32:8; 48:14; Is. 58:11</char></note>You will guide me with Your counsel,</para>
	<para style="q2">And afterward receive me <char style="it">to</char> glory.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="25" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Phil. 3:8)</char></note>Whom have I in heaven <char style="it">but</char> <char style="it">You?</char></para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> none upon earth <char style="it">that</char> I desire besides You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="26" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 84:2</char></note>My flesh and my heart fail;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">But</char> God <char style="it">is</char> the strength of my heart and my <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 16:5</char></note>portion forever.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="27" style="v" />For indeed, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 119:155)</char></note>those who are far from You shall perish;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have destroyed all those who desert You for harlotry.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="28" style="v" />But <char style="it">it</char> <char style="it">is</char> good for me to <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Heb. 10:22; James 4:8)</char></note>draw near to God;</para>
	<para style="q2">I have put my trust in the Lord G<char style="sc">OD</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">That I may <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 116:10; 2 Cor. 4:13</char></note>declare all Your works.</para>
	<chapter number="74" style="c" />
	<para style="s">A Plea for Relief from Oppressors</para>
	<para style="d">A Contemplation of Asaph.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />O God, why have You cast <char style="it">us</char> off forever?</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Why</char> does Your anger smoke against the sheep of Your pasture?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Remember Your congregation, <char style="it">which</char> You have purchased of old,</para>
	<para style="q2">The tribe of Your inheritance, <char style="it">which</char> You have redeemed—</para>
	<para style="q2">This Mount Zion where You have dwelt.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Lift up Your feet to the perpetual desolations.</para>
	<para style="q2">The enemy has damaged everything in the sanctuary.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lam. 2:7</char></note>Your enemies roar in the midst of Your meeting place;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 2:2</char></note>They set up their banners <char style="it">for</char> signs.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />They seem like men who lift up</para>
	<para style="q2">Axes among the thick trees.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />And now they break down its carved work, all at once,</para>
	<para style="q2">With axes and hammers.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />They have set fire to Your sanctuary;</para>
	<para style="q2">They have defiled the dwelling place of Your name to the ground.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 83:4</char></note>They said in their hearts,</para>
	<para style="q2">“Let us destroy them altogether.”</para>
	<para style="q2">They have burned up all the meeting places of God in the land.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />We do not see our signs;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 3:1; Lam. 2:9; Ezek. 7:26; Amos 8:11</char></note><char style="it">There</char> <char style="it">is</char> no longer any prophet;</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">there</char> any among us who knows how long.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />O God, how long will the adversary reproach?</para>
	<para style="q2">Will the enemy blaspheme Your name forever?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lam. 2:3</char></note>Why do You withdraw Your hand, even Your right hand?</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Take</char> <char style="it">it</char> out of Your bosom and destroy <char style="it">them.</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 44:4</char></note>God <char style="it">is</char> my King from of old,</para>
	<para style="q2">Working salvation in the midst of the earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 14:21</char></note>You divided the sea by Your strength;</para>
	<para style="q2">You broke the heads of the sea serpents in the waters.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />You broke the heads of Leviathan in pieces,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> gave him <char style="it">as</char> food to the people inhabiting the wilderness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 17:5, 6; Num. 20:11; Ps. 105:41; Is. 48:21</char></note>You broke open the fountain and the flood;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 14:21, 22; Josh. 2:10; 3:13</char></note>You dried up mighty rivers.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />The day <char style="it">is</char> Yours, the night also <char style="it">is</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 38:12</char></note>Yours;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 1:14–18</char></note>You have prepared the light and the sun.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />You have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 32:8; Acts 17:26</char></note>set all the borders of the earth;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 8:22</char></note>You have made summer and winter.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="18" style="v" />Remember this, <char style="it">that</char> the enemy has reproached, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">that</char> a foolish people has blasphemed Your name.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />Oh, do not deliver the life of Your turtledove to the wild beast!</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not forget the life of Your poor forever.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 17:7, 8; Lev. 26:44, 45</char></note>Have respect to the covenant;</para>
	<para style="q2">For the dark places of the earth are full of the haunts of cruelty.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />Oh, do not let the oppressed return ashamed!</para>
	<para style="q2">Let the poor and needy praise Your name.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="22" style="v" />Arise, O God, plead Your own cause;</para>
	<para style="q2">Remember how the foolish man reproaches You daily.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" />Do not forget the voice of Your enemies;</para>
	<para style="q2">The tumult of those who rise up against You increases continually.</para>
	<chapter number="75" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Thanksgiving for God’s Righteous Judgment</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. Set to <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 57:title</char></note>“Do Not Destroy.” A Psalm of Asaph. A Song.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />We give thanks to You, O God, we give thanks!</para>
	<para style="q2">For Your wondrous works declare <char style="it">that</char> Your name is near.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" />“When I choose the proper time,</para>
	<para style="q2">I will judge uprightly.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />The earth and all its inhabitants are dissolved;</para>
	<para style="q2">I set up its pillars firmly.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />“I said to the boastful, ‘Do not deal boastfully,’</para>
	<para style="q2">And to the wicked, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Sam. 2:3); Ps. 94:4</char></note>‘Do not lift up the horn.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Do not lift up your horn on high;</para>
	<para style="q2">Do <char style="it">not</char> speak with a stiff neck.’ ”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />For exaltation <char style="it">comes</char> neither from the east</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor from the west nor from the south.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 50:6</char></note>God <char style="it">is</char> the Judge:</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 2:7; Ps. 147:6; Dan. 2:21</char></note>He puts down one,</para>
	<para style="q2">And exalts another.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 21:20; Ps. 60:3; Jer. 25:15; Rev. 14:10; 16:19</char></note>in the hand of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> a cup,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the wine is red;</para>
	<para style="q2">It is fully mixed, and He pours it out;</para>
	<para style="q2">Surely its dregs shall all the wicked of the earth</para>
	<para style="q2">Drain <char style="it">and</char> drink down.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />But I will declare forever,</para>
	<para style="q2">I will sing praises to the God of Jacob.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />“All<note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 101:8; Jer. 48:25</char></note> the horns of the wicked I will also cut off,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">But</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 89:17; 148:14</char></note>the horns of the righteous shall be <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 2:1</char></note>exalted.”</para>
	<chapter number="76" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Majesty of God in Judgment</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. On stringed instruments. A Psalm of Asaph. A Song.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />In <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 48:1, 3</char></note>Judah God <char style="it">is</char> known;</para>
	<para style="q2">His name <char style="it">is</char> great in Israel.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />In Salem also is His tabernacle,</para>
	<para style="q2">And His dwelling place in Zion.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />There He broke the arrows of the bow,</para>
	<para style="q2">The shield and sword of battle.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />You <char style="it">are</char> more glorious and excellent</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ezek. 38:12</char></note><char style="it">Than</char> the mountains of prey.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 10:12; 46:12</char></note>The stouthearted were plundered;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 13:3</char></note>They have sunk into their sleep;</para>
	<para style="q2">And none of the mighty men have found the use of their hands.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 15:1–21; Ezek. 39:20; Nah. 2:13; Zech. 12:4</char></note>At Your rebuke, O God of Jacob,</para>
	<para style="q2">Both the chariot and horse were cast into a dead sleep.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />You, Yourself, <char style="it">are</char> to be feared;</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ezra 9:15; Nah. 1:6; Mal. 3:2; Rev. 6:17)</char></note>who may stand in Your presence</para>
	<para style="q2">When once You are angry?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 19:9</char></note>You caused judgment to be heard from heaven;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 16:30; 2 Chr. 20:29</char></note>The earth feared and was still,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />When God <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 9:7–9)</char></note>arose to judgment,</para>
	<para style="q2">To deliver all the oppressed of the earth.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 9:16; Rom. 9:17</char></note>Surely the wrath of man shall praise You;</para>
	<para style="q2">With the remainder of wrath You shall gird Yourself.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Eccl. 5:4–6)</char></note>Make vows to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> your God, and pay <char style="it">them;</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Chr. 32:22, 23</char></note>Let all who are around Him bring presents to Him who ought to be feared.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />He shall cut off the spirit of princes;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 68:35</char></note><char style="it">He</char> <char style="it">is</char> awesome to the kings of the earth.</para>
	<chapter number="77" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Consoling Memory of God’s Redemptive Works</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 39:title</char></note>To Jeduthun. A Psalm of Asaph.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />I cried out to God with my voice—</para>
	<para style="q2">To God with my voice;</para>
	<para style="q2">And He gave ear to me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />In the day of my trouble I sought the Lord;</para>
	<para style="q2">My hand was stretched out in the night without ceasing;</para>
	<para style="q2">My soul refused to be comforted.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />I remembered God, and was troubled;</para>
	<para style="q2">I complained, and my spirit was overwhelmed.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />You hold my eyelids <char style="it">open;</char></para>
	<para style="q2">I am so troubled that I cannot speak.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />I have considered the days of old,</para>
	<para style="q2">The years of ancient times.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />I call to remembrance my song in the night;</para>
	<para style="q2">I meditate within my heart,</para>
	<para style="q2">And my spirit makes diligent search.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />Will the Lord cast off forever?</para>
	<para style="q2">And will He be favorable no more?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Has His mercy ceased forever?</para>
	<para style="q2">Has <char style="it">His</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(2 Pet. 3:8, 9)</char></note>promise failed forevermore?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />Has God forgotten to be gracious?</para>
	<para style="q2">Has He in anger shut up His tender mercies?</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />And I said, “This <char style="it">is</char> my anguish;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">But</char> <char style="it">I</char> <char style="it">will</char> <char style="it">remember</char> the years of the right hand of the Most High.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />I will remember the works of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">Surely I will remember Your wonders of old.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />I will also meditate on all Your work,</para>
	<para style="q2">And talk of Your deeds.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />Your way, O God, <char style="it">is</char> in the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 73:17</char></note>sanctuary;</para>
	<para style="q2">Who <char style="it">is</char> so great a God as <char style="it">our</char> God?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />You <char style="it">are</char> the God who does wonders;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have declared Your strength among the peoples.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />You have with <char style="it">Your</char> arm redeemed Your people,</para>
	<para style="q2">The sons of Jacob and Joseph.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" />The waters saw You, O God;</para>
	<para style="q2">The waters saw You, they were <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 14:21; Hab. 3:8, 10</char></note>afraid;</para>
	<para style="q2">The depths also trembled.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />The clouds poured out water;</para>
	<para style="q2">The skies sent out a sound;</para>
	<para style="q2">Your arrows also flashed about.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />The voice of Your thunder <char style="it">was</char> in the whirlwind;</para>
	<para style="q2">The lightnings lit up the world;</para>
	<para style="q2">The earth trembled and shook.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />Your way <char style="it">was</char> in the sea,</para>
	<para style="q2">Your path in the great waters,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Your footsteps were not known.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />You led Your people like a flock</para>
	<para style="q2">By the hand of Moses and Aaron.</para>
	<chapter number="78" style="c" />
	<para style="s">God’s Kindness to Rebellious Israel</para>
	<para style="d">A <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 74:title</char></note>Contemplation of Asaph.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Give ear, O my people, <char style="it">to</char> my law;</para>
	<para style="q2">Incline your ears to the words of my mouth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />I will open my mouth in a <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 13:34, 35</char></note>parable;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will utter dark sayings of old,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Which we have heard and known,</para>
	<para style="q2">And our fathers have told us.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 12:26, 27; Deut. 4:9; 6:7; Job 15:18; Is. 38:19; Joel 1:3</char></note>We will not hide <char style="it">them</char> from their children,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 13:8, 14</char></note>Telling to the generation to come the praises of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And His strength and His wonderful works that He has done.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 147:19</char></note>He established a testimony in Jacob,</para>
	<para style="q2">And appointed a law in Israel,</para>
	<para style="q2">Which He commanded our fathers,</para>
	<para style="q2">That <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 4:9; 11:19</char></note>they should make them known to their children;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 102:18</char></note>That the generation to come might know <char style="it">them,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">The children <char style="it">who</char> would be born,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">That</char> they may arise and declare <char style="it">them</char> to their children,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />That they may set their hope in God,</para>
	<para style="q2">And not forget the works of God,</para>
	<para style="q2">But keep His commandments;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Kin. 17:14; 2 Chr. 30:7; Ezek. 20:18</char></note>may not be like their fathers,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 32:9; Deut. 9:7, 24; 31:27; Judg. 2:19; Is. 30:9</char></note>A stubborn and rebellious generation,</para>
	<para style="q2">A generation <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 11:13; Ps. 78:37</char></note><char style="it">that</char> did not set its heart aright,</para>
	<para style="q2">And whose spirit was not faithful to God.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />The children of Ephraim, <char style="it">being</char> armed <char style="it">and</char> carrying bows,</para>
	<para style="q2">Turned back in the day of battle.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Kin. 17:15</char></note>They did not keep the covenant of God;</para>
	<para style="q2">They refused to walk in His law,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 106:13</char></note>forgot His works</para>
	<para style="q2">And His wonders that He had shown them.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 7—12</char></note>Marvelous things He did in the sight of their fathers,</para>
	<para style="q2">In the land of Egypt, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 13:22; Is. 19:11; 30:4; Ezek. 30:14</char></note><char style="it">in</char> the field of Zoan.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 14:21</char></note>He divided the sea and caused them to pass through;</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 15:8</char></note>He made the waters stand up like a heap.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 13:21</char></note>In the daytime also He led them with the cloud,</para>
	<para style="q2">And all the night with a light of fire.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 17:6; Num. 20:11; Is. 48:21; (1 Cor. 10:4)</char></note>He split the rocks in the wilderness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And gave <char style="it">them</char> drink in abundance like the depths.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />He also brought <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 20:8, 10, 11</char></note>streams out of the rock,</para>
	<para style="q2">And caused waters to run down like rivers.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="17" style="v" />But they sinned even more against Him</para>
	<para style="q2">By <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 9:22; Is. 63:10; Heb. 3:16</char></note>rebelling against the Most High in the wilderness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 16:2</char></note>they tested God in their heart</para>
	<para style="q2">By asking for the food of their fancy.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 16:3; Num. 11:4; 20:3; 21:5</char></note>Yes, they spoke against God:</para>
	<para style="q2">They said, “Can God prepare a table in the wilderness?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 20:11</char></note>Behold, He struck the rock,</para>
	<para style="q2">So that the waters gushed out,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the streams overflowed.</para>
	<para style="q2">Can He give bread also?</para>
	<para style="q2">Can He provide meat for His people?”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="21" style="v" />Therefore the <char style="sc">Lord</char> heard <char style="it">this</char> and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 11:1</char></note>was furious;</para>
	<para style="q2">So a fire was kindled against Jacob,</para>
	<para style="q2">And anger also came up against Israel,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" />Because they <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 1:32; 9:23; (Heb. 3:18)</char></note>did not believe in God,</para>
	<para style="q2">And did not trust in His salvation.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" />Yet He had commanded the clouds above,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 7:11; (Mal. 3:10)</char></note>And opened the doors of heaven,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 16:4</char></note>Had rained down manna on them to eat,</para>
	<para style="q2">And given them of the bread of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">John 6:31</char></note>heaven.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="25" style="v" />Men ate angels’ food;</para>
	<para style="q2">He sent them food to the full.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="26" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 11:31</char></note>He caused an east wind to blow in the heavens;</para>
	<para style="q2">And by His power He brought in the south wind.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="27" style="v" />He also rained meat on them like the dust,</para>
	<para style="q2">Feathered fowl like the sand of the seas;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="28" style="v" />And He let <char style="it">them</char> fall in the midst of their camp,</para>
	<para style="q2">All around their dwellings.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="29" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 11:19, 20</char></note>So they ate and were well filled,</para>
	<para style="q2">For He gave them their own desire.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="30" style="v" />They were not deprived of their craving;</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 11:33</char></note>while their food <char style="it">was</char> still in their mouths,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="31" style="v" />The wrath of God came against them,</para>
	<para style="q2">And slew the stoutest of them,</para>
	<para style="q2">And struck down the choice <char style="it">men</char> of Israel.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="32" style="v" />In spite of this <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 14:16, 17</char></note>they still sinned,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 14:11; Ps. 78:11, 22</char></note>did not believe in His wondrous works.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="33" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 14:29, 35</char></note>Therefore their days He consumed in futility,</para>
	<para style="q2">And their years in fear.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="34" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 21:7; (Hos. 5:15)</char></note>When He slew them, then they sought Him;</para>
	<para style="q2">And they returned and sought earnestly for God.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="35" style="v" />Then they remembered that <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 32:4, 15)</char></note>God <char style="it">was</char> their rock,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the Most High God <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 15:13); Deut. 7:8; Is. 41:14; 44:6; 63:9</char></note>their Redeemer.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="36" style="v" />Nevertheless they <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 24:7, 8; Ezek. 33:31</char></note>flattered Him with their mouth,</para>
	<para style="q2">And they lied to Him with their tongue;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="37" style="v" />For their heart was not steadfast with Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor were they faithful in His covenant.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="38" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Num. 14:18–20)</char></note>But He, <char style="it">being</char> full of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 34:6</char></note>compassion, forgave <char style="it">their</char> iniquity,</para>
	<para style="q2">And did not destroy <char style="it">them.</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Yes, many a time <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 48:9)</char></note>He turned His anger away,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 21:29</char></note>did not stir up all His wrath;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="39" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 10:9; Ps. 103:14–16</char></note>He remembered <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">John 3:6</char></note>that they <char style="it">were</char> <char style="it">but</char> flesh,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Job 7:7, 16; James 4:14)</char></note>A breath that passes away and does not come again.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="40" style="v" />How often they <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 95:8–10; (Eph. 4:30); Heb. 3:16</char></note>provoked Him in the wilderness,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> grieved Him in the desert!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="41" style="v" />Yes, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 14:22; Deut. 6:16</char></note>again and again they tempted God,</para>
	<para style="q2">And limited the Holy One of Israel.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="42" style="v" />They did not remember His power:</para>
	<para style="q2">The day when He redeemed them from the enemy,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="43" style="v" />When He worked His signs in Egypt,</para>
	<para style="q2">And His wonders in the field of Zoan;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="44" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 7:20</char></note>Turned their rivers into blood,</para>
	<para style="q2">And their streams, that they could not drink.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="45" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 8:24</char></note>He sent swarms of flies among them, which devoured them,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 8:6</char></note>frogs, which destroyed them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="46" style="v" />He also gave their crops to the caterpillar,</para>
	<para style="q2">And their labor to the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 10:14</char></note>locust.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="47" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 9:23–25</char></note>He destroyed their vines with hail,</para>
	<para style="q2">And their sycamore trees with frost.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="48" style="v" />He also gave up their <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 9:19</char></note>cattle to the hail,</para>
	<para style="q2">And their flocks to fiery lightning.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="49" style="v" />He cast on them the fierceness of His anger,</para>
	<para style="q2">Wrath, indignation, and trouble,</para>
	<para style="q2">By sending angels of destruction <char style="it">among</char> <char style="it">them.</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="50" style="v" />He made a path for His anger;</para>
	<para style="q2">He did not spare their soul from death,</para>
	<para style="q2">But gave their life over to the plague,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="51" style="v" />And destroyed all the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 12:29, 30</char></note>firstborn in Egypt,</para>
	<para style="q2">The first of <char style="it">their</char> strength in the tents of Ham.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="52" style="v" />But He <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 77:20</char></note>made His own people go forth like sheep,</para>
	<para style="q2">And guided them in the wilderness like a flock;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="53" style="v" />And He <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 14:19, 20</char></note>led them on safely, so that they did not fear;</para>
	<para style="q2">But the sea <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 14:27, 28</char></note>overwhelmed their enemies.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="54" style="v" />And He brought them to His <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 15:17</char></note>holy border,</para>
	<para style="q2">This mountain <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 44:3</char></note><char style="it">which</char> His right hand had acquired.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="55" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Josh. 11:16–23; Ps. 44:2</char></note>He also drove out the nations before them,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Josh. 13:7; 19:51; 23:4</char></note>Allotted them an inheritance by survey,</para>
	<para style="q2">And made the tribes of Israel dwell in their tents.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="56" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Judg. 2:11–13</char></note>Yet they tested and provoked the Most High God,</para>
	<para style="q2">And did not keep His testimonies,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="57" style="v" />But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ezek. 20:27, 28</char></note>turned back and acted unfaithfully like their fathers;</para>
	<para style="q2">They were turned aside <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Hos. 7:16</char></note>like a deceitful bow.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="58" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 32:16, 21; Judg. 2:12; 1 Kin. 14:9; Is. 65:3</char></note>For they provoked Him to anger with their <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 12:2</char></note>high places,</para>
	<para style="q2">And moved Him to jealousy with their carved images.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="59" style="v" />When God heard <char style="it">this,</char> He was furious,</para>
	<para style="q2">And greatly abhorred Israel,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="60" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 4:11; Jer. 7:12–14; 26:6–9</char></note>So that He forsook the tabernacle of Shiloh,</para>
	<para style="q2">The tent He had placed among men,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="61" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Judg. 18:30</char></note>And delivered His strength into captivity,</para>
	<para style="q2">And His glory into the enemy’s hand.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="62" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Judg. 20:21; 1 Sam. 4:10</char></note>He also gave His people over to the sword,</para>
	<para style="q2">And was furious with His inheritance.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="63" style="v" />The fire consumed their young men,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 7:34; 16:9; 25:10</char></note>their maidens were not given in marriage.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="64" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 4:17; 22:18</char></note>Their priests fell by the sword,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 27:15; Ezek. 24:23</char></note>their widows made no lamentation.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="65" style="v" />Then the Lord awoke as <char style="it">from</char> sleep,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 42:13</char></note>Like a mighty man who shouts because of wine.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="66" style="v" />And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 5:6</char></note>He beat back His enemies;</para>
	<para style="q2">He put them to a perpetual reproach.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="67" style="v" />Moreover He rejected the tent of Joseph,</para>
	<para style="q2">And did not choose the tribe of Ephraim,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="68" style="v" />But chose the tribe of Judah,</para>
	<para style="q2">Mount Zion <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 87:2)</char></note>which He loved.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="69" style="v" />And He built His <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 6:1–38</char></note>sanctuary like the heights,</para>
	<para style="q2">Like the earth which He has established forever.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="70" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 16:11, 12; 2 Sam. 7:8</char></note>He also chose David His servant,</para>
	<para style="q2">And took him from the sheepfolds;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="71" style="v" />From following <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 7:8; (Is. 40:11)</char></note>the ewes that had young He brought him,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 5:2; 1 Chr. 11:2</char></note>To shepherd Jacob His people,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Israel His inheritance.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="72" style="v" />So he shepherded them according to the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 9:4</char></note>integrity of his heart,</para>
	<para style="q2">And guided them by the skillfulness of his hands.</para>
	<chapter number="79" style="c" />
	<para style="s">A Dirge and a Prayer for Israel, Destroyed by Enemies</para>
	<para style="d">A Psalm of Asaph.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />O God, the nations have come into <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 74:2</char></note>Your inheritance;</para>
	<para style="q2">Your holy temple they have defiled;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Kin. 25:9, 10; 2 Chr. 36:17–19; Jer. 26:18; 52:12–14; Mic. 3:12</char></note>They have laid Jerusalem in heaps.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 28:26; Jer. 7:33; 19:7; 34:20</char></note>The dead bodies of Your servants</para>
	<para style="q2">They have given <char style="it">as</char> food for the birds of the heavens,</para>
	<para style="q2">The flesh of Your saints to the beasts of the earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Their blood they have shed like water all around Jerusalem,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">was</char> no one to bury <char style="it">them.</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />We have become a reproach to our <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 44:13; (Dan. 9:16)</char></note>neighbors,</para>
	<para style="q2">A scorn and derision to those who are around us.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 74:1, 9</char></note>How long, <char style="sc">Lord</char>?</para>
	<para style="q2">Will You be angry forever?</para>
	<para style="q2">Will Your <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Zeph. 3:8)</char></note>jealousy burn like fire?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 10:25; (Zeph. 3:8)</char></note>Pour out Your wrath on the nations that <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 45:4, 5; 1 Thess. 4:5; (2 Thess. 1:8)</char></note>do not know You,</para>
	<para style="q2">And on the kingdoms that <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 53:4</char></note>do not call on Your name.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />For they have devoured Jacob,</para>
	<para style="q2">And laid waste his dwelling place.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 64:9</char></note>Oh, do not remember former iniquities against us!</para>
	<para style="q2">Let Your tender mercies come speedily to meet us,</para>
	<para style="q2">For we have been brought very low.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />Help us, O God of our salvation,</para>
	<para style="q2">For the glory of Your name;</para>
	<para style="q2">And deliver us, and provide atonement for our sins,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 14:7, 21</char></note>For Your name’s sake!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 42:10</char></note>Why should the nations say,</para>
	<para style="q2">“Where <char style="it">is</char> their God?”</para>
	<para style="q2">Let there be known among the nations in our sight</para>
	<para style="q2">The avenging of the blood of Your servants <char style="it">which</char> <char style="it">has</char> <char style="it">been</char> shed.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" />Let <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 102:20</char></note>the groaning of the prisoner come before You;</para>
	<para style="q2">According to the greatness of Your power</para>
	<para style="q2">Preserve those who are appointed to die;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />And return to our neighbors <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 4:15; Lev. 26:21; Prov. 6:31; Is. 30:26</char></note>sevenfold into their bosom</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 74:10, 18, 22</char></note>Their reproach with which they have reproached You, O Lord.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" />So <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 74:1; 95:7</char></note>we, Your people and sheep of Your pasture,</para>
	<para style="q2">Will give You thanks forever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 43:21</char></note>We will show forth Your praise to all generations.</para>
	<chapter number="80" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Prayer for Israel’s Restoration</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 45:title</char></note>Set to “The Lilies.” A Testimony of Asaph. A Psalm.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Give ear, O Shepherd of Israel,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 25:20–22); 1 Sam. 4:4; 2 Sam. 6:2</char></note>You who lead Joseph <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 77:20</char></note>like a flock;</para>
	<para style="q2">You who dwell <char style="it">between</char> the cherubim, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 33:2</char></note>shine forth!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Before <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 78:9, 67</char></note>Ephraim, Benjamin, and Manasseh,</para>
	<para style="q2">Stir up Your strength,</para>
	<para style="q2">And come <char style="it">and</char> save us!</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lam. 5:21</char></note>Restore us, O God;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 6:25; Ps. 4:6</char></note>Cause Your face to shine,</para>
	<para style="q2">And we shall be saved!</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />O <char style="sc">Lord</char> God of hosts,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 79:5</char></note>How long will You be angry</para>
	<para style="q2">Against the prayer of Your people?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 42:3; Is. 30:20</char></note>You have fed them with the bread of tears,</para>
	<para style="q2">And given them tears to drink in great measure.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />You have made us a strife to our neighbors,</para>
	<para style="q2">And our enemies laugh among themselves.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />Restore us, O God of hosts;</para>
	<para style="q2">Cause Your face to shine,</para>
	<para style="q2">And we shall be saved!</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />You have brought <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 5:1, 7); Jer. 2:21; Ezek. 15:6; 17:6; 19:10</char></note>a vine out of Egypt;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 44:2; Acts 7:45</char></note>You have cast out the nations, and planted it.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />You prepared <char style="it">room</char> for it,</para>
	<para style="q2">And caused it to take deep root,</para>
	<para style="q2">And it filled the land.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />The hills were covered with its shadow,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the mighty cedars with its <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 23:40</char></note>boughs.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />She sent out her boughs to the Sea,</para>
	<para style="q2">And her branches to the River.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />Why have You <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 5:5; Nah. 2:2</char></note>broken down her hedges,</para>
	<para style="q2">So that all who pass by the way pluck her <char style="it">fruit?</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />The boar out of the woods uproots it,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the wild beast of the field devours it.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" />Return, we beseech You, O God of hosts;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 63:15</char></note>Look down from heaven and see,</para>
	<para style="q2">And visit this vine</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />And the vineyard which Your right hand has planted,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the branch <char style="it">that</char> You made strong <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 49:5)</char></note>for Yourself.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" /><char style="it">It</char> <char style="it">is</char> burned with fire, <char style="it">it</char> <char style="it">is</char> cut down;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 39:11)</char></note>They perish at the rebuke of Your countenance.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 89:21</char></note>Let Your hand be upon the man of Your right hand,</para>
	<para style="q2">Upon the son of man <char style="it">whom</char> You made strong for Yourself.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />Then we will not turn back from You;</para>
	<para style="q2">Revive us, and we will call upon Your name.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" />Restore us, O <char style="sc">Lord</char> God of hosts;</para>
	<para style="q2">Cause Your face to shine,</para>
	<para style="q2">And we shall be saved!</para>
	<chapter number="81" style="c" />
	<para style="s">An Appeal for Israel’s Repentance</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 8:title</char></note>On an instrument of Gath. <char style="it">A</char> <char style="it">Psalm</char> of Asaph.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Sing aloud to God our strength;</para>
	<para style="q2">Make a joyful shout to the God of Jacob.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Raise a song and strike the timbrel,</para>
	<para style="q2">The pleasant harp with the lute.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />Blow the trumpet at the time of the New Moon,</para>
	<para style="q2">At the full moon, on our solemn feast day.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 23:24; Num. 10:10</char></note>this <char style="it">is</char> a statute for Israel,</para>
	<para style="q2">A law of the God of Jacob.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />This He established in Joseph <char style="it">as</char> a testimony,</para>
	<para style="q2">When He went throughout the land of Egypt,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 28:49; Ps. 114:1; Jer. 5:15</char></note><char style="it">Where</char> I heard a language I did not understand.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />“I removed his shoulder from the burden;</para>
	<para style="q2">His hands were freed from the baskets.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 2:23; 14:10; Ps. 50:15</char></note>You called in trouble, and I delivered you;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 19:19; 20:18</char></note>I answered you in the secret place of thunder;</para>
	<para style="q2">I <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 17:6, 7; Num. 20:13</char></note>tested you at the waters of Meribah.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />“Hear,<note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 50:7)</char></note> O My people, and I will admonish you!</para>
	<para style="q2">O Israel, if you will listen to Me!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />There shall be no <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 20:3; Deut. 5:7; 32:12); Ps. 44:20; (Is. 43:12)</char></note>foreign god among you;</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor shall you worship any foreign god.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 20:2; Deut. 5:6</char></note>I <char style="it">am</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char> your God,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who brought you out of the land of Egypt;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 103:5</char></note>Open your mouth wide, and I will fill it.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" />“But My people would not heed My voice,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Israel would <char style="it">have</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 32:1; Deut. 32:15</char></note>none of Me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Job 8:4; Acts 7:42; Rom. 1:24, 26)</char></note>So I gave them over to their own stubborn heart,</para>
	<para style="q2">To walk in their own counsels.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" />“Oh,<note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 5:29; Is. 48:18)</char></note> that My people would listen to Me,</para>
	<para style="q2">That Israel would walk in My ways!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />I would soon subdue their enemies,</para>
	<para style="q2">And turn My hand against their adversaries.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rom. 1:30</char></note>The haters of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> would pretend submission to Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">But their fate would endure forever.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />He would <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 32:14</char></note>have fed them also with the finest of wheat;</para>
	<para style="q2">And with honey <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 29:6</char></note>from the rock I would have satisfied you.”</para>
	<chapter number="82" style="c" />
	<para style="s">A Plea for Justice</para>
	<para style="d">A Psalm of Asaph.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />God <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(2 Chr. 19:6; Eccl. 5:8)</char></note>stands in the congregation of the mighty;</para>
	<para style="q2">He judges among <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 82:6</char></note>the gods.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />How long will you judge unjustly,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 1:17); Prov. 18:5</char></note>show partiality to the wicked?</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Defend the poor and fatherless;</para>
	<para style="q2">Do justice to the afflicted and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 24:17; Is. 11:4; Jer. 22:16)</char></note>needy.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Deliver the poor and needy;</para>
	<para style="q2">Free <char style="it">them</char> from the hand of the wicked.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />They do not know, nor do they understand;</para>
	<para style="q2">They walk about in darkness;</para>
	<para style="q2">All the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 11:3</char></note>foundations of the earth are unstable.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />I said, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">John 10:34</char></note>“You <char style="it">are</char> gods,</para>
	<para style="q2">And all of you <char style="it">are</char> children of the Most High.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />But you shall die like men,</para>
	<para style="q2">And fall like one of the princes.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />Arise, O God, judge the earth;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 2:8; (Rev. 11:15)</char></note>For You shall inherit all nations.</para>
	<chapter number="83" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Prayer to Frustrate Conspiracy Against Israel</para>
	<para style="d">A Song. A Psalm of Asaph.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Do<note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 28:1</char></note> not keep silent, O God!</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not hold Your peace,</para>
	<para style="q2">And do not be still, O God!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />For behold, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 81:15; Is. 17:12; Acts 4:25</char></note>Your enemies make a tumult;</para>
	<para style="q2">And those who hate You have lifted up their head.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />They have taken crafty counsel against Your people,</para>
	<para style="q2">And consulted together <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 27:5)</char></note>against Your sheltered ones.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />They have said, “Come, and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Esth. 3:6, 9; Jer. 11:19; 31:36</char></note>let us cut them off from <char style="it">being</char> a nation,</para>
	<para style="q2">That the name of Israel may be remembered no more.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />For they have consulted together with one consent;</para>
	<para style="q2">They form a confederacy against You:</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Chr. 20:1, 10, 11</char></note>The tents of Edom and the Ishmaelites;</para>
	<para style="q2">Moab and the Hagrites;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Gebal, Ammon, and Amalek;</para>
	<para style="q2">Philistia with the inhabitants of Tyre;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Assyria also has joined with them;</para>
	<para style="q2">They have helped the children of Lot.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />Deal with them as <char style="it">with</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 31:7; Judg. 7:22</char></note>Midian,</para>
	<para style="q2">As <char style="it">with</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Judg. 4:15–24; 5:20, 21</char></note>Sisera,</para>
	<para style="q2">As <char style="it">with</char> Jabin at the Brook Kishon,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />Who perished at En Dor,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Zeph. 1:17</char></note><char style="it">Who</char> became <char style="it">as</char> refuse on the earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />Make their nobles like <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Judg. 7:25</char></note>Oreb and like Zeeb,</para>
	<para style="q2">Yes, all their princes like <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Judg. 8:12–21</char></note>Zebah and Zalmunna,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />Who said, “Let us take for ourselves</para>
	<para style="q2">The pastures of God for a possession.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 17:13</char></note>O my God, make them like the whirling dust,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 21:18; Ps. 35:5; Is. 40:24; Jer. 13:24</char></note>Like the chaff before the wind!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />As the fire burns the woods,</para>
	<para style="q2">And as the flame <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 19:18; Deut. 32:22</char></note>sets the mountains on fire,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />So pursue them with Your tempest,</para>
	<para style="q2">And frighten them with Your storm.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />Fill their faces with shame,</para>
	<para style="q2">That they may seek Your name, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />Let them be confounded and dismayed forever;</para>
	<para style="q2">Yes, let them be put to shame and perish,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 59:13</char></note>That they may know that You, whose <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 6:3</char></note>name alone <char style="it">is</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Are</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 92:8)</char></note>the Most High over all the earth.</para>
	<chapter number="84" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Blessedness of Dwelling in the House of God</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 8:title</char></note>On an instrument of Gath. A Psalm of the sons of Korah.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />How <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 27:4; 46:4, 5</char></note>lovely <char style="it">is</char> Your tabernacle,</para>
	<para style="q2">O <char style="sc">Lord</char> of hosts!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 42:1, 2</char></note>My soul longs, yes, even faints</para>
	<para style="q2">For the courts of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">My heart and my flesh cry out for the living God.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />Even the sparrow has found a home,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the swallow a nest for herself,</para>
	<para style="q2">Where she may lay her young—</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Even</char> Your altars, O <char style="sc">Lord</char> of hosts,</para>
	<para style="q2">My King and my God.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Blessed <char style="it">are</char> those who dwell in Your <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 65:4)</char></note>house;</para>
	<para style="q2">They will still be praising You.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />Blessed <char style="it">is</char> the man whose strength <char style="it">is</char> in You,</para>
	<para style="q2">Whose heart <char style="it">is</char> set on pilgrimage.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><char style="it">As</char> <char style="it">they</char> pass through the Valley <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 5:22–25</char></note>of Baca,</para>
	<para style="q2">They make it a spring;</para>
	<para style="q2">The rain also covers it with pools.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />They go <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 4:18; Is. 40:31; John 1:16; 2 Cor. 3:18</char></note>from strength to strength;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Each</char> <char style="it">one</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 34:23; Deut. 16:16</char></note>appears before God in Zion.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />O <char style="sc">Lord</char> God of hosts, hear my prayer;</para>
	<para style="q2">Give ear, O God of Jacob!</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 15:1</char></note>O God, behold our shield,</para>
	<para style="q2">And look upon the face of Your anointed.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />For a day in Your courts <char style="it">is</char> better than a thousand.</para>
	<para style="q2">I would rather be a doorkeeper in the house of my God</para>
	<para style="q2">Than dwell in the tents of wickedness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />For the <char style="sc">Lord</char> God <char style="it">is</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 60:19, 20; Mal. 4:2; Rev. 21:23</char></note>a sun and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 15:1</char></note>shield;</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> will give grace and glory;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 34:9, 10</char></note>No good <char style="it">thing</char> will He withhold</para>
	<para style="q2">From those who walk uprightly.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />O <char style="sc">Lord</char> of hosts,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 2:12; 40:4)</char></note>Blessed <char style="it">is</char> the man who trusts in You!</para>
	<chapter number="85" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Prayer that the <char style="sc">Lord</char> Will Restore Favor to the Land</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. A Psalm <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 42:title</char></note>of the sons of Korah.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" /><char style="sc">Lord</char>, You have been favorable to Your land;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ezra 1:11—2:1; Ps. 14:7; Jer. 30:18; 31:23; Ezek. 39:25; Hos. 6:11; Joel 3:1</char></note>brought back the captivity of Jacob.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />You have forgiven the iniquity of Your people;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have covered all their sin.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />You have taken away all Your wrath;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have turned from the fierceness of Your anger.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 80:3, 7</char></note>Restore us, O God of our salvation,</para>
	<para style="q2">And cause Your anger toward us to cease.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 79:5</char></note>Will You be angry with us forever?</para>
	<para style="q2">Will You prolong Your anger to all generations?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Will You not <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Hab. 3:2</char></note>revive us again,</para>
	<para style="q2">That Your people may rejoice in You?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Show us Your mercy, <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And grant us Your salvation.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />I will hear what God the <char style="sc">Lord</char> will speak,</para>
	<para style="q2">For He will speak peace</para>
	<para style="q2">To His people and to His saints;</para>
	<para style="q2">But let them not turn back to folly.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />Surely <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 46:13</char></note>His salvation <char style="it">is</char> near to those who fear Him,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Hag. 2:7; Zech. 2:5; (John 1:14)</char></note>That glory may dwell in our land.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />Mercy and truth have met together;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 72:3; (Is. 32:17); Luke 2:14</char></note>Righteousness and peace have kissed.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />Truth shall spring out of the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2">And righteousness shall look down from heaven.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 84:11; James 1:17)</char></note>Yes, the <char style="sc">Lord</char> will give <char style="it">what</char> <char style="it">is</char> good;</para>
	<para style="q2">And our land will yield its increase.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />Righteousness will go before Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">And shall make His footsteps <char style="it">our</char> pathway.</para>
	<chapter number="86" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Prayer for Mercy, with Meditation on the Excellencies of the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="d">A Prayer of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Bow down Your ear, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, hear me;</para>
	<para style="q2">For I <char style="it">am</char> poor and needy.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Preserve my life, for I <char style="it">am</char> holy;</para>
	<para style="q2">You are my God;</para>
	<para style="q2">Save Your servant who trusts in You!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Be merciful to me, O Lord,</para>
	<para style="q2">For I cry to You all day long.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Rejoice the soul of Your servant,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 25:1; 143:8</char></note>For to You, O Lord, I lift up my soul.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 130:7; 145:9; (Joel 2:13)</char></note>You, Lord, <char style="it">are</char> good, and ready to forgive,</para>
	<para style="q2">And abundant in mercy to all those who call upon You.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />Give ear, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, to my prayer;</para>
	<para style="q2">And attend to the voice of my supplications.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />In the day of my trouble I will call upon You,</para>
	<para style="q2">For You will answer me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 15:11); 2 Sam. 7:22; 1 Kin. 8:23; Ps. 89:6; Jer. 10:6</char></note>Among the gods <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> none like You, O Lord;</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor <char style="it">are</char> <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">any</char> <char style="it">works</char> like Your works.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />All nations whom You have made</para>
	<para style="q2">Shall come and worship before You, O Lord,</para>
	<para style="q2">And shall glorify Your name.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />For You <char style="it">are</char> great, and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 15:11)</char></note>do wondrous things;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 6:4; Is. 37:16; Mark 12:29; 1 Cor. 8:4</char></note>You alone <char style="it">are</char> God.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 27:11; 143:8</char></note>Teach me Your way, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will walk in Your truth;</para>
	<para style="q2">Unite my heart to fear Your name.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />I will praise You, O Lord my God, with all my heart,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I will glorify Your name forevermore.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />For great <char style="it">is</char> Your mercy toward me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And You have delivered my soul from the depths of Sheol.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" />O God, the proud have risen against me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And a mob of violent <char style="it">men</char> have sought my life,</para>
	<para style="q2">And have not set You before them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 34:6; (Ps. 86:5)</char></note>You, O Lord, <char style="it">are</char> a God full of compassion, and gracious,</para>
	<para style="q2">Longsuffering and abundant in mercy and truth.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" />Oh, turn to me, and have mercy on me!</para>
	<para style="q2">Give Your strength to Your servant,</para>
	<para style="q2">And save the son of Your maidservant.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />Show me a sign for good,</para>
	<para style="q2">That those who hate me may see <char style="it">it</char> and be ashamed,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because You, <char style="sc">Lord</char>, have helped me and comforted me.</para>
	<chapter number="87" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Glories of the City of God</para>
	<para style="d">A Psalm of the sons of Korah. A Song.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />His foundation <char style="it">is</char> in the holy mountains.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 78:67, 68</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> loves the gates of Zion</para>
	<para style="q2">More than all the dwellings of Jacob.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 60:1</char></note>Glorious things are spoken of you,</para>
	<para style="q2">O city of God!</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />“I will make mention of Rahab and Babylon to those who know Me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Behold, O Philistia and Tyre, with Ethiopia:</para>
	<para style="q2">‘This <char style="it">one</char> was born there.’ ”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />And of Zion it will be said,</para>
	<para style="q2">“This <char style="it">one</char> and that <char style="it">one</char> were born in her;</para>
	<para style="q2">And the Most High Himself shall establish her.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> will record,</para>
	<para style="q2">When He <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 4:3</char></note>registers the peoples:</para>
	<para style="q2">“This <char style="it">one</char> was born there.”</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />Both the singers and the players on instruments <char style="it">say,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">“All my springs <char style="it">are</char> in you.”</para>
	<chapter number="88" style="c" />
	<para style="s">A Prayer for Help in Despondency</para>
	<para style="d">A Song. A Psalm of the sons of Korah. To the Chief Musician. Set to “Mahalath Leannoth.” A Contemplation of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 4:31; 1 Chr. 2:6</char></note>Heman the Ezrahite.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 27:9; (Luke 18:7)</char></note>God of my salvation,</para>
	<para style="q2">I have cried out day and night before You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Let my prayer come before You;</para>
	<para style="q2">Incline Your ear to my cry.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />For my soul is full of troubles,</para>
	<para style="q2">And my life <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 107:18</char></note>draws near to the grave.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />I am counted with those who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 28:1)</char></note>go down to the pit;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 31:12</char></note>I am like a man <char style="it">who</char> <char style="it">has</char> no strength,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Adrift among the dead,</para>
	<para style="q2">Like the slain who lie in the grave,</para>
	<para style="q2">Whom You remember no more,</para>
	<para style="q2">And who are cut off from Your hand.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />You have laid me in the lowest pit,</para>
	<para style="q2">In darkness, in the depths.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Your wrath lies heavy upon me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And You have afflicted <char style="it">me</char> with all <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 42:7</char></note>Your waves.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 19:13, 19; Ps. 31:11; 142:4</char></note>You have put away my acquaintances far from me;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have made me an abomination to them;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lam. 3:7</char></note><char style="it">I</char> <char style="it">am</char> shut up, and I cannot get out;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />My eye wastes away because of affliction.</para>
	<para style="q1"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 86:3</char></note><char style="sc">Lord</char>, I have called daily upon You;</para>
	<para style="q2">I have stretched out my hands to You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />Will You work wonders for the dead?</para>
	<para style="q2">Shall the dead arise <char style="it">and</char> praise You?</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />Shall Your lovingkindness be declared in the grave?</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Or</char> Your faithfulness in the place of destruction?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />Shall Your wonders be known in the dark?</para>
	<para style="q2">And Your righteousness in the land of forgetfulness?</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" />But to You I have cried out, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And in the morning my prayer comes before You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" /><char style="sc">Lord</char>, why do You cast off my soul?</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Why</char> do You hide Your face from me?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />I <char style="it">have</char> <char style="it">been</char> afflicted and ready to die from <char style="it">my</char> youth;</para>
	<para style="q2">I suffer Your terrors;</para>
	<para style="q2">I am distraught.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />Your fierce wrath has gone over me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Your terrors have cut me off.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />They came around me all day long like water;</para>
	<para style="q2">They engulfed me altogether.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 19:13; Ps. 31:11; 38:11</char></note>Loved one and friend You have put far from me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> my acquaintances into darkness.</para>
	<chapter number="89" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Remembering the Covenant with David, and Sorrow for Lost Blessings</para>
	<para style="d">A Contemplation of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 4:31</char></note>Ethan the Ezrahite.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />I will sing of the mercies of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> forever;</para>
	<para style="q2">With my mouth will I make known Your faithfulness to all generations.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />For I have said, “Mercy shall be built up forever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 119:89, 90)</char></note>Your faithfulness You shall establish in the very heavens.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />“I<note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 8:16</char></note> have made a covenant with My chosen,</para>
	<para style="q2">I have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 7:11; 1 Chr. 17:10–12</char></note>sworn to My servant David:</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />‘Your seed I will establish forever,</para>
	<para style="q2">And build up your throne <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(2 Sam. 7:13; Is. 9:7; Luke 1:33)</char></note>to all generations.’ ”</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 19:1)</char></note>the heavens will praise Your wonders, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">Your faithfulness also in the assembly of the saints.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 86:8; 113:5</char></note>For who in the heavens can be compared to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>?</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Who</char> among the sons of the mighty can be likened to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 76:7, 11</char></note>God is greatly to be feared in the assembly of the saints,</para>
	<para style="q2">And to be held in reverence by all <char style="it">those</char> around Him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />O <char style="sc">Lord</char> God of hosts,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who <char style="it">is</char> mighty like You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>?</para>
	<para style="q2">Your faithfulness also surrounds You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 65:7; 93:3, 4; 107:29</char></note>You rule the raging of the sea;</para>
	<para style="q2">When its waves rise, You still them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 14:26–28; Ps. 87:4; Is. 30:7; 51:9</char></note>You have broken Rahab in pieces, as one who is slain;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have scattered Your enemies with Your mighty arm.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Gen. 1:1; 1 Chr. 29:11)</char></note>The heavens <char style="it">are</char> Yours, the earth also <char style="it">is</char> Yours;</para>
	<para style="q2">The world and all its fullness, You have founded them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />The north and the south, You have created them;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Josh. 19:22; Judg. 4:6; Jer. 46:18</char></note>Tabor and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 3:8; Josh. 11:17; 12:1; Song 4:8</char></note>Hermon rejoice in Your name.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />You have a mighty arm;</para>
	<para style="q2">Strong is Your hand, <char style="it">and</char> high is Your right hand.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />Righteousness and justice <char style="it">are</char> the foundation of Your throne;</para>
	<para style="q2">Mercy and truth go before Your face.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />Blessed <char style="it">are</char> the people who know the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 23:24; Num. 10:10; Ps. 98:6</char></note>joyful sound!</para>
	<para style="q2">They walk, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, in the light of Your countenance.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />In Your name they rejoice all day long,</para>
	<para style="q2">And in Your righteousness they are exalted.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />For You <char style="it">are</char> the glory of their strength,</para>
	<para style="q2">And in Your favor our horn is <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 75:10; 92:10; 132:17</char></note>exalted.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />For our shield <char style="it">belongs</char> to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And our king to the Holy One of Israel.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" />Then You spoke in a vision to Your holy one,</para>
	<para style="q2">And said: “I have given help to <char style="it">one</char> <char style="it">who</char> <char style="it">is</char> mighty;</para>
	<para style="q2">I have exalted one <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 11:34</char></note>chosen from the people.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 13:14; 16:1–12; Acts 13:22</char></note>I have found My servant David;</para>
	<para style="q2">With My holy oil I have anointed him,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 80:17</char></note>With whom My hand shall be established;</para>
	<para style="q2">Also My arm shall strengthen him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" />The enemy shall not outwit him,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor the son of wickedness afflict him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" />I will beat down his foes before his face,</para>
	<para style="q2">And plague those who hate him.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="24" style="v" />“But My faithfulness and My mercy <char style="it">shall</char> <char style="it">be</char> with him,</para>
	<para style="q2">And in My name his horn shall be exalted.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="25" style="v" />Also I will <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 72:8</char></note>set his hand over the sea,</para>
	<para style="q2">And his right hand over the rivers.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="26" style="v" />He shall cry to Me, ‘You <char style="it">are</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 7:14; (1 Chr. 22:10); Jer. 3:19</char></note>my Father,</para>
	<para style="q2">My God, and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 22:47</char></note>the rock of my salvation.’</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="27" style="v" />Also I will make him <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 4:22; Ps. 2:7; Jer. 31:9; (Col. 1:15, 18)</char></note><char style="it">My</char> firstborn,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 24:7; (Ps. 72:11); Rev. 19:16</char></note>The highest of the kings of the earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="28" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 55:3</char></note>My mercy I will keep for him forever,</para>
	<para style="q2">And My covenant shall stand firm with him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="29" style="v" />His seed also I will make <char style="it">to</char> <char style="it">endure</char> forever,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Kin. 2:4; Is. 9:7); Jer. 33:17</char></note>And his throne <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 11:21</char></note>as the days of heaven.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="30" style="v" />“If<note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(2 Sam. 7:14)</char></note> his sons <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:53</char></note>forsake My law</para>
	<para style="q2">And do not walk in My judgments,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="31" style="v" />If they break My statutes</para>
	<para style="q2">And do not keep My commandments,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="32" style="v" />Then I will punish their transgression with the rod,</para>
	<para style="q2">And their iniquity with stripes.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="33" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 7:14, 15</char></note>Nevertheless My lovingkindness I will not utterly take from him,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor allow My faithfulness to fail.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="34" style="v" />My covenant I will not break,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Num. 23:19); Jer. 33:20–22</char></note>alter the word that has gone out of My lips.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="35" style="v" />Once I have sworn <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Sam. 15:29); Amos 4:2; (Titus 1:2)</char></note>by My holiness;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will not lie to David:</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="36" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Luke 1:33)</char></note>His seed shall endure forever,</para>
	<para style="q2">And his throne <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 72:17</char></note>as the sun before Me;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="37" style="v" />It shall be established forever like the moon,</para>
	<para style="q2">Even <char style="it">like</char> the faithful witness in the sky.”</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="38" style="v" />But You have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Chr. 28:9)</char></note>cast off and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 32:19</char></note>abhorred,</para>
	<para style="q2">You have been furious with Your anointed.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="39" style="v" />You have renounced the covenant of Your servant;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 74:7; Lam. 5:16</char></note>You have profaned his crown <char style="it">by</char> <char style="it">casting</char> <char style="it">it</char> to the ground.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="40" style="v" />You have broken down all his hedges;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have brought his strongholds to ruin.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="41" style="v" />All who pass by the way <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 80:12</char></note>plunder him;</para>
	<para style="q2">He is a reproach to his neighbors.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="42" style="v" />You have exalted the right hand of his adversaries;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have made all his enemies rejoice.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="43" style="v" />You have also turned back the edge of his sword,</para>
	<para style="q2">And have not sustained him in the battle.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="44" style="v" />You have made his glory cease,</para>
	<para style="q2">And cast his throne down to the ground.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="45" style="v" />The days of his youth You have shortened;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have covered him with shame.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="46" style="v" />How long, <char style="sc">Lord</char>?</para>
	<para style="q2">Will You hide Yourself forever?</para>
	<para style="q2">Will Your wrath burn like fire?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="47" style="v" />Remember how short my time <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 90:9</char></note>is;</para>
	<para style="q2">For what <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 62:9</char></note>futility have You created all the children of men?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="48" style="v" />What man can live and not see <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Eccl. 3:19)</char></note>death?</para>
	<para style="q2">Can he deliver his life from the power of the grave?</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="49" style="v" />Lord, where <char style="it">are</char> Your former lovingkindnesses,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Which</char> You <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(2 Sam. 7:15); Jer. 30:9; Ezek. 34:23</char></note>swore to David <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 54:5</char></note>in Your truth?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="50" style="v" />Remember, Lord, the reproach of Your servants—</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 69:9, 19</char></note><char style="it">How</char> I bear in my bosom <char style="it">the</char> <char style="it">reproach</char> <char style="it">of</char> all the many peoples,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="51" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 74:10, 18, 22</char></note>With which Your enemies have reproached, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">With which they have reproached the footsteps of Your anointed.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="52" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 41:13</char></note>Blessed <char style="it">be</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char> forevermore!</para>
	<para style="q2">Amen and Amen.</para>
	<chapter number="90" style="c" />
	<para style="s">BOOK FOUR: Psalms 90—106</para>
	<para style="s">The Eternity of God, and Man’s Frailty</para>
	<para style="d">A Prayer <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 33:1</char></note>of Moses the man of God.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Lord, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 33:27; Ezek. 11:16)</char></note>You have been our dwelling place in all generations.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 15:7; (Prov. 8:25, 26)</char></note>Before the mountains were brought forth,</para>
	<para style="q2">Or ever You had formed the earth and the world,</para>
	<para style="q2">Even from everlasting to everlasting, You <char style="it">are</char> God.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />You turn man to destruction,</para>
	<para style="q2">And say, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 3:19; Job 34:14, 15</char></note>“Return, O children of men.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Pet. 3:8</char></note>For a thousand years in Your sight</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Are</char> like yesterday when it is past,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">like</char> a watch in the night.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />You carry them away <char style="it">like</char> a flood;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 73:20</char></note><char style="it">They</char> <char style="it">are</char> like a sleep.</para>
	<para style="q2">In the morning <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 40:6</char></note>they are like grass <char style="it">which</char> grows up:</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />In the morning it flourishes and grows up;</para>
	<para style="q2">In the evening it is cut down and withers.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />For we have been consumed by Your anger,</para>
	<para style="q2">And by Your wrath we are terrified.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 50:21; (Jer. 16:17)</char></note>You have set our iniquities before You,</para>
	<para style="q2">Our <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 19:12; (Eccl. 12:14)</char></note>secret <char style="it">sins</char> in the light of Your countenance.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />For all our days have passed away in Your wrath;</para>
	<para style="q2">We finish our years like a sigh.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />The days of our lives <char style="it">are</char> seventy years;</para>
	<para style="q2">And if by reason of strength <char style="it">they</char> <char style="it">are</char> eighty years,</para>
	<para style="q2">Yet their boast <char style="it">is</char> only labor and sorrow;</para>
	<para style="q2">For it is soon cut off, and we fly away.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />Who knows the power of Your anger?</para>
	<para style="q2">For as the fear of You, <char style="it">so</char> <char style="it">is</char> Your wrath.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 32:29; Ps. 39:4</char></note>So teach <char style="it">us</char> to number our days,</para>
	<para style="q2">That we may gain a heart of wisdom.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" />Return, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q2">How long?</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 32:12; Deut. 32:36</char></note>have compassion on Your servants.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />Oh, satisfy us early with Your mercy,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 85:6</char></note>That we may rejoice and be glad all our days!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />Make us glad according to the days <char style="it">in</char> <char style="it">which</char> You have afflicted us,</para>
	<para style="q2">The years <char style="it">in</char> <char style="it">which</char> we have seen evil.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />Let <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 32:4); Hab. 3:2</char></note>Your work appear to Your servants,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Your glory to their children.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 27:4</char></note>And let the beauty of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> our God be upon us,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 26:12</char></note>establish the work of our hands for us;</para>
	<para style="q2">Yes, establish the work of our hands.</para>
	<chapter number="91" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Safety of Abiding in the Presence of God</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />He <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 27:5; 31:20; 32:7</char></note>who dwells in the secret place of the Most High</para>
	<para style="q2">Shall abide <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 17:8; Is. 25:4; 32:2</char></note>under the shadow of the Almighty.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 142:5</char></note>I will say of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <char style="it">“He is</char> my refuge and my fortress;</para>
	<para style="q2">My God, in Him I will trust.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />Surely <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 124:7; Prov. 6:5</char></note>He shall deliver you from the snare of the fowler</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> from the perilous pestilence.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 17:8</char></note>He shall cover you with His feathers,</para>
	<para style="q2">And under His wings you shall take refuge;</para>
	<para style="q2">His truth <char style="it">shall</char> <char style="it">be</char> <char style="it">your</char> shield and buckler.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Job 5:19; Ps. 112:7; Is. 43:2)</char></note>You shall not be afraid of the terror by night,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Nor</char> of the arrow <char style="it">that</char> flies by day,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><char style="it">Nor</char> of the pestilence <char style="it">that</char> walks in darkness,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Nor</char> of the destruction <char style="it">that</char> lays waste at noonday.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />A thousand may fall at your side,</para>
	<para style="q2">And ten thousand at your right hand;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">But</char> it shall not come near you.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Only <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:34; Mal. 1:5</char></note>with your eyes shall you look,</para>
	<para style="q2">And see the reward of the wicked.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />Because you have made the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <char style="it">who</char> <char style="it">is</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 91:2</char></note>my refuge,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Even</char> the Most High, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 90:1</char></note>your dwelling place,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Prov. 12:21)</char></note>No evil shall befall you,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor shall any plague come near your dwelling;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 34:7; Matt. 4:6; Luke 4:10; (Heb. 1:14)</char></note>For He shall give His angels charge over you,</para>
	<para style="q2">To keep you in all your ways.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />In <char style="it">their</char> hands they shall bear you up,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 4:6; Luke 4:11</char></note>Lest you dash your foot against a stone.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />You shall tread upon the lion and the cobra,</para>
	<para style="q2">The young lion and the serpent you shall trample underfoot.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" />“Because he has set his love upon Me, therefore I will deliver him;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will set him on high, because he has <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 9:10)</char></note>known My name.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />He shall <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 12:4; Ps. 50:15</char></note>call upon Me, and I will answer him;</para>
	<para style="q2">I <char style="it">will</char> <char style="it">be</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 43:2</char></note>with him in trouble;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will deliver him and honor him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />With long life I will satisfy him,</para>
	<para style="q2">And show him My salvation.”</para>
	<chapter number="92" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Praise to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> for His Love and Faithfulness</para>
	<para style="d">A Psalm. A Song for the Sabbath day.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" /><char style="it">It</char> <char style="it">is</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 147:1</char></note>good to give thanks to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And to sing praises to Your name, O Most High;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />To <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 89:1</char></note>declare Your lovingkindness in the morning,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Your faithfulness every night,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 23:5</char></note>On an instrument of ten strings,</para>
	<para style="q2">On the lute,</para>
	<para style="q2">And on the harp,</para>
	<para style="q2">With harmonious sound.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />For You, <char style="sc">Lord</char>, have made me glad through Your work;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will triumph in the works of Your hands.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 40:5; (Rev. 15:3)</char></note>O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, how great are Your works!</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 139:17, 18; (Is. 28:29; Rom. 11:33, 34)</char></note>Your thoughts are very deep.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 73:22</char></note>A senseless man does not know,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor does a fool understand this.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />When <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 12:6; Ps. 37:1, 2; Jer. 12:1, 2; (Mal. 3:15)</char></note>the wicked spring up like grass,</para>
	<para style="q2">And when all the workers of iniquity flourish,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">It</char> <char style="it">is</char> that they may be destroyed forever.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 83:18)</char></note>But You, <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <char style="it">are</char> on high forevermore.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />For behold, Your enemies, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">For behold, Your enemies shall perish;</para>
	<para style="q2">All the workers of iniquity shall <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 68:1</char></note>be scattered.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 89:17</char></note>my horn You have exalted like a wild ox;</para>
	<para style="q2">I have been <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 23:5</char></note>anointed with fresh oil.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 54:7</char></note>My eye also has seen <char style="it">my</char> <char style="it">desire</char> on my enemies;</para>
	<para style="q2">My ears hear <char style="it">my</char> <char style="it">desire</char> on the wicked</para>
	<para style="q2">Who rise up against me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 24:6; Ps. 52:8; Jer. 17:8; Hos. 14:5, 6</char></note>The righteous shall flourish like a palm tree,</para>
	<para style="q2">He shall grow like a cedar in Lebanon.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />Those who are planted in the house of the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Shall flourish in the courts of our God.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />They shall still bear fruit in old age;</para>
	<para style="q2">They shall be fresh and flourishing,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />To declare that the <char style="sc">Lord</char> is upright;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 32:4)</char></note><char style="it">He</char> <char style="it">is</char> my rock, and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Rom. 9:14)</char></note><char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> no unrighteousness in Him.</para>
	<chapter number="93" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Eternal Reign of the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />The <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 96:10</char></note><char style="sc">Lord</char> reigns, He is clothed with majesty;</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> is clothed,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 65:6</char></note>He has girded Himself with strength.</para>
	<para style="q2">Surely the world is established, so that it cannot be moved.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 45:6; (Lam. 5:19)</char></note>Your throne <char style="it">is</char> established from of old;</para>
	<para style="q2">You <char style="it">are</char> from everlasting.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />The floods have lifted up, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">The floods have lifted up their voice;</para>
	<para style="q2">The floods lift up their waves.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 65:7</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> on high <char style="it">is</char> mightier</para>
	<para style="q2">Than the noise of many waters,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Than</char> the mighty waves of the sea.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />Your testimonies are very sure;</para>
	<para style="q2">Holiness adorns Your house,</para>
	<para style="q2">O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, forever.</para>
	<chapter number="94" style="c" />
	<para style="s">God the Refuge of the Righteous</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />O <char style="sc">Lord</char> God, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 32:35; (Is. 35:4; Nah. 1:2; Rom. 12:19)</char></note>to whom vengeance belongs—</para>
	<para style="q2">O God, to whom vengeance belongs, shine forth!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Rise up, O <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Gen. 18:25)</char></note>Judge of the earth;</para>
	<para style="q2">Render punishment to the proud.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><char style="sc">Lord</char>, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Job 20:5)</char></note>how long will the wicked,</para>
	<para style="q2">How long will the wicked triumph?</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />They <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 31:18; Jude 15</char></note>utter speech, <char style="it">and</char> speak insolent things;</para>
	<para style="q2">All the workers of iniquity boast in themselves.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />They break in pieces Your people, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And afflict Your heritage.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />They slay the widow and the stranger,</para>
	<para style="q2">And murder the fatherless.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 22:13; Ps. 10:11</char></note>Yet they say, “The <char style="sc">Lord</char> does not see,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor does the God of Jacob understand.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />Understand, you senseless among the people;</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">you</char> fools, when will you be wise?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 4:11; Prov. 20:12)</char></note>He who planted the ear, shall He not hear?</para>
	<para style="q2">He who formed the eye, shall He not see?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />He who instructs the nations, shall He not correct,</para>
	<para style="q2">He who teaches man knowledge?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 11:11; 1 Cor. 3:20</char></note>knows the thoughts of man,</para>
	<para style="q2">That they <char style="it">are</char> futile.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />Blessed <char style="it">is</char> the man whom You <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 8:5; Job 5:17; Ps. 119:71; Prov. 3:11, 12; Heb. 12:5, 6)</char></note>instruct, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And teach out of Your law,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />That You may give him rest from the days of adversity,</para>
	<para style="q2">Until the pit is dug for the wicked.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />For the <char style="sc">Lord</char> will not cast off His people,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor will He forsake His inheritance.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />But judgment will return to righteousness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And all the upright in heart will follow it.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" />Who will rise up for me against the evildoers?</para>
	<para style="q2">Who will stand up for me against the workers of iniquity?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />Unless the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">had</char> <char style="it">been</char> my help,</para>
	<para style="q2">My soul would soon have settled in silence.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />If I say, “My foot slips,”</para>
	<para style="q2">Your mercy, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, will hold me up.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />In the multitude of my anxieties within me,</para>
	<para style="q2">Your comforts delight my soul.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="20" style="v" />Shall <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Amos 6:3</char></note>the throne of iniquity, which devises evil by law,</para>
	<para style="q2">Have fellowship with You?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />They gather together against the life of the righteous,</para>
	<para style="q2">And condemn <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 23:7); Ps. 106:38; (Prov. 17:15); Matt. 27:4</char></note>innocent blood.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" />But the <char style="sc">Lord</char> has been my defense,</para>
	<para style="q2">And my God the rock of my refuge.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" />He has brought on them their own iniquity,</para>
	<para style="q2">And shall cut them off in their own wickedness;</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> our God shall cut them off.</para>
	<chapter number="95" style="c" />
	<para style="s">A Call to Worship and Obedience</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Oh come, let us sing to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q2">Let us shout joyfully to the Rock of our salvation.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Let us come before His presence with thanksgiving;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let us shout joyfully to Him with <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Eph. 5:19; James 5:13</char></note>psalms.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 96:4; 1 Cor. 8:5, 6)</char></note>the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> the great God,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the great King above all gods.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />In His hand <char style="it">are</char> the deep places of the earth;</para>
	<para style="q2">The heights of the hills <char style="it">are</char> His also.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 1:9, 10; Jon. 1:9</char></note>The sea <char style="it">is</char> His, for He made it;</para>
	<para style="q2">And His hands formed the dry <char style="it">land.</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />Oh come, let us worship and bow down;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Chr. 6:13; Dan. 6:10; (Phil. 2:10)</char></note>us kneel before the <char style="sc">Lord</char> our Maker.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />For He <char style="it">is</char> our God,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 79:13</char></note>we <char style="it">are</char> the people of His pasture,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the sheep of His hand.</para>
	<para style="q1"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Heb. 3:7–11, 15; 4:7</char></note>Today, if you will hear His voice:</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />“Do not harden your hearts, as in the rebellion,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 17:2–7; Num. 20:13</char></note>As <char style="it">in</char> the day of trial in the wilderness,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />When <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 78:18; (1 Cor. 10:9)</char></note>your fathers tested Me;</para>
	<para style="q2">They tried Me, though they <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 14:22</char></note>saw My work.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Acts 7:36; 13:18; Heb. 3:10, 17</char></note>For forty years I was grieved with <char style="it">that</char> generation,</para>
	<para style="q2">And said, ‘It <char style="it">is</char> a people who go astray in their hearts,</para>
	<para style="q2">And they do not know My ways.’</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />So <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 14:23, 28–30; Deut. 1:35; Heb. 4:3, 5</char></note>I swore in My wrath,</para>
	<para style="q2">‘They shall not enter My rest.’ ”</para>
	<chapter number="96" style="c" />
	<para style="s">A Song of Praise to God Coming in Judgment</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Oh, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 16:23–33</char></note>sing to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> a new song!</para>
	<para style="q2">Sing to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, all the earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Sing to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, bless His name;</para>
	<para style="q2">Proclaim the good news of His salvation from day to day.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Declare His glory among the nations,</para>
	<para style="q2">His wonders among all peoples.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 145:3</char></note>the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> great and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 18:3</char></note>greatly to be praised;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 95:3</char></note>He <char style="it">is</char> to be feared above all gods.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 16:26; (Jer. 10:11)</char></note>all the gods of the peoples <char style="it">are</char> idols,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 115:15; Is. 42:5</char></note>But the <char style="sc">Lord</char> made the heavens.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Honor and majesty <char style="it">are</char> before Him;</para>
	<para style="q2">Strength and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 29:2</char></note>beauty <char style="it">are</char> in His sanctuary.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 16:28, 29; Ps. 29:1, 2</char></note>Give to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, O families of the peoples,</para>
	<para style="q2">Give to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> glory and strength.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Give to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> the glory <char style="it">due</char> His name;</para>
	<para style="q2">Bring an offering, and come into His courts.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />Oh, worship the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 16:29; 2 Chr. 20:21; Ps. 29:2</char></note>in the beauty of holiness!</para>
	<para style="q2">Tremble before Him, all the earth.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />Say among the nations, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 93:1; 97:1; (Rev. 11:15; 19:6)</char></note>“The <char style="sc">Lord</char> reigns;</para>
	<para style="q2">The world also is firmly established,</para>
	<para style="q2">It shall not be moved;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 67:4</char></note>He shall judge the peoples righteously.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 69:34; Is. 49:13</char></note>Let the heavens rejoice, and let the earth be glad;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 98:7</char></note>Let the sea roar, and all its fullness;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />Let the field be joyful, and all that <char style="it">is</char> in it.</para>
	<para style="q2">Then all the trees of the woods will rejoice before the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />For He is coming, for He is coming to judge the earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Rev. 19:11)</char></note>He shall judge the world with righteousness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the peoples with His truth.</para>
	<chapter number="97" style="c" />
	<para style="s">A Song of Praise to the Sovereign <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 96:10)</char></note>reigns;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let the earth rejoice;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let the multitude of isles be glad!</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 19:9; Deut. 4:11; 1 Kin. 8:12; Ps. 18:11</char></note>Clouds and darkness surround Him;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 89:14)</char></note>Righteousness and justice <char style="it">are</char> the foundation of His throne.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 18:8; Dan. 7:10; Hab. 3:5</char></note>A fire goes before Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">And burns up His enemies round about.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 19:18</char></note>His lightnings light the world;</para>
	<para style="q2">The earth sees and trembles.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 46:6; Amos 9:5; Mic. 1:4; Nah. 1:5</char></note>The mountains melt like wax at the presence of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">At the presence of the Lord of the whole earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 19:1</char></note>The heavens declare His righteousness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And all the peoples see His glory.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 20:4)</char></note>Let all be put to shame who serve carved images,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who boast of idols.</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Heb. 1:6)</char></note>Worship Him, all <char style="it">you</char> gods.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Zion hears and is glad,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the daughters of Judah rejoice</para>
	<para style="q2">Because of Your judgments, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />For You, <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <char style="it">are</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 83:18</char></note>most high above all the earth;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 18:11; Ps. 95:3; 96:4</char></note>You are exalted far above all gods.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />You who love the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 34:14; Prov. 8:13; Amos 5:15; Rom. 12:9)</char></note>hate evil!</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 31:23; 145:20; Prov. 2:8</char></note>He preserves the souls of His saints;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:40; Jer. 15:21; Dan. 3:28</char></note>He delivers them out of the hand of the wicked.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 22:28; Ps. 112:4; Prov. 4:18</char></note>Light is sown for the righteous,</para>
	<para style="q2">And gladness for the upright in heart.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 33:1</char></note>Rejoice in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, you righteous,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 30:4</char></note>And give thanks at the remembrance of His holy name.</para>
	<chapter number="98" style="c" />
	<para style="s">A Song of Praise to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> for His Salvation and Judgment</para>
	<para style="d">A Psalm.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Oh, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 33:3; Is. 42:10</char></note>sing to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> a new song!</para>
	<para style="q2">For He has <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 15:11; Ps. 77:14</char></note>done marvelous things;</para>
	<para style="q2">His right hand and His holy arm have gained Him the victory.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 52:10; (Luke 1:77; 2:30, 31)</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> has made known His salvation;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 62:2; Rom. 3:25</char></note>His righteousness He has revealed in the sight of the nations.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />He has remembered His mercy and His faithfulness to the house of Israel;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 49:6); Luke 3:6; (Acts 13:47; 28:28)</char></note>All the ends of the earth have seen the salvation of our God.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />Shout joyfully to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, all the earth;</para>
	<para style="q2">Break forth in song, rejoice, and sing praises.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Sing to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> with the harp,</para>
	<para style="q2">With the harp and the sound of a psalm,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />With trumpets and the sound of a horn;</para>
	<para style="q2">Shout joyfully before the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, the King.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />Let the sea roar, and all its fullness,</para>
	<para style="q2">The world and those who dwell in it;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Let the rivers clap <char style="it">their</char> hands;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let the hills be joyful together before the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 96:10, 13)</char></note>For He is coming to judge the earth.</para>
	<para style="q2">With righteousness He shall judge the world,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the peoples with equity.</para>
	<chapter number="99" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Praise to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> for His Holiness</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> reigns;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let the peoples tremble!</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 25:22; 1 Sam. 4:4; Ps. 80:1</char></note>He dwells <char style="it">between</char> the cherubim;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let the earth be moved!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> great in Zion,</para>
	<para style="q2">And He <char style="it">is</char> high above all the peoples.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Let them praise Your great and awesome name—</para>
	<para style="q2">He <char style="it">is</char> holy.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />The King’s strength also loves justice;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have established equity;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have executed justice and righteousness in Jacob.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Exalt the <char style="sc">Lord</char> our God,</para>
	<para style="q2">And worship at His footstool—</para>
	<para style="q2">He <char style="it">is</char> holy.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />Moses and Aaron were among His priests,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Samuel was among those who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 7:9; 12:18</char></note>called upon His name;</para>
	<para style="q2">They called upon the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, and He answered them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />He spoke to them in the cloudy pillar;</para>
	<para style="q2">They kept His testimonies and the ordinance He gave them.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />You answered them, O <char style="sc">Lord</char> our God;</para>
	<para style="q2">You were to them God-Who-Forgives,</para>
	<para style="q2">Though You took vengeance on their deeds.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />Exalt the <char style="sc">Lord</char> our God,</para>
	<para style="q2">And worship at His holy hill;</para>
	<para style="q2">For the <char style="sc">Lord</char> our God <char style="it">is</char> holy.</para>
	<chapter number="100" style="c" />
	<para style="s">A Song of Praise for the <char style="sc">Lord</char>’s Faithfulness to His People</para>
	<para style="d"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 145:title</char></note>A Psalm of Thanksgiving.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Make <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 95:1</char></note>a joyful shout to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, all you lands!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Serve the <char style="sc">Lord</char> with gladness;</para>
	<para style="q2">Come before His presence with singing.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Know that the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, He <char style="it">is</char> God;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 10:3, 8; Ps. 119:73; 139:13, 14; (Eph. 2:10)</char></note><char style="it">It</char> <char style="it">is</char> He <char style="it">who</char> has made us, and not we ourselves;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 95:7; (Is. 40:11); Ezek. 34:30, 31</char></note><char style="it">We</char> <char style="it">are</char> His people and the sheep of His pasture.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 66:13; 116:17–19</char></note>Enter into His gates with thanksgiving,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> into His courts with praise.</para>
	<para style="q2">Be thankful to Him, <char style="it">and</char> bless His name.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />For the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> good;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 136:1</char></note>His mercy <char style="it">is</char> everlasting,</para>
	<para style="q2">And His truth <char style="it">endures</char> to all generations.</para>
	<chapter number="101" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Promised Faithfulness to the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="d">A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />I will sing of mercy and justice;</para>
	<para style="q2">To You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, I will sing praises.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" />I will behave wisely in a perfect way.</para>
	<para style="q2">Oh, when will You come to me?</para>
	<para style="q2">I will <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 11:4</char></note>walk within my house with a perfect heart.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />I will set nothing wicked before my eyes;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 97:10</char></note>I hate the work of those <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Josh. 23:6</char></note>who fall away;</para>
	<para style="q2">It shall not cling to me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />A perverse heart shall depart from me;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will not <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 119:115)</char></note>know wickedness.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />Whoever secretly slanders his neighbor,</para>
	<para style="q2">Him I will destroy;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 6:17</char></note>The one who has a haughty look and a proud heart,</para>
	<para style="q2">Him I will not endure.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />My eyes <char style="it">shall</char> <char style="it">be</char> on the faithful of the land,</para>
	<para style="q2">That they may dwell with me;</para>
	<para style="q2">He who walks in a perfect way,</para>
	<para style="q2">He shall serve me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />He who works deceit shall not dwell within my house;</para>
	<para style="q2">He who tells lies shall not continue in my presence.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 75:10); Jer. 21:12</char></note>Early I will destroy all the wicked of the land,</para>
	<para style="q2">That I may cut off all the evildoers <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 48:2, 8</char></note>from the city of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<chapter number="102" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The <char style="sc">Lord</char>’s Eternal Love</para>
	<para style="d">A Prayer of the afflicted, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 61:2</char></note>when he is overwhelmed and pours out his complaint before the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Hear my prayer, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And let my cry come to You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 27:9; 69:17</char></note>Do not hide Your face from me in the day of my trouble;</para>
	<para style="q2">Incline Your ear to me;</para>
	<para style="q2">In the day that I call, answer me speedily.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />For my days are <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">James 4:14</char></note>consumed like smoke,</para>
	<para style="q2">And my bones are burned like a hearth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />My heart is stricken and withered like grass,</para>
	<para style="q2">So that I forget to eat my bread.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Because of the sound of my groaning</para>
	<para style="q2">My bones cling to my skin.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />I am like a pelican of the wilderness;</para>
	<para style="q2">I am like an owl of the desert.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />I lie awake,</para>
	<para style="q2">And am like a sparrow alone on the housetop.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />My enemies reproach me all day long;</para>
	<para style="q2">Those who deride me swear an oath against me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />For I have eaten ashes like bread,</para>
	<para style="q2">And mingled my drink with weeping,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />Because of Your indignation and Your wrath;</para>
	<para style="q2">For You have lifted me up and cast me away.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />My days <char style="it">are</char> like a shadow that lengthens,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I wither away like grass.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />But You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, shall endure forever,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the remembrance of Your name to all generations.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />You will arise <char style="it">and</char> have mercy on Zion;</para>
	<para style="q2">For the time to favor her,</para>
	<para style="q2">Yes, the set time, has come.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />For Your servants take pleasure in her stones,</para>
	<para style="q2">And show favor to her dust.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />So the nations shall <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 8:43</char></note>fear the name of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And all the kings of the earth Your glory.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />For the <char style="sc">Lord</char> shall build up Zion;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 60:1, 2)</char></note>He shall appear in His glory.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Neh. 1:6; Ps. 22:24</char></note>He shall regard the prayer of the destitute,</para>
	<para style="q2">And shall not despise their prayer.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="18" style="v" />This will be <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 31:19; (Rom. 15:4; 1 Cor. 10:11)</char></note>written for the generation to come,</para>
	<para style="q2">That <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 22:31</char></note>a people yet to be created may praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />For He <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 26:15; Ps. 14:2</char></note>looked down from the height of His sanctuary;</para>
	<para style="q2">From heaven the <char style="sc">Lord</char> viewed the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 79:11</char></note>To hear the groaning of the prisoner,</para>
	<para style="q2">To release those appointed to death,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />To <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 22:22</char></note>declare the name of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> in Zion,</para>
	<para style="q2">And His praise in Jerusalem,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 2:2, 3; 49:22, 23; 60:3); Zech. 8:20–23</char></note>When the peoples are gathered together,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the kingdoms, to serve the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="23" style="v" />He weakened my strength in the way;</para>
	<para style="q2">He <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 21:21</char></note>shortened my days.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 39:13); Is. 38:10</char></note>I said, “O my God,</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not take me away in the midst of my days;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 36:26; (Ps. 90:2); Hab. 1:12</char></note>Your years <char style="it">are</char> throughout all generations.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="25" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Gen. 1:1; Neh. 9:6; Heb. 1:10–12)</char></note>Of old You laid the foundation of the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the heavens <char style="it">are</char> the work of Your hands.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="26" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 34:4; 51:6; Matt. 24:35; (2 Pet. 3:7, 10–12); Rev. 20:11</char></note>They will perish, but You will endure;</para>
	<para style="q2">Yes, they will all grow old like a garment;</para>
	<para style="q2">Like a cloak You will change them,</para>
	<para style="q2">And they will be changed.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="27" style="v" />But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 41:4; 43:10; Mal. 3:6; Heb. 13:8); James 1:17</char></note>You <char style="it">are</char> the same,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Your years will have no end.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="28" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 69:36</char></note>The children of Your servants will continue,</para>
	<para style="q2">And their descendants will be established before You.”</para>
	<chapter number="103" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Praise for the <char style="sc">Lord</char>’s Mercies</para>
	<para style="d"><char style="it">A</char> <char style="it">Psalm</char> of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Bless <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 104:1, 35</char></note>the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, O my soul;</para>
	<para style="q2">And all that is within me, <char style="it">bless</char> His holy name!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Bless the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, O my soul,</para>
	<para style="q2">And forget not all His benefits:</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 130:8; Is. 33:24</char></note>Who forgives all your iniquities,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 15:26); Ps. 147:3; (Is. 53:5); Jer. 17:14</char></note>heals all your diseases,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Who redeems your life from destruction,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 5:12)</char></note>Who crowns you with lovingkindness and tender mercies,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Who satisfies your mouth with good <char style="it">things,</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">So</char> <char style="it">that</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 40:31)</char></note>your youth is renewed like the eagle’s.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> executes righteousness</para>
	<para style="q2">And justice for all who are oppressed.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 33:12–17; Ps. 147:19</char></note>He made known His ways to Moses,</para>
	<para style="q2">His acts to the children of Israel.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 34:6, 7; Num. 14:18); Deut. 5:10; Neh. 9:17; Ps. 86:15; Jer. 32:18; Jon. 4:2; James 5:11</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> merciful and gracious,</para>
	<para style="q2">Slow to anger, and abounding in mercy.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 30:5; Is. 57:16); Jer. 3:5; (Mic. 7:18)</char></note>He will not always strive <char style="it">with</char> <char style="it">us,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Nor will He keep <char style="it">His</char> <char style="it">anger</char> forever.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ezra 9:13; Lam. 3:22)</char></note>He has not dealt with us according to our sins,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor punished us according to our iniquities.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" />For as the heavens are high above the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">So</char> great is His mercy toward those who fear Him;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />As far as the east is from the west,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">So</char> far has He <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(2 Sam. 12:13; Is. 38:17; 43:25; Zech. 3:9; Heb. 9:26)</char></note>removed our transgressions from us.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Mal. 3:17</char></note>As a father pities <char style="it">his</char> children,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">So</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char> pities those who fear Him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />For He knows our frame;</para>
	<para style="q2">He remembers that we <char style="it">are</char> dust.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" /><char style="it">As</char> <char style="it">for</char> man, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 40:6–8; James 1:10, 11; 1 Pet. 1:24</char></note>his days <char style="it">are</char> like grass;</para>
	<para style="q2">As a flower of the field, so he flourishes.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 40:7)</char></note>For the wind passes over it, and it is gone,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 7:10</char></note>its place remembers it no more.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />But the mercy of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> from everlasting to everlasting</para>
	<para style="q2">On those who fear Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">And His righteousness to children’s children,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 7:9); Ps. 25:10</char></note>To such as keep His covenant,</para>
	<para style="q2">And to those who remember His commandments to do them.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> has established His throne in heaven,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 47:2; Dan. 4:17, 25)</char></note>His kingdom rules over all.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="20" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 148:2</char></note>Bless the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, you His angels,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who excel in strength, who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Matt. 6:10)</char></note>do His word,</para>
	<para style="q2">Heeding the voice of His word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />Bless the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, all <char style="it">you</char> His hosts,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Heb. 1:14)</char></note><char style="it">You</char> ministers of His, who do His pleasure.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" />Bless the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, all His works,</para>
	<para style="q2">In all places of His dominion.</para>
	<para style="q1">Bless the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, O my soul!</para>
	<chapter number="104" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Praise to the Sovereign <char style="sc">Lord</char> for His Creation and Providence</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Bless <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 103:1</char></note>the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, O my soul!</para>
	<para style="q1">O <char style="sc">Lord</char> my God, You are very great:</para>
	<para style="q2">You are clothed with honor and majesty,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Who cover <char style="it">Yourself</char> with light as <char style="it">with</char> a garment,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who stretch out the heavens like a curtain.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Amos 9:6)</char></note>He lays the beams of His upper chambers in the waters,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who makes the clouds His chariot,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who walks on the wings of the wind,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Who makes His angels spirits,</para>
	<para style="q2">His ministers a flame of fire.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><char style="it">You</char> <char style="it">who</char> laid the foundations of the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2">So <char style="it">that</char> it should not be moved forever,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />You <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 1:6</char></note>covered it with the deep as <char style="it">with</char> a garment;</para>
	<para style="q2">The waters stood above the mountains.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />At Your rebuke they fled;</para>
	<para style="q2">At the voice of Your thunder they hastened away.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />They went up over the mountains;</para>
	<para style="q2">They went down into the valleys,</para>
	<para style="q2">To the place which You founded for them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />You have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 26:10; Ps. 33:7; (Jer. 5:22)</char></note>set a boundary that they may not pass over,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 9:11–15</char></note>That they may not return to cover the earth.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />He sends the springs into the valleys;</para>
	<para style="q2">They flow among the hills.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />They give drink to every beast of the field;</para>
	<para style="q2">The wild donkeys quench their thirst.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />By them the birds of the heavens have their home;</para>
	<para style="q2">They sing among the branches.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 147:8</char></note>He waters the hills from His upper chambers;</para>
	<para style="q2">The earth is satisfied with <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 10:13</char></note>the fruit of Your works.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 1:29</char></note>He causes the grass to grow for the cattle,</para>
	<para style="q2">And vegetation for the service of man,</para>
	<para style="q2">That he may bring forth <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 28:5</char></note>food from the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Judg. 9:13; Ps. 23:5; Prov. 31:6; Eccl. 10:19</char></note>wine <char style="it">that</char> makes glad the heart of man,</para>
	<para style="q2">Oil to make <char style="it">his</char> face shine,</para>
	<para style="q2">And bread <char style="it">which</char> strengthens man’s heart.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />The trees of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> are full <char style="it">of</char> <char style="it">sap,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">The cedars of Lebanon which He planted,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />Where the birds make their nests;</para>
	<para style="q2">The stork has her home in the fir trees.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />The high hills <char style="it">are</char> for the wild goats;</para>
	<para style="q2">The cliffs are a refuge for the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 11:5</char></note>rock badgers.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 1:14</char></note>He appointed the moon for seasons;</para>
	<para style="q2">The <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 38:12; Ps. 19:6</char></note>sun knows its going down.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 74:16; Is. 45:7)</char></note>You make darkness, and it is night,</para>
	<para style="q2">In which all the beasts of the forest creep about.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 38:39</char></note>The young lions roar after their prey,</para>
	<para style="q2">And seek their food from God.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" /><char style="it">When</char> the sun rises, they gather together</para>
	<para style="q2">And lie down in their dens.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" />Man goes out to <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 3:19</char></note>his work</para>
	<para style="q2">And to his labor until the evening.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="24" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 40:5; Prov. 3:19; (Jer. 10:12); 51:15</char></note>O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, how manifold are Your works!</para>
	<para style="q2">In wisdom You have made them all.</para>
	<para style="q2">The earth is full of Your <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 65:9</char></note>possessions—</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="25" style="v" />This great and wide sea,</para>
	<para style="q2">In which <char style="it">are</char> innumerable teeming things,</para>
	<para style="q2">Living things both small and great.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="26" style="v" />There the ships sail about;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">There</char> <char style="it">is</char> that <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 41:1; Is. 27:1</char></note>Leviathan</para>
	<para style="q2">Which You have made to play there.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="27" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 36:31; Ps. 136:25</char></note>These all wait for You,</para>
	<para style="q2">That You may give <char style="it">them</char> their food in due season.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="28" style="v" /><char style="it">What</char> You give them they gather in;</para>
	<para style="q2">You open Your hand, they are filled with good.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="29" style="v" />You hide Your face, they are troubled;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 34:15; (Eccl. 12:7)</char></note>You take away their breath, they die and return to their dust.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="30" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 32:15</char></note>You send forth Your Spirit, they are created;</para>
	<para style="q2">And You renew the face of the earth.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="31" style="v" />May the glory of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> endure forever;</para>
	<para style="q2">May the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 1:31; Prov. 8:31</char></note>rejoice in His works.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="32" style="v" />He looks on the earth, and it <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Hab. 3:10</char></note>trembles;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 19:18; Ps. 144:5</char></note>He touches the hills, and they smoke.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="33" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 63:4</char></note>I will sing to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> as long as I live;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will sing praise to my God while I have my being.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="34" style="v" />May my <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 19:14</char></note>meditation be sweet to Him;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will be glad in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="35" style="v" />May <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:38</char></note>sinners be consumed from the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the wicked be no more.</para>
	<para style="q1">Bless the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, O my soul!</para>
	<para style="q2">Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<chapter number="105" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Eternal Faithfulness of the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Oh, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 16:8–22, 34; Ps. 106:1; Is. 12:4</char></note>give thanks to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q2">Call upon His name;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 145:12</char></note>Make known His deeds among the peoples!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Sing to Him, sing psalms to Him;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:27</char></note>Talk of all His wondrous works!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Glory in His holy name;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let the hearts of those rejoice who seek the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Seek the <char style="sc">Lord</char> and His strength;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 27:8</char></note>Seek His face evermore!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 77:11</char></note>Remember His marvelous works which He has done,</para>
	<para style="q2">His wonders, and the judgments of His mouth,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />O seed of Abraham His servant,</para>
	<para style="q2">You children of Jacob, His chosen ones!</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />He <char style="it">is</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char> our God;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 26:9)</char></note>His judgments <char style="it">are</char> in all the earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />He <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Luke 1:72</char></note>remembers His covenant forever,</para>
	<para style="q2">The word <char style="it">which</char> He commanded, for a thousand generations,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 17:2; Luke 1:73; (Gal. 3:17); Heb. 6:17</char></note><char style="it">The</char> <char style="it">covenant</char> which He made with Abraham,</para>
	<para style="q2">And His oath to Isaac,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />And confirmed it to Jacob for a statute,</para>
	<para style="q2">To Israel <char style="it">as</char> an everlasting covenant,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />Saying, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 13:15; 15:18</char></note>“To you I will give the land of Canaan</para>
	<para style="q2">As the allotment of your inheritance,”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 34:30; (Deut. 7:7)</char></note>When they were few in number,</para>
	<para style="q2">Indeed very few, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 23:4; Heb. 11:9</char></note>and strangers in it.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" />When they went from one nation to another,</para>
	<para style="q2">From <char style="it">one</char> kingdom to another people,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 35:5</char></note>He permitted no one to do them wrong;</para>
	<para style="q2">Yes, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 12:17</char></note>He rebuked kings for their sakes,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" /><char style="it">Saying,</char> “Do not touch My anointed ones,</para>
	<para style="q2">And do My prophets no harm.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" />Moreover <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 41:54</char></note>He called for a famine in the land;</para>
	<para style="q2">He destroyed all the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 26:26; Is. 3:1; Ezek. 4:16</char></note>provision of bread.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Gen. 45:5)</char></note>He sent a man before them—</para>
	<para style="q2">Joseph—<char style="it">who</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 37:28, 36; Acts 7:9</char></note>was sold as a slave.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 40:15</char></note>They hurt his feet with fetters,</para>
	<para style="q2">He was laid in irons.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />Until the time that his word came to pass,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 39:11–21; 41:25, 42, 43</char></note>The word of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> tested him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 41:14</char></note>The king sent and released him,</para>
	<para style="q2">The ruler of the people let him go free.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 41:40–44</char></note>He made him lord of his house,</para>
	<para style="q2">And ruler of all his possessions,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" />To bind his princes at his pleasure,</para>
	<para style="q2">And teach his elders wisdom.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="23" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 46:6; Acts 7:15</char></note>Israel also came into Egypt,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Jacob dwelt <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 78:51</char></note>in the land of Ham.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 1:7, 9</char></note>He increased His people greatly,</para>
	<para style="q2">And made them stronger than their enemies.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="25" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 1:8–10; 4:21</char></note>He turned their heart to hate His people,</para>
	<para style="q2">To deal craftily with His servants.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="26" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 3:10; 4:12–15</char></note>He sent Moses His servant,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> Aaron whom He had chosen.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="27" style="v" />They <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 7—12; Ps. 78:43</char></note>performed His signs among them,</para>
	<para style="q2">And wonders in the land of Ham.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="28" style="v" />He sent darkness, and made <char style="it">it</char> dark;</para>
	<para style="q2">And they did not rebel against His word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="29" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 7:20, 21; Ps. 78:44</char></note>He turned their waters into blood,</para>
	<para style="q2">And killed their fish.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="30" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 8:6</char></note>Their land abounded with frogs,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Even</char> in the chambers of their kings.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="31" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 8:16, 17</char></note>He spoke, and there came swarms of flies,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> lice in all their territory.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="32" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 9:23–25</char></note>He gave them hail for rain,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> flaming fire in their land.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="33" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 78:47</char></note>He struck their vines also, and their fig trees,</para>
	<para style="q2">And splintered the trees of their territory.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="34" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 10:4</char></note>He spoke, and locusts came,</para>
	<para style="q2">Young locusts without number,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="35" style="v" />And ate up all the vegetation in their land,</para>
	<para style="q2">And devoured the fruit of their ground.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="36" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 12:29; 13:15; Ps. 135:8; 136:10</char></note>He also destroyed all the firstborn in their land,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 49:3</char></note>The first of all their strength.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="37" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 12:35, 36</char></note>He also brought them out with silver and gold,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">was</char> none feeble among His tribes.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="38" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 12:33</char></note>Egypt was glad when they departed,</para>
	<para style="q2">For the fear of them had fallen upon them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="39" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 13:21; Neh. 9:12; Ps. 78:14; Is. 4:5</char></note>He spread a cloud for a covering,</para>
	<para style="q2">And fire to give light in the night.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="40" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 16:12</char></note><char style="it">The</char> <char style="it">people</char> asked, and He brought quail,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 78:24</char></note>satisfied them with the bread of heaven.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="41" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 17:6; Num. 20:11; Ps. 78:15; 114:8; Is. 48:21; (1 Cor. 10:4)</char></note>He opened the rock, and water gushed out;</para>
	<para style="q2">It ran in the dry places <char style="it">like</char> a river.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="42" style="v" />For He remembered <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 15:13, 14; Ps. 105:8</char></note>His holy promise,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> Abraham His servant.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="43" style="v" />He brought out His people with joy,</para>
	<para style="q2">His chosen ones with gladness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="44" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Josh. 11:16–23; 13:7; Ps. 78:55</char></note>He gave them the lands of the Gentiles,</para>
	<para style="q2">And they inherited the labor of the nations,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="45" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 4:1, 40)</char></note>That they might observe His statutes</para>
	<para style="q2">And keep His laws.</para>
	<para style="q1">Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<chapter number="106" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Joy in Forgiveness of Israel’s Sins</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q1"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 16:34, 41</char></note>Oh, give thanks to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, for <char style="it">He</char> <char style="it">is</char> good!</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" />Who can utter the mighty acts of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>?</para>
	<para style="q2">Who can declare all His praise?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Blessed <char style="it">are</char> those who keep justice,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> he who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 15:2</char></note>does righteousness at <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Gal. 6:9)</char></note>all times!</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:132</char></note>Remember me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, with the favor <char style="it">You</char> <char style="it">have</char> <char style="it">toward</char> Your people.</para>
	<para style="q2">Oh, visit me with Your salvation,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />That I may see the benefit of Your chosen ones,</para>
	<para style="q2">That I may rejoice in the gladness of Your nation,</para>
	<para style="q2">That I may glory with Your inheritance.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 8:47; (Ezra 9:7; Neh. 1:7; Jer. 3:25; Dan. 9:5)</char></note>We have sinned with our fathers,</para>
	<para style="q2">We have committed iniquity,</para>
	<para style="q2">We have done wickedly.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Our fathers in Egypt did not understand Your wonders;</para>
	<para style="q2">They did not remember the multitude of Your mercies,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 14:11, 12</char></note>But rebelled by the sea—the Red Sea.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />Nevertheless He saved them for His name’s sake,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 9:16</char></note>That He might make His mighty power known.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 14:21; Ps. 18:15; Is. 51:10; Nah. 1:4</char></note>He rebuked the Red Sea also, and it dried up;</para>
	<para style="q2">So <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 63:11–13</char></note>He led them through the depths,</para>
	<para style="q2">As through the wilderness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />He <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 14:30</char></note>saved them from the hand of him who hated <char style="it">them,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">And redeemed them from the hand of the enemy.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 14:27, 28; 15:5</char></note>The waters covered their enemies;</para>
	<para style="q2">There was not one of them left.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 15:1–21</char></note>Then they believed His words;</para>
	<para style="q2">They sang His praise.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 15:24; 16:2; 17:2</char></note>They soon forgot His works;</para>
	<para style="q2">They did not wait for His counsel,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 11:4; 1 Cor. 10:6</char></note>But lusted exceedingly in the wilderness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And tested God in the desert.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 11:31</char></note>And He gave them their request,</para>
	<para style="q2">But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 10:16</char></note>sent leanness into their soul.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" />When <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 16:1–3</char></note>they envied Moses in the camp,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> Aaron the saint of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 16:31, 32; Deut. 11:6</char></note>The earth opened up and swallowed Dathan,</para>
	<para style="q2">And covered the faction of Abiram.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 16:35, 46</char></note>A fire was kindled in their company;</para>
	<para style="q2">The flame burned up the wicked.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 32:1–4; Deut. 9:8; Acts 7:41</char></note>They made a calf in Horeb,</para>
	<para style="q2">And worshiped the molded image.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />Thus <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 2:11; Rom. 1:23</char></note>they changed their glory</para>
	<para style="q2">Into the image of an ox that eats grass.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />They forgot God their Savior,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who had done great things in Egypt,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" />Wondrous works in the land of Ham,</para>
	<para style="q2">Awesome things by the Red Sea.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 32:10; Deut. 9:19</char></note>Therefore He said that He would destroy them,</para>
	<para style="q2">Had not Moses His chosen one <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ezek. 22:30</char></note>stood before Him in the breach,</para>
	<para style="q2">To turn away His wrath, lest He destroy <char style="it">them.</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="24" style="v" />Then they despised <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 8:7; Jer. 3:19; Ezek. 20:6</char></note>the pleasant land;</para>
	<para style="q2">They <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 1:32; 9:23; (Heb. 3:18, 19)</char></note>did not believe His word,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="25" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 14:2, 27; Deut. 1:27</char></note>But complained in their tents,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> did not heed the voice of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="26" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ezek. 20:15, 16; (Heb. 3:11, 18)</char></note>Therefore He raised His hand <char style="it">in</char> <char style="it">an</char> <char style="it">oath</char> against them,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 14:28–30</char></note>To overthrow them in the wilderness,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="27" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 26:33; Ezek. 20:23</char></note>To overthrow their descendants among the nations,</para>
	<para style="q2">And to scatter them in the lands.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="28" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 25:3; Deut. 4:3; Hos. 9:10</char></note>They joined themselves also to Baal of Peor,</para>
	<para style="q2">And ate sacrifices made to the dead.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="29" style="v" />Thus they provoked <char style="it">Him</char> to anger with their deeds,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the plague broke out among them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="30" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 25:7, 8</char></note>Then Phinehas stood up and intervened,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the plague was stopped.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="31" style="v" />And that was accounted to him <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 15:6; Num. 25:11–13</char></note>for righteousness</para>
	<para style="q2">To all generations forevermore.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="32" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 20:3–13; Ps. 81:7</char></note>They angered <char style="it">Him</char> also at the waters of strife,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 1:37; 3:26</char></note>So that it went ill with Moses on account of them;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="33" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 20:3, 10</char></note>Because they rebelled against His Spirit,</para>
	<para style="q2">So that he spoke rashly with his lips.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="34" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Judg. 1:21</char></note>They did not destroy the peoples,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 7:2, 16); Judg. 2:2</char></note>Concerning whom the <char style="sc">Lord</char> had commanded them,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="35" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Judg. 3:5, 6</char></note>But they mingled with the Gentiles</para>
	<para style="q2">And learned their works;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="36" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Judg. 2:12</char></note>They served their idols,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 7:16</char></note>Which became a snare to them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="37" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 12:31; 32:17, 18); 2 Kin. 16:3; 17:17; Ezek. 16:20, 21; (1 Cor. 10:20)</char></note>They even sacrificed their sons</para>
	<para style="q2">And their daughters to <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Lev. 17:7)</char></note>demons,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="38" style="v" />And shed innocent blood,</para>
	<para style="q2">The blood of their sons and daughters,</para>
	<para style="q2">Whom they sacrificed to the idols of Canaan;</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Num. 35:33; Is. 24:5; Jer. 3:1, 2)</char></note>the land was polluted with blood.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="39" style="v" />Thus they were <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Lev. 18:24); Ezek. 20:18</char></note>defiled by their own works,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Lev. 17:7; Num. 15:39); Judg. 2:17; Hos. 4:12</char></note>played the harlot by their own deeds.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="40" style="v" />Therefore <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Judg. 2:14; Ps. 78:59</char></note>the wrath of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> was kindled against His people,</para>
	<para style="q2">So that He abhorred <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 9:29; 32:9)</char></note>His own inheritance.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="41" style="v" />And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Judg. 2:14; (Neh. 9:27)</char></note>He gave them into the hand of the Gentiles,</para>
	<para style="q2">And those who hated them ruled over them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="42" style="v" />Their enemies also oppressed them,</para>
	<para style="q2">And they were brought into subjection under their hand.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="43" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Judg. 2:16; (Neh. 9:27)</char></note>Many times He delivered them;</para>
	<para style="q2">But they rebelled in their counsel,</para>
	<para style="q2">And were brought low for their iniquity.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="44" style="v" />Nevertheless He regarded their affliction,</para>
	<para style="q2">When <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Judg. 3:9; 6:7; 10:10</char></note>He heard their cry;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="45" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Lev. 26:41, 42)</char></note>And for their sake He remembered His covenant,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Judg. 2:18</char></note>relented <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 69:16</char></note>according to the multitude of His mercies.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="46" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 8:50; (2 Chr. 30:9); Ezra 9:9; Neh. 1:11; Jer. 42:12</char></note>He also made them to be pitied</para>
	<para style="q2">By all those who carried them away captive.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="47" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 16:35, 36</char></note>Save us, O <char style="sc">Lord</char> our God,</para>
	<para style="q2">And gather us from among the Gentiles,</para>
	<para style="q2">To give thanks to Your holy name,</para>
	<para style="q2">To triumph in Your praise.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="48" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 41:13</char></note>Blessed <char style="it">be</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char> God of Israel</para>
	<para style="q2">From everlasting to everlasting!</para>
	<para style="q2">And let all the people say, “Amen!”</para>
	<para style="q1">Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<chapter number="107" style="c" />
	<para style="s">BOOK FIVE: Psalms 107—150</para>
	<para style="s">Thanksgiving to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> for His Great Works of Deliverance</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Oh, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 16:34; Ps. 106:1; Jer. 33:11</char></note>give thanks to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, for <char style="it">He</char> <char style="it">is</char> good!</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Let the redeemed of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> say <char style="it">so,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Whom He has redeemed from the hand of the enemy,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 43:5, 6; Jer. 29:14; 31:8–10; (Ezek. 39:27, 28)</char></note>gathered out of the lands,</para>
	<para style="q2">From the east and from the west,</para>
	<para style="q2">From the north and from the south.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />They wandered in <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 14:33; 32:13; (Deut. 2:7; 32:10); Josh. 5:6; 14:10</char></note>the wilderness in a desolate way;</para>
	<para style="q2">They found no city to dwell in.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Hungry and thirsty,</para>
	<para style="q2">Their soul fainted in them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 50:15; (Hos. 5:15)</char></note>Then they cried out to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> in their trouble,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> He delivered them out of their distresses.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />And He led them forth by the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ezra 8:21; Ps. 5:8; Jer. 31:9</char></note>right way,</para>
	<para style="q2">That they might go to a city for a dwelling place.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 107:15, 21</char></note>Oh, that <char style="it">men</char> would give thanks to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">for</char> His goodness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">for</char> His wonderful works to the children of men!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 34:10; Luke 1:53)</char></note>He satisfies the longing soul,</para>
	<para style="q2">And fills the hungry soul with goodness.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />Those who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 42:7; Mic. 7:8; Luke 1:79)</char></note>sat in darkness and in the shadow of death,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 36:8</char></note>Bound in affliction and irons—</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />Because they <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lam. 3:42</char></note>rebelled against the words of God,</para>
	<para style="q2">And despised <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 73:24)</char></note>the counsel of the Most High,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />Therefore He brought down their heart with labor;</para>
	<para style="q2">They fell down, and <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">was</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 22:11</char></note>none to help.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />Then they cried out to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> in their trouble,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> He saved them out of their distresses.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 68:6</char></note>He brought them out of darkness and the shadow of death,</para>
	<para style="q2">And broke their chains in pieces.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />Oh, that <char style="it">men</char> would give thanks to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">for</char> His goodness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">for</char> His wonderful works to the children of men!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />For He has <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 45:1, 2</char></note>broken the gates of bronze,</para>
	<para style="q2">And cut the bars of iron in two.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="17" style="v" />Fools, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 65:6, 7; Jer. 30:14, 15); Lam. 3:39; Ezek. 24:23</char></note>because of their transgression,</para>
	<para style="q2">And because of their iniquities, were afflicted.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 33:20</char></note>Their soul abhorred all manner of food,</para>
	<para style="q2">And they <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 33:22</char></note>drew near to the gates of death.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />Then they cried out to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> in their trouble,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> He saved them out of their distresses.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 8:8</char></note>He sent His word and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Kin. 20:5; Ps. 30:2</char></note>healed them,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 33:28, 30</char></note>delivered <char style="it">them</char> from their destructions.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />Oh, that <char style="it">men</char> would give thanks to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">for</char> His goodness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">for</char> His wonderful works to the children of men!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 7:12; Ps. 50:14; Heb. 13:15</char></note>Let them sacrifice the sacrifices of thanksgiving,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 9:11</char></note>declare His works with rejoicing.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="23" style="v" />Those who go down to the sea in ships,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who do business on great waters,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" />They see the works of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And His wonders in the deep.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="25" style="v" />For He commands and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jon. 1:4</char></note>raises the stormy wind,</para>
	<para style="q2">Which lifts up the waves of the sea.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="26" style="v" />They mount up to the heavens,</para>
	<para style="q2">They go down again to the depths;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 22:14</char></note>Their soul melts because of trouble.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="27" style="v" />They reel to and fro, and stagger like a drunken man,</para>
	<para style="q2">And are at their wits’ end.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="28" style="v" />Then they cry out to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> in their trouble,</para>
	<para style="q2">And He brings them out of their distresses.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="29" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 89:9; Matt. 8:26; Luke 8:24</char></note>He calms the storm,</para>
	<para style="q2">So that its waves are still.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="30" style="v" />Then they are glad because they are quiet;</para>
	<para style="q2">So He guides them to their desired haven.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="31" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 107:8, 15, 21</char></note>Oh, that <char style="it">men</char> would give thanks to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">for</char> His goodness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">for</char> His wonderful works to the children of men!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="32" style="v" />Let them exalt Him also <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 22:22, 25</char></note>in the assembly of the people,</para>
	<para style="q2">And praise Him in the company of the elders.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="33" style="v" />He <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 17:1, 7; Is. 50:2</char></note>turns rivers into a wilderness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the watersprings into dry ground;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="34" style="v" />A <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 13:10; Deut. 29:23</char></note>fruitful land into barrenness,</para>
	<para style="q2">For the wickedness of those who dwell in it.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="35" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 114:8; (Is. 41:17, 18)</char></note>He turns a wilderness into pools of water,</para>
	<para style="q2">And dry land into watersprings.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="36" style="v" />There He makes the hungry dwell,</para>
	<para style="q2">That they may establish a city for a dwelling place,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="37" style="v" />And sow fields and plant vineyards,</para>
	<para style="q2">That they may yield a fruitful harvest.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="38" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 12:2; 17:16, 20</char></note>He also blesses them, and they multiply greatly;</para>
	<para style="q2">And He does not let their cattle <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 1:7; (Deut. 7:14)</char></note>decrease.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="39" style="v" />When they are <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Kin. 10:32</char></note>diminished and brought low</para>
	<para style="q2">Through oppression, affliction, and sorrow,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="40" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 12:21, 24</char></note>He pours contempt on princes,</para>
	<para style="q2">And causes them to wander in the wilderness <char style="it">where</char> <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> no way;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="41" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 2:8; (Ps. 113:7, 8)</char></note>Yet He sets the poor on high, far from affliction,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 78:52</char></note>makes <char style="it">their</char> families like a flock.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="42" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 5:15, 16</char></note>The righteous see <char style="it">it</char> and rejoice,</para>
	<para style="q2">And all <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 5:16; Ps. 63:11; (Rom. 3:19)</char></note>iniquity stops its mouth.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="43" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 64:9; Jer. 9:12; (Hos. 14:9)</char></note>Whoever <char style="it">is</char> wise will observe these <char style="it">things,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">And they will understand the lovingkindness of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<chapter number="108" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Assurance of God’s Victory over Enemies</para>
	<para style="d">A Song. A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />O <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 57:7–11</char></note>God, my heart is steadfast;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will sing and give praise, even with my glory.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 57:8–11</char></note>Awake, lute and harp!</para>
	<para style="q2">I will awaken the dawn.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />I will praise You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, among the peoples,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I will sing praises to You among the nations.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />For Your mercy <char style="it">is</char> great above the heavens,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Your truth <char style="it">reaches</char> to the clouds.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 57:5, 11</char></note>Be exalted, O God, above the heavens,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Your glory above all the earth;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 60:5–12</char></note>That Your beloved may be delivered,</para>
	<para style="q2">Save <char style="it">with</char> Your right hand, and hear me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />God has spoken in His holiness:</para>
	<para style="q2">“I will rejoice;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will divide Shechem</para>
	<para style="q2">And measure out the Valley of Succoth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Gilead <char style="it">is</char> Mine; Manasseh <char style="it">is</char> Mine;</para>
	<para style="q2">Ephraim also <char style="it">is</char> the helmet for My head;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Gen. 49:10)</char></note>Judah <char style="it">is</char> My lawgiver.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />Moab <char style="it">is</char> My washpot;</para>
	<para style="q2">Over Edom I will cast My shoe;</para>
	<para style="q2">Over Philistia I will triumph.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 60:9</char></note>Who will bring me <char style="it">into</char> the strong city?</para>
	<para style="q2">Who will lead me to Edom?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><char style="it">Is</char> <char style="it">it</char> not <char style="it">You,</char> O God, <char style="it">who</char> cast us off?</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">You,</char> O God, <char style="it">who</char> did not go out with our armies?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />Give us help from trouble,</para>
	<para style="q2">For the help of man is useless.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 60:12</char></note>Through God we will do valiantly,</para>
	<para style="q2">For <char style="it">it</char> <char style="it">is</char> He <char style="it">who</char> shall tread down our enemies.</para>
	<chapter number="109" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Plea for Judgment of False Accusers</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Do<note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 83:1</char></note> not keep silent,</para>
	<para style="q2">O God of my praise!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />For the mouth of the wicked and the mouth of the deceitful</para>
	<para style="q2">Have opened against me;</para>
	<para style="q2">They have spoken against me with a <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 27:12</char></note>lying tongue.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />They have also surrounded me with words of hatred,</para>
	<para style="q2">And fought against me <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:7; 69:4; John 15:25</char></note>without a cause.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />In return for my love they are my accusers,</para>
	<para style="q2">But I <char style="it">give</char> <char style="it">myself</char> <char style="it">to</char> prayer.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Thus <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:7, 12; 38:20; Prov. 17:13</char></note>they have rewarded me evil for good,</para>
	<para style="q2">And hatred for my love.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />Set a wicked man over him,</para>
	<para style="q2">And let <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Zech. 3:1</char></note>an accuser stand at his right hand.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />When he is judged, let him be found guilty,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Prov. 28:9)</char></note>let his prayer become sin.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Let his days be <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 55:23); John 17:12</char></note>few,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 69:25; Acts 1:20</char></note>let another take his office.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 22:24</char></note>Let his children be fatherless,</para>
	<para style="q2">And his wife a widow.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />Let his children continually be vagabonds, and beg;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let them seek <char style="it">their</char> <char style="it">bread</char> also from their desolate places.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Neh. 5:7; Job 5:5; 18:9</char></note>Let the creditor seize all that he has,</para>
	<para style="q2">And let strangers plunder his labor.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />Let there be none to extend mercy to him,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor let there be any to favor his fatherless children.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 18:19; Ps. 37:28</char></note>Let his posterity be cut off,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> in the generation following let their <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:7</char></note>name be blotted out.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 20:5; Num. 14:18); Is. 65:6; (Jer. 32:18)</char></note>Let the iniquity of his fathers be remembered before the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And let not the sin of his mother <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Neh. 4:5; Jer. 18:23</char></note>be blotted out.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />Let them be continually before the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">That He may <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 18:17; (Ps. 34:16)</char></note>cut off the memory of them from the earth;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />Because he did not remember to show mercy,</para>
	<para style="q2">But persecuted the poor and needy man,</para>
	<para style="q2">That he might even slay the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 34:18)</char></note>broken in heart.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 14:14; (Matt. 7:2)</char></note>As he loved cursing, so let it come to him;</para>
	<para style="q2">As he did not delight in blessing, so let it be far from him.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />As he clothed himself with cursing as with his garment,</para>
	<para style="q2">So let it <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 5:22</char></note>enter his body like water,</para>
	<para style="q2">And like oil into his bones.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />Let it be to him like the garment which covers him,</para>
	<para style="q2">And for a belt with which he girds himself continually.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" /><char style="it">Let</char> this <char style="it">be</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char>’s reward to my accusers,</para>
	<para style="q2">And to those who speak evil against my person.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="21" style="v" />But You, O G<char style="sc">OD</char> the Lord,</para>
	<para style="q2">Deal with me for Your name’s sake;</para>
	<para style="q2">Because Your mercy <char style="it">is</char> good, deliver me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" />For I <char style="it">am</char> poor and needy,</para>
	<para style="q2">And my heart is wounded within me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" />I am gone <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 102:11</char></note>like a shadow when it lengthens;</para>
	<para style="q2">I am shaken off like a locust.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" />My <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Heb. 12:12</char></note>knees are weak through fasting,</para>
	<para style="q2">And my flesh is feeble from lack of fatness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="25" style="v" />I also have become <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 22:7; Jer. 18:16; Lam. 2:15</char></note>a reproach to them;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">When</char> they look at me, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 27:39; Mark 15:29</char></note>they shake their heads.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="26" style="v" />Help me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char> my God!</para>
	<para style="q2">Oh, save me according to Your mercy,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="27" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 37:7</char></note>That they may know that this <char style="it">is</char> Your hand—</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">That</char> You, <char style="sc">Lord</char>, have done it!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="28" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 6:11, 12</char></note>Let them curse, but You bless;</para>
	<para style="q2">When they arise, let them be ashamed,</para>
	<para style="q2">But let <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 65:14</char></note>Your servant rejoice.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="29" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 8:22; Ps. 35:26</char></note>Let my accusers be clothed with shame,</para>
	<para style="q2">And let them cover themselves with their own disgrace as with a mantle.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="30" style="v" />I will greatly praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char> with my mouth;</para>
	<para style="q2">Yes, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:18; 111:1</char></note>I will praise Him among the multitude.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="31" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 16:8)</char></note>He shall stand at the right hand of the poor,</para>
	<para style="q2">To save <char style="it">him</char> from those who condemn him.</para>
	<chapter number="110" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Announcement of the Messiah’s Reign</para>
	<para style="d">A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />The <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 22:44; Mark 12:36; 16:19; Luke 20:42, 43; Acts 2:34, 35; Col. 3:1; Heb. 1:13</char></note><char style="sc">Lord</char> said to my Lord,</para>
	<para style="q2">“Sit at My right hand,</para>
	<para style="q2">Till I make Your enemies Your <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Cor. 15:25; Eph. 1:22)</char></note>footstool.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> shall send the rod of Your strength <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Rom. 11:26, 27)</char></note>out of Zion.</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 2:9; Dan. 7:13, 14)</char></note>Rule in the midst of Your enemies!</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Judg. 5:2; Neh. 11:2</char></note>Your people <char style="it">shall</char> <char style="it">be</char> volunteers</para>
	<para style="q2">In the day of Your power;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 16:29; Ps. 96:9</char></note>In the beauties of holiness, from the womb of the morning,</para>
	<para style="q2">You have the dew of Your youth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> has sworn</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Num. 23:19)</char></note>will not relent,</para>
	<para style="q2">“You <char style="it">are</char> a <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Zech. 6:13)</char></note>priest forever</para>
	<para style="q2">According to the order of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Heb. 5:6, 10; 6:20)</char></note>Melchizedek.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />The Lord <char style="it">is</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 16:8)</char></note>at Your right hand;</para>
	<para style="q2">He shall execute kings <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 2:5, 12; (Rom. 2:5; Rev. 6:17)</char></note>in the day of His wrath.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />He shall judge among the nations,</para>
	<para style="q2">He shall fill <char style="it">the</char> <char style="it">places</char> with dead bodies,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 68:21</char></note>He shall execute the heads of many countries.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />He shall drink of the brook by the wayside;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 53:12)</char></note>Therefore He shall lift up the head.</para>
	<chapter number="111" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Praise to God for His Faithfulness and Justice</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q1"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:18</char></note>I will praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char> with <char style="it">my</char> whole heart,</para>
	<para style="q2">In the assembly of the upright and <char style="it">in</char> the congregation.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 92:5</char></note>The works of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">are</char> great,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 143:5</char></note>Studied by all who have pleasure in them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />His work <char style="it">is</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 145:4, 5</char></note>honorable and glorious,</para>
	<para style="q2">And His righteousness endures forever.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />He has made His wonderful works to be remembered;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 86:5)</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> gracious and full of compassion.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />He has given food to those who fear Him;</para>
	<para style="q2">He will ever be mindful of His covenant.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />He has declared to His people the power of His works,</para>
	<para style="q2">In giving them the heritage of the nations.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />The works of His hands <char style="it">are</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Rev. 15:3)</char></note>verity and justice;</para>
	<para style="q2">All His precepts <char style="it">are</char> sure.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 40:8; Matt. 5:18</char></note>They stand fast forever and ever,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> <char style="it">are</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Rev. 15:3)</char></note>done in truth and uprightness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Luke 1:68</char></note>He has sent redemption to His people;</para>
	<para style="q2">He has commanded His covenant forever:</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Luke 1:49</char></note>Holy and awesome <char style="it">is</char> His name.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 28:28; (Prov. 1:7; 9:10); Eccl. 12:13</char></note>The fear of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> the beginning of wisdom;</para>
	<para style="q2">A good understanding have all those who do <char style="it">His</char> <char style="it">commandments.</char></para>
	<para style="q2">His praise endures forever.</para>
	<chapter number="112" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Blessed State of the Righteous</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q1">Blessed <char style="it">is</char> the man <char style="it">who</char> fears the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Who</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 128:1</char></note>delights greatly in His commandments.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 102:28)</char></note>His descendants will be mighty on earth;</para>
	<para style="q2">The generation of the upright will be blessed.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 3:16; 8:18; (Matt. 6:33)</char></note>Wealth and riches <char style="it">will</char> <char style="it">be</char> in his house,</para>
	<para style="q2">And his righteousness endures forever.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 11:17; Ps. 97:11</char></note>Unto the upright there arises light in the darkness;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">He</char> <char style="it">is</char> gracious, and full of compassion, and righteous.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:26; (Luke 6:35)</char></note>A good man deals graciously and lends;</para>
	<para style="q2">He will guide his affairs <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Eph. 5:15; Col. 4:5)</char></note>with discretion.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Surely he will never be shaken;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 10:7</char></note>The righteous will be in everlasting remembrance.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Prov. 1:33)</char></note>He will not be afraid of evil tidings;</para>
	<para style="q2">His heart is steadfast, trusting in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />His <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Heb. 13:9</char></note>heart <char style="it">is</char> established;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 27:1; 56:11); Prov. 1:33; 3:24; (Is. 12:2)</char></note>He will not be afraid,</para>
	<para style="q2">Until he <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 59:10</char></note>sees <char style="it">his</char> <char style="it">desire</char> upon his enemies.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />He has dispersed abroad,</para>
	<para style="q2">He has given to the poor;</para>
	<para style="q2">His righteousness endures forever;</para>
	<para style="q2">His horn will be exalted with honor.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />The wicked will see <char style="it">it</char> and be grieved;</para>
	<para style="q2">He will gnash his teeth and melt away;</para>
	<para style="q2">The desire of the wicked shall perish.</para>
	<chapter number="113" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Majesty and Condescension of God</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q1"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 135:1</char></note>Praise, O servants of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Praise the name of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Dan. 2:20)</char></note>Blessed be the name of the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="q2">From this time forth and forevermore!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 59:19; Mal. 1:11</char></note>From the rising of the sun to its going down</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char>’s name <char style="it">is</char> to be praised.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 97:9; 99:2</char></note>high above all nations,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 8:1)</char></note>His glory above the heavens.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 89:6; (Is. 57:15)</char></note>Who <char style="it">is</char> like the <char style="sc">Lord</char> our God,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who dwells on high,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 11:4; Is. 57:15)</char></note>Who humbles Himself to behold</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">The</char> <char style="it">things</char> <char style="it">that</char> <char style="it">are</char> in the heavens and in the earth?</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 2:8; Ps. 107:41</char></note>He raises the poor out of the dust,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> lifts the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 72:12</char></note>needy out of the ash heap,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />That He may <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Job 36:7)</char></note>seat <char style="it">him</char> with princes—</para>
	<para style="q2">With the princes of His people.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 2:5; Is. 54:1</char></note>He grants the barren woman a home,</para>
	<para style="q2">Like a joyful mother of children.</para>
	<para style="q1">Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<chapter number="114" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Power of God in His Deliverance of Israel</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />When <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 12:51; 13:3</char></note>Israel went out of Egypt,</para>
	<para style="q2">The house of Jacob <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 81:5</char></note>from a people of strange language,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 6:7; 19:6; 25:8; 29:45, 46; Deut. 27:9</char></note>Judah became His sanctuary,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> Israel His dominion.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 14:21; Ps. 77:16</char></note>The sea saw <char style="it">it</char> and fled;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Josh. 3:13–16</char></note>Jordan turned back.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 19:18; Judg. 5:5; Ps. 29:6; Hab. 3:6</char></note>The mountains skipped like rams,</para>
	<para style="q2">The little hills like lambs.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Hab. 3:8</char></note>What ails you, O sea, that you fled?</para>
	<para style="q2">O Jordan, <char style="it">that</char> you turned back?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />O mountains, <char style="it">that</char> you skipped like rams?</para>
	<para style="q2">O little hills, like lambs?</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />Tremble, O earth, at the presence of the Lord,</para>
	<para style="q2">At the presence of the God of Jacob,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 17:6; Num. 20:11; Ps. 107:35</char></note>Who turned the rock <char style="it">into</char> a pool of water,</para>
	<para style="q2">The flint into a fountain of waters.</para>
	<chapter number="115" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Futility of Idols and the Trustworthiness of God</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Not <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 48:11); Ezek. 36:32</char></note>unto us, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, not unto us,</para>
	<para style="q2">But to Your name give glory,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because of Your mercy,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because of Your truth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Why should the Gentiles say,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 42:3, 10</char></note>“So where <char style="it">is</char> their God?”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Chr. 16:26)</char></note>But our God <char style="it">is</char> in heaven;</para>
	<para style="q2">He does whatever He pleases.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 4:28; 2 Kin. 19:18; Is. 37:19; 44:10, 20; Jer. 10:3</char></note>Their idols <char style="it">are</char> silver and gold,</para>
	<para style="q2">The work of men’s hands.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />They have mouths, but they do not speak;</para>
	<para style="q2">Eyes they have, but they do not see;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />They have ears, but they do not hear;</para>
	<para style="q2">Noses they have, but they do not smell;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />They have hands, but they do not handle;</para>
	<para style="q2">Feet they have, but they do not walk;</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor do they mutter through their throat.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 135:18; Is. 44:9–11</char></note>Those who make them are like them;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">So</char> <char style="it">is</char> everyone who trusts in them.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 118:2, 3</char></note>O Israel, trust in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 33:20</char></note>He <char style="it">is</char> their help and their shield.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />O house of Aaron, trust in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">He <char style="it">is</char> their help and their shield.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />You who fear the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, trust in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">He <char style="it">is</char> their help and their shield.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> has been mindful of <char style="it">us;</char></para>
	<para style="q2">He will bless us;</para>
	<para style="q2">He will bless the house of Israel;</para>
	<para style="q2">He will bless the house of Aaron.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 128:1, 4</char></note>He will bless those who fear the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Both</char> small and great.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" />May the <char style="sc">Lord</char> give you increase more and more,</para>
	<para style="q2">You and your children.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" /><char style="it">May</char> you <char style="it">be</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Gen. 14:19)</char></note>blessed by the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 1:1; Acts 14:15; Rev. 14:7</char></note>Who made heaven and earth.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" />The heaven, <char style="it">even</char> the heavens, <char style="it">are</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char>’s;</para>
	<para style="q2">But the earth He has given to the children of men.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 6:5; 88:10–12; (Is. 38:18)</char></note>The dead do not praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor any who go down into silence.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 113:2; Dan. 2:20</char></note>But we will bless the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="q2">From this time forth and forevermore.</para>
	<para style="q1">Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<chapter number="116" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Thanksgiving for Deliverance from Death</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />I <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 18:1</char></note>love the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, because He has heard</para>
	<para style="q2">My voice <char style="it">and</char> my supplications.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Because He has inclined His ear to me,</para>
	<para style="q2">Therefore I will call <char style="it">upon</char> <char style="it">Him</char> as long as I live.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 18:4–6</char></note>The pains of death surrounded me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the pangs of Sheol laid hold of me;</para>
	<para style="q2">I found trouble and sorrow.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Then I called upon the name of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>:</para>
	<para style="q2">“O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, I implore You, deliver my soul!”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 103:8)</char></note>Gracious <char style="it">is</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ezra 9:15); Neh. 9:8; (Ps. 119:137; 145:17; Jer. 12:1; Dan. 9:14)</char></note>righteous;</para>
	<para style="q2">Yes, our God <char style="it">is</char> merciful.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> preserves the simple;</para>
	<para style="q2">I was brought low, and He saved me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Return to your <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Jer. 6:16; Matt. 11:29)</char></note>rest, O my soul,</para>
	<para style="q2">For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 13:6</char></note>the <char style="sc">Lord</char> has dealt bountifully with you.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 56:13</char></note>For You have delivered my soul from death,</para>
	<para style="q2">My eyes from tears,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> my feet from falling.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />I will walk before the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 27:13</char></note>In the land of the living.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Cor. 4:13</char></note>I believed, therefore I spoke,</para>
	<para style="q2">“I am greatly afflicted.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 31:22</char></note>I said in my haste,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rom. 3:4</char></note>“All men <char style="it">are</char> liars.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />What shall I render to the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">For</char> all His benefits toward me?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />I will take up the cup of salvation,</para>
	<para style="q2">And call upon the name of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 116:18</char></note>I will pay my vows to the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Now in the presence of all His people.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 72:14; (Rev. 14:13)</char></note>Precious in the sight of the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Is</char> the death of His saints.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="16" style="v" />O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, truly <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:125; 143:12</char></note>I <char style="it">am</char> Your servant;</para>
	<para style="q2">I <char style="it">am</char> Your servant, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 86:16</char></note>the son of Your maidservant;</para>
	<para style="q2">You have loosed my bonds.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />I will offer to You <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 7:12; Ps. 50:14; 107:22</char></note>the sacrifice of thanksgiving,</para>
	<para style="q2">And will call upon the name of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="18" style="v" />I will pay my vows to the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Now in the presence of all His people,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />In the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 96:8</char></note>courts of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>’s house,</para>
	<para style="q2">In the midst of you, O Jerusalem.</para>
	<para style="q1">Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<chapter number="117" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Let All Peoples Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Praise <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rom. 15:11</char></note>the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, all you Gentiles!</para>
	<para style="q2">Laud Him, all you peoples!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />For His merciful kindness is great toward us,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 100:5)</char></note>the truth of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">endures</char> forever.</para>
	<para style="q1">Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<chapter number="118" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Praise to God for His Everlasting Mercy</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Oh, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 16:8, 34; Jer. 33:11</char></note>give thanks to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, for <char style="it">He</char> <char style="it">is</char> good!</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Chr. 5:13; 7:3; Ezra 3:11; (Ps. 136:1–26)</char></note>For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 115:9)</char></note>Let Israel now say,</para>
	<para style="q2">“His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Let the house of Aaron now say,</para>
	<para style="q2">“His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Let those who fear the <char style="sc">Lord</char> now say,</para>
	<para style="q2">“His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 120:1</char></note>I called on the <char style="sc">Lord</char> in distress;</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> answered me <char style="it">and</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 18:19</char></note>set me in a broad place.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 27:1; 56:9; (Rom. 8:31; Heb. 13:6)</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> on my side;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will not fear.</para>
	<para style="q2">What can man do to me?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 54:4</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> is for me among those who help me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Therefore <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 59:10</char></note>I shall see <char style="it">my</char> <char style="it">desire</char> on those who hate me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Chr. 32:7, 8; Ps. 40:4; Is. 31:1, 3; 57:13; Jer. 17:5</char></note><char style="it">It</char> <char style="it">is</char> better to trust in the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Than to put confidence in man.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 146:3</char></note><char style="it">It</char> <char style="it">is</char> better to trust in the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="q2">Than to put confidence in princes.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />All nations surrounded me,</para>
	<para style="q2">But in the name of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> I will destroy them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />They <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 88:17</char></note>surrounded me,</para>
	<para style="q2">Yes, they surrounded me;</para>
	<para style="q2">But in the name of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> I will destroy them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />They surrounded me <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 1:44</char></note>like bees;</para>
	<para style="q2">They were quenched <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Eccl. 7:6; Nah. 1:10</char></note>like a fire of thorns;</para>
	<para style="q2">For in the name of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> I will destroy them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />You pushed me violently, that I might fall,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the <char style="sc">Lord</char> helped me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 15:2; Is. 12:2</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> my strength and song,</para>
	<para style="q2">And He has become my salvation.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" />The voice of rejoicing and salvation</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Is</char> in the tents of the righteous;</para>
	<para style="q2">The right hand of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> does valiantly.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 15:6</char></note>The right hand of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> is exalted;</para>
	<para style="q2">The right hand of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> does valiantly.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 6:5); Hab. 1:12</char></note>I shall not die, but live,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 73:28</char></note>declare the works of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> has <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 73:14; Jer. 31:18; (1 Cor. 11:32); 2 Cor. 6:9</char></note>chastened me severely,</para>
	<para style="q2">But He has not given me over to death.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 26:2</char></note>Open to me the gates of righteousness;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will go through them,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> I will praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 24:7</char></note>This is the gate of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 35:8; (Rev. 21:27; 22:14, 15)</char></note>Through which the righteous shall enter.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="21" style="v" />I will praise You,</para>
	<para style="q2">For You have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 116:1</char></note>answered me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And have become my salvation.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="22" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 21:42; Mark 12:10, 11; Luke 20:17; Acts 4:11; (Eph. 2:20; 1 Pet. 2:7, 8)</char></note>The stone <char style="it">which</char> the builders rejected</para>
	<para style="q2">Has become the chief cornerstone.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" />This was the <char style="sc">Lord</char>’s doing;</para>
	<para style="q2">It <char style="it">is</char> marvelous in our eyes.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" />This <char style="it">is</char> the day the <char style="sc">Lord</char> has made;</para>
	<para style="q2">We will rejoice and be glad in it.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="25" style="v" />Save now, I pray, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, I pray, send now prosperity.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="26" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 21:9; 23:39; Mark 11:9; Luke 13:35; 19:38</char></note>Blessed <char style="it">is</char> he who comes in the name of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q2">We have blessed you from the house of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="27" style="v" />God <char style="it">is</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And He has given us <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Esth. 8:16; (1 Pet. 2:9)</char></note>light;</para>
	<para style="q2">Bind the sacrifice with cords to the horns of the altar.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="28" style="v" />You <char style="it">are</char> my God, and I will praise You;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 15:2; Is. 25:1</char></note><char style="it">You</char> <char style="it">are</char> my God, I will exalt You.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="29" style="v" />Oh, give thanks to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, for <char style="it">He</char> <char style="it">is</char> good!</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever.</para>
	<chapter number="119" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Meditations on the Excellencies of the Word of God</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1488; <char style="sc">Aleph</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Blessed <char style="it">are</char> the undefiled in the way,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 128:1; (Ezek. 11:20; 18:17); Mic. 4:2</char></note>Who walk in the law of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Blessed <char style="it">are</char> those who keep His testimonies,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who seek Him with the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 6:5; 10:12; 11:13; 13:3</char></note>whole heart!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 John 3:9; 5:18)</char></note>They also do no iniquity;</para>
	<para style="q2">They walk in His ways.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />You have commanded <char style="it">us</char></para>
	<para style="q2">To keep Your precepts diligently.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Oh, that my ways were directed</para>
	<para style="q2">To keep Your statutes!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 22:26</char></note>Then I would not be ashamed,</para>
	<para style="q2">When I look into all Your commandments.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />I will praise You with uprightness of heart,</para>
	<para style="q2">When I learn Your righteous judgments.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />I will keep Your statutes;</para>
	<para style="q2">Oh, do not forsake me utterly!</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1489; <char style="sc">Beth</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />How can a young man cleanse his way?</para>
	<para style="q2">By taking heed according to Your word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />With my whole heart I have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Chr. 15:15</char></note>sought You;</para>
	<para style="q2">Oh, let me not wander from Your commandments!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:31; Luke 2:19</char></note>Your word I have hidden in my heart,</para>
	<para style="q2">That I might not sin against You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />Blessed <char style="it">are</char> You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q2">Teach me Your statutes.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />With my lips I have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 34:11</char></note>declared</para>
	<para style="q2">All the judgments of Your mouth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />I have rejoiced in the way of Your testimonies,</para>
	<para style="q2">As <char style="it">much</char> <char style="it">as</char> in all riches.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" />I will meditate on Your precepts,</para>
	<para style="q2">And contemplate Your ways.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />I will <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 1:2</char></note>delight myself in Your statutes;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will not forget Your word.</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1490; <char style="sc">Gimel</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 116:7</char></note>Deal bountifully with Your servant,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">That</char> I may live and keep Your word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />Open my eyes, that I may see</para>
	<para style="q2">Wondrous things from Your law.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 47:9; Lev. 25:23; 1 Chr. 29:15; Ps. 39:12; Heb. 11:13</char></note>I <char style="it">am</char> a stranger in the earth;</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not hide Your commandments from me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 42:1, 2; 63:1; 84:2</char></note>My soul breaks with longing</para>
	<para style="q2">For Your judgments at all times.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />You rebuke the proud—the cursed,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who stray from Your commandments.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 39:8</char></note>Remove from me reproach and contempt,</para>
	<para style="q2">For I have kept Your testimonies.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="23" style="v" />Princes also sit <char style="it">and</char> speak against me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">But</char> Your servant meditates on Your statutes.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" />Your testimonies also <char style="it">are</char> my delight</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> my counselors.</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1491; <char style="sc">Daleth</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="25" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 44:25</char></note>My soul clings to the dust;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 143:11</char></note>Revive me according to Your word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="26" style="v" />I have declared my ways, and You answered me;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 25:4; 27:11; 86:11</char></note>Teach me Your statutes.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="27" style="v" />Make me understand the way of Your precepts;</para>
	<para style="q2">So <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 145:5, 6</char></note>shall I meditate on Your wonderful works.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="28" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 107:26</char></note>My soul melts from heaviness;</para>
	<para style="q2">Strengthen me according to Your word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="29" style="v" />Remove from me the way of lying,</para>
	<para style="q2">And grant me Your law graciously.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="30" style="v" />I have chosen the way of truth;</para>
	<para style="q2">Your judgments I have laid <char style="it">before</char> <char style="it">me.</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="31" style="v" />I cling to Your testimonies;</para>
	<para style="q2">O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, do not put me to shame!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="32" style="v" />I will run the course of Your commandments,</para>
	<para style="q2">For You shall <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 4:29; Is. 60:5; 2 Cor. 6:11, 13</char></note>enlarge my heart.</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1492; <char style="sc">He</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="33" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Matt. 10:22; Rev. 2:26)</char></note>Teach me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, the way of Your statutes,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I shall keep it <char style="it">to</char> the end.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="34" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Prov. 2:6; James 1:5)</char></note>Give me understanding, and I shall keep Your law;</para>
	<para style="q2">Indeed, I shall observe it with <char style="it">my</char> whole heart.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="35" style="v" />Make me walk in the path of Your commandments,</para>
	<para style="q2">For I delight in it.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="36" style="v" />Incline my heart to Your testimonies,</para>
	<para style="q2">And not to <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ezek. 33:31; (Mark 7:20–23); Luke 12:15; (Heb. 13:5)</char></note>covetousness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="37" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 33:15</char></note>Turn away my eyes from <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 23:5</char></note>looking at worthless things,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> revive me in Your way.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="38" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 7:25</char></note>Establish Your word to Your servant,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">devoted</char> to fearing You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="39" style="v" />Turn away my reproach which I dread,</para>
	<para style="q2">For Your judgments <char style="it">are</char> good.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="40" style="v" />Behold, I long for Your precepts;</para>
	<para style="q2">Revive me in Your righteousness.</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1493; <char style="sc">Waw</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="41" style="v" />Let Your mercies come also to me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>—</para>
	<para style="q2">Your salvation according to Your word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="42" style="v" />So shall I have an answer for him who reproaches me,</para>
	<para style="q2">For I trust in Your word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="43" style="v" />And take not the word of truth utterly out of my mouth,</para>
	<para style="q2">For I have hoped in Your ordinances.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="44" style="v" />So shall I keep Your law continually,</para>
	<para style="q2">Forever and ever.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="45" style="v" />And I will walk at <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 4:12</char></note>liberty,</para>
	<para style="q2">For I seek Your precepts.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="46" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 138:1; Matt. 10:18; Acts 26</char></note>I will speak of Your testimonies also before kings,</para>
	<para style="q2">And will not be ashamed.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="47" style="v" />And I will delight myself in Your commandments,</para>
	<para style="q2">Which I love.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="48" style="v" />My hands also I will lift up to Your commandments,</para>
	<para style="q2">Which I love,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I will meditate on Your statutes.</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1494; <char style="sc">Zayin</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="49" style="v" />Remember the word to Your servant,</para>
	<para style="q2">Upon which You have caused me to hope.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="50" style="v" />This <char style="it">is</char> my <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 6:10; (Rom. 15:4)</char></note>comfort in my affliction,</para>
	<para style="q2">For Your word has given me life.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="51" style="v" />The proud have me in great derision,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Yet</char> I do not turn aside from Your law.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="52" style="v" />I remembered Your judgments of old, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And have comforted myself.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="53" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 32:19; Ezra 9:3; Neh. 13:25</char></note>Indignation has taken hold of me</para>
	<para style="q2">Because of the wicked, who forsake Your law.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="54" style="v" />Your statutes have been my songs</para>
	<para style="q2">In the house of my pilgrimage.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="55" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 63:6</char></note>I remember Your name in the night, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I keep Your law.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="56" style="v" />This has become mine,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because I kept Your precepts.</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1495; <char style="sc">Heth</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="57" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 18:20; Ps. 16:5; Jer. 10:16; Lam. 3:24</char></note><char style="it">You</char> <char style="it">are</char> my portion, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">I have said that I would keep Your words.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="58" style="v" />I entreated Your favor with <char style="it">my</char> whole heart;</para>
	<para style="q2">Be merciful to me according to Your word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="59" style="v" />I <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Mark 14:72; Luke 15:17</char></note>thought about my ways,</para>
	<para style="q2">And turned my feet to Your testimonies.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="60" style="v" />I made haste, and did not delay</para>
	<para style="q2">To keep Your commandments.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="61" style="v" />The cords of the wicked have bound me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">But</char> I have not forgotten Your law.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="62" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Acts 16:25</char></note>At midnight I will rise to give thanks to You,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because of Your righteous judgments.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="63" style="v" />I <char style="it">am</char> a companion of all who fear You,</para>
	<para style="q2">And of those who keep Your precepts.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="64" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 33:5</char></note>The earth, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, is full of Your mercy;</para>
	<para style="q2">Teach me Your statutes.</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1496; <char style="sc">Teth</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="65" style="v" />You have dealt well with Your servant,</para>
	<para style="q2">O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, according to Your word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="66" style="v" />Teach me good judgment and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Phil. 1:9</char></note>knowledge,</para>
	<para style="q2">For I believe Your commandments.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="67" style="v" />Before I was <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 3:11; Jer. 31:18, 19; (Heb. 12:5–11)</char></note>afflicted I went astray,</para>
	<para style="q2">But now I keep Your word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="68" style="v" />You <char style="it">are</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 106:1; 107:1; (Matt. 19:17)</char></note>good, and do good;</para>
	<para style="q2">Teach me Your statutes.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="69" style="v" />The proud have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 13:4; Ps. 109:2</char></note>forged a lie against me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">But</char> I will keep Your precepts with <char style="it">my</char> whole heart.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="70" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 32:15; Job 15:27; Ps. 17:10; Is. 6:10; Jer. 5:28; Acts 28:27</char></note>Their heart is as fat as grease,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">But</char> I delight in Your law.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="71" style="v" /><char style="it">It</char> <char style="it">is</char> good for me that I have been afflicted,</para>
	<para style="q2">That I may learn Your statutes.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="72" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 19:10; Prov. 8:10, 11, 19</char></note>The law of Your mouth <char style="it">is</char> better to me</para>
	<para style="q2">Than thousands of <char style="it">coins</char> <char style="it">of</char> gold and silver.</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1497; <char style="sc">Yod</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="73" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 10:8; 31:15; (Ps. 139:15, 16)</char></note>Your hands have made me and fashioned me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Give me understanding, that I may learn Your commandments.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="74" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 34:2</char></note>Those who fear You will be glad when they see me,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because I have hoped in Your word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="75" style="v" />I know, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Heb. 12:10)</char></note>that Your judgments <char style="it">are</char> right,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">that</char> in faithfulness You have afflicted me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="76" style="v" />Let, I pray, Your merciful kindness be for my comfort,</para>
	<para style="q2">According to Your word to Your servant.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="77" style="v" />Let Your tender mercies come to me, that I may live;</para>
	<para style="q2">For Your law <char style="it">is</char> my delight.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="78" style="v" />Let the proud <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 25:3</char></note>be ashamed,</para>
	<para style="q2">For they treated me wrongfully with falsehood;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">But</char> I will meditate on Your precepts.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="79" style="v" />Let those who fear You turn to me,</para>
	<para style="q2">Those who know Your testimonies.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="80" style="v" />Let my heart be blameless regarding Your statutes,</para>
	<para style="q2">That I may not be ashamed.</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1498; <char style="sc">Kaph</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="81" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 73:26; 84:2</char></note>My soul faints for Your salvation,</para>
	<para style="q2">But I hope in Your word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="82" style="v" />My eyes fail <char style="it">from</char> <char style="it">searching</char> Your word,</para>
	<para style="q2">Saying, “When will You comfort me?”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="83" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 30:30</char></note>I have become like a wineskin in smoke,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Yet</char> I do not forget Your statutes.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="84" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 39:4</char></note>How many <char style="it">are</char> the days of Your servant?</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Rev. 6:10</char></note>When will You execute judgment on those who persecute me?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="85" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:7; Prov. 16:27; Jer. 18:22</char></note>The proud have dug pits for me,</para>
	<para style="q2">Which <char style="it">is</char> not according to Your law.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="86" style="v" />All Your commandments <char style="it">are</char> faithful;</para>
	<para style="q2">They persecute me <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:19</char></note>wrongfully;</para>
	<para style="q2">Help me!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="87" style="v" />They almost made an end of me on earth,</para>
	<para style="q2">But I did not forsake Your precepts.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="88" style="v" />Revive me according to Your lovingkindness,</para>
	<para style="q2">So that I may keep the testimony of Your mouth.</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1500; <char style="sc">Lamed</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="89" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 89:2; Is. 40:8; Matt. 24:35; (1 Pet. 1:25)</char></note>Forever, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Your word is settled in heaven.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="90" style="v" />Your faithfulness <char style="it">endures</char> to all generations;</para>
	<para style="q2">You established the earth, and it abides.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="91" style="v" />They continue this day according to <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 33:25</char></note>Your ordinances,</para>
	<para style="q2">For all <char style="it">are</char> Your servants.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="92" style="v" />Unless Your law <char style="it">had</char> <char style="it">been</char> my delight,</para>
	<para style="q2">I would then have perished in my affliction.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="93" style="v" />I will never forget Your precepts,</para>
	<para style="q2">For by them You have given me life.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="94" style="v" />I <char style="it">am</char> Yours, save me;</para>
	<para style="q2">For I have sought Your precepts.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="95" style="v" />The wicked wait for me to destroy me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">But</char> I will consider Your testimonies.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="96" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 5:18</char></note>I have seen the consummation of all perfection,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">But</char> Your commandment <char style="it">is</char> exceedingly broad.</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1501; <char style="sc">Mem</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="97" style="v" />Oh, how I love Your law!</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 1:2</char></note>It <char style="it">is</char> my meditation all the day.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="98" style="v" />You, through Your commandments, make me <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 4:6</char></note>wiser than my enemies;</para>
	<para style="q2">For they <char style="it">are</char> ever with me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="99" style="v" />I have more understanding than all my teachers,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(2 Tim. 3:15)</char></note>For Your testimonies <char style="it">are</char> my meditation.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="100" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Job 32:7–9)</char></note>I understand more than the ancients,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because I keep Your precepts.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="101" style="v" />I have restrained my feet from every evil way,</para>
	<para style="q2">That I may keep Your word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="102" style="v" />I have not departed from Your judgments,</para>
	<para style="q2">For You Yourself have taught me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="103" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 19:10; Prov. 8:11</char></note>How sweet are Your words to my taste,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Sweeter</char> than honey to my mouth!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="104" style="v" />Through Your precepts I get understanding;</para>
	<para style="q2">Therefore I hate every false way.</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1503; <char style="sc">Nun</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="105" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 6:23</char></note>Your word <char style="it">is</char> a lamp to my feet</para>
	<para style="q2">And a light to my path.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="106" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Neh. 10:29</char></note>I have sworn and confirmed</para>
	<para style="q2">That I will keep Your righteous judgments.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="107" style="v" />I am afflicted very much;</para>
	<para style="q2">Revive me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, according to Your word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="108" style="v" />Accept, I pray, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Hos. 14:2; Heb. 13:15</char></note>the freewill offerings of my mouth, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And teach me Your judgments.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="109" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Judg. 12:3; Job 13:14</char></note>My life <char style="it">is</char> continually in my hand,</para>
	<para style="q2">Yet I do not forget Your law.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="110" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 140:5</char></note>The wicked have laid a snare for me,</para>
	<para style="q2">Yet I have not strayed from Your precepts.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="111" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 33:4</char></note>Your testimonies I have taken as a heritage forever,</para>
	<para style="q2">For they <char style="it">are</char> the rejoicing of my heart.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="112" style="v" />I have inclined my heart to perform Your statutes</para>
	<para style="q2">Forever, to the very end.</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1505; <char style="sc">Samek</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="113" style="v" />I hate the double-minded,</para>
	<para style="q2">But I love Your law.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="114" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 32:7)</char></note>You <char style="it">are</char> my hiding place and my shield;</para>
	<para style="q2">I hope in Your word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="115" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 6:8; Matt. 7:23</char></note>Depart from me, you evildoers,</para>
	<para style="q2">For I will keep the commandments of my God!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="116" style="v" />Uphold me according to Your word, that I may live;</para>
	<para style="q2">And do not let me <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 25:2; (Rom. 5:5; 9:33; 10:11; Phil. 1:20)</char></note>be ashamed of my hope.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="117" style="v" />Hold me up, and I shall be safe,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I shall observe Your statutes continually.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="118" style="v" />You reject all those who stray from Your statutes,</para>
	<para style="q2">For their deceit <char style="it">is</char> falsehood.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="119" style="v" />You put away all the wicked of the earth <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 1:22, 25; Ezek. 22:18, 19</char></note><char style="it">like</char> dross;</para>
	<para style="q2">Therefore I love Your testimonies.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="120" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 4:14; Hab. 3:16</char></note>My flesh trembles for fear of You,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I am afraid of Your judgments.</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1506; <char style="sc">Ayin</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="121" style="v" />I have done justice and righteousness;</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not leave me to my oppressors.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="122" style="v" />Be <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 17:3; Heb. 7:22</char></note>surety for Your servant for good;</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not let the proud oppress me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="123" style="v" />My eyes fail <char style="it">from</char> <char style="it">seeking</char> Your salvation</para>
	<para style="q2">And Your righteous word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="124" style="v" />Deal with Your servant according to Your mercy,</para>
	<para style="q2">And teach me Your statutes.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="125" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 116:16</char></note>I <char style="it">am</char> Your servant;</para>
	<para style="q2">Give me understanding,</para>
	<para style="q2">That I may know Your testimonies.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="126" style="v" /><char style="it">It</char> <char style="it">is</char> time for <char style="it">You</char> to act, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">For</char> they have regarded Your law as void.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="127" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 19:10</char></note>Therefore I love Your commandments</para>
	<para style="q2">More than gold, yes, than fine gold!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="128" style="v" />Therefore all <char style="it">Your</char> precepts <char style="it">concerning</char> all <char style="it">things</char></para>
	<para style="q2">I consider <char style="it">to</char> <char style="it">be</char> right;</para>
	<para style="q2">I hate every false way.</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1508; <char style="sc">Pe</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="129" style="v" />Your testimonies are wonderful;</para>
	<para style="q2">Therefore my soul keeps them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="130" style="v" />The entrance of Your words gives light;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 6:23</char></note>It gives understanding to the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 19:7); Prov. 1:4</char></note>simple.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="131" style="v" />I opened my mouth and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 42:1</char></note>panted,</para>
	<para style="q2">For I longed for Your commandments.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="132" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 106:4</char></note>Look upon me and be merciful to me,</para>
	<para style="q2">As Your custom <char style="it">is</char> toward those who love Your name.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="133" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 51:1; (2 Thess. 1:6)</char></note>Direct my steps by Your word,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 17:5</char></note>let no iniquity have dominion over me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="134" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 19:13; Rom. 6:12)</char></note>Redeem me from the oppression of man,</para>
	<para style="q2">That I may keep Your precepts.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="135" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Luke 1:74</char></note>Make Your face shine upon Your servant,</para>
	<para style="q2">And teach me Your statutes.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="136" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 6:25; Ps. 4:6</char></note>Rivers of water run down from my eyes,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because <char style="it">men</char> do not keep Your law.</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1509; <char style="sc">Tsadde</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="137" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 9:1, 18; 14:17; Lam. 3:48; Ezek. 9:4</char></note>Righteous <char style="it">are</char> You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And upright <char style="it">are</char> Your judgments.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="138" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ezra 9:15; Neh. 9:33; Jer. 12:1; Lam. 1:18; Dan. 9:7, 14</char></note>Your testimonies, <char style="it">which</char> You have commanded,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Are</char> righteous and very faithful.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="139" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 19:7–9)</char></note>My zeal has consumed me,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because my enemies have forgotten Your words.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="140" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 69:9; John 2:17</char></note>Your word <char style="it">is</char> very pure;</para>
	<para style="q2">Therefore Your servant loves it.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="141" style="v" />I <char style="it">am</char> small and despised,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Yet</char> I do not forget Your precepts.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="142" style="v" />Your righteousness <char style="it">is</char> an everlasting righteousness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Your law <char style="it">is</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 12:6</char></note>truth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="143" style="v" />Trouble and anguish have overtaken me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Yet</char> Your commandments <char style="it">are</char> my delights.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="144" style="v" />The righteousness of Your testimonies <char style="it">is</char> everlasting;</para>
	<para style="q2">Give me understanding, and I shall live.</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1511; <char style="sc">Qoph</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="145" style="v" />I cry out with <char style="it">my</char> whole heart;</para>
	<para style="q2">Hear me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q2">I will keep Your statutes.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="146" style="v" />I cry out to You;</para>
	<para style="q2">Save me, and I will keep Your testimonies.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="147" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 19:9; John 17:17)</char></note>I rise before the dawning of the morning,</para>
	<para style="q2">And cry for help;</para>
	<para style="q2">I hope in Your word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="148" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 5:3</char></note>My eyes are awake through the <char style="it">night</char> watches,</para>
	<para style="q2">That I may meditate on Your word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="149" style="v" />Hear my voice according to Your lovingkindness;</para>
	<para style="q2">O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, revive me according to Your justice.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="150" style="v" />They draw near who follow after wickedness;</para>
	<para style="q2">They are far from Your law.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="151" style="v" />You <char style="it">are</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 63:1, 6</char></note>near, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And all Your commandments <char style="it">are</char> truth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="152" style="v" />Concerning Your testimonies,</para>
	<para style="q2">I have known of old that You have founded them <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 145:18); Is. 50:8</char></note>forever.</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1512; <char style="sc">Resh</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="153" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Luke 21:33</char></note>Consider my affliction and deliver me,</para>
	<para style="q2">For I do not forget Your law.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="154" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lam. 5:1</char></note>Plead my cause and redeem me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Revive me according to Your word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="155" style="v" />Salvation <char style="it">is</char> far from the wicked,</para>
	<para style="q2">For they do not seek Your statutes.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="156" style="v" />Great <char style="it">are</char> Your tender mercies, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">Revive me according to Your judgments.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="157" style="v" />Many <char style="it">are</char> my persecutors and my enemies,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Yet</char> I do not <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 24:15; Mic. 7:9</char></note>turn from Your testimonies.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="158" style="v" />I see the treacherous, and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 44:18</char></note>am disgusted,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because they do not keep Your word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="159" style="v" />Consider how I love Your precepts;</para>
	<para style="q2">Revive me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, according to Your lovingkindness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="160" style="v" />The entirety of Your word <char style="it">is</char> truth,</para>
	<para style="q2">And every one of Your righteous judgments <char style="it">endures</char> forever.</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1513;&#1473; <char style="sc">Shin</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="161" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ezek. 9:4</char></note>Princes persecute me without a cause,</para>
	<para style="q2">But my heart stands in awe of Your word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="162" style="v" />I rejoice at Your word</para>
	<para style="q2">As one who finds great treasure.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="163" style="v" />I hate and abhor lying,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">But</char> I love Your law.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="164" style="v" />Seven times a day I praise You,</para>
	<para style="q2">Because of Your righteous judgments.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="165" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 24:11; 26:18</char></note>Great peace have those who love Your law,</para>
	<para style="q2">And nothing causes them to stumble.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="166" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 3:2; (Is. 26:3; 32:17)</char></note><char style="sc">Lord</char>, I hope for Your salvation,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I do Your commandments.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="167" style="v" />My soul keeps Your testimonies,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I love them exceedingly.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="168" style="v" />I keep Your precepts and Your testimonies,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 49:18</char></note>For all my ways <char style="it">are</char> before You.</para>
	<para style="qa">&#1514; <char style="sc">Tau</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="169" style="v" />Let my cry come before You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 24:23; Prov. 5:21</char></note>Give me understanding according to Your word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="170" style="v" />Let my supplication come before You;</para>
	<para style="q2">Deliver me according to Your word.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="171" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:27, 144</char></note>My lips shall utter praise,</para>
	<para style="q2">For You teach me Your statutes.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="172" style="v" />My tongue shall speak of Your word,</para>
	<para style="q2">For all Your commandments <char style="it">are</char> righteousness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="173" style="v" />Let Your hand become my help,</para>
	<para style="q2">For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:7</char></note>I have chosen Your precepts.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="174" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Josh. 24:22; Luke 10:42</char></note>I long for Your salvation, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:166</char></note>Your law <char style="it">is</char> my delight.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="175" style="v" />Let my soul live, and it shall praise You;</para>
	<para style="q2">And let Your judgments help me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="176" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:16, 24</char></note>I have gone astray like a lost sheep;</para>
	<para style="q2">Seek Your servant,</para>
	<para style="q2">For I do not forget Your commandments.</para>
	<chapter number="120" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Plea for Relief from Bitter Foes</para>
	<para style="d">A Song of Ascents.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />In <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 53:6); Jer. 50:6; Matt. 18:12; Luke 15:4; (1 Pet. 2:25)</char></note>my distress I cried to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And He heard me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Deliver my soul, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, from lying lips</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> from a deceitful tongue.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />What shall be given to you,</para>
	<para style="q2">Or what shall be done to you,</para>
	<para style="q2">You false tongue?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Sharp arrows of the warrior,</para>
	<para style="q2">With coals of the broom tree!</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />Woe is me, that I dwell in <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jon. 2:2</char></note>Meshech,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 10:2; 1 Chr. 1:5; Ezek. 27:13; 38:2, 3; 39:1</char></note><char style="it">That</char> I dwell among the tents of Kedar!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />My soul has dwelt too long</para>
	<para style="q2">With one who hates peace.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />I <char style="it">am</char> <char style="it">for</char> peace;</para>
	<para style="q2">But when I speak, they <char style="it">are</char> for war.</para>
	<chapter number="121" style="c" />
	<para style="s">God the Help of Those Who Seek Him</para>
	<para style="d">A Song of Ascents.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />I <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 25:13; Is. 21:16; 60:7; Jer. 2:10; 49:28; Ezek. 27:21</char></note>will lift up my eyes to the hills—</para>
	<para style="q2">From whence comes my help?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Jer. 3:23)</char></note>My help <char style="it">comes</char> from the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who made heaven and earth.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 124:8)</char></note>He will not allow your foot to be moved;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 2:9; Prov. 3:23, 26</char></note>He who keeps you will not slumber.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Behold, He who keeps Israel</para>
	<para style="q2">Shall neither slumber nor sleep.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> your keeper;</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 127:1; Prov. 24:12); Is. 27:3</char></note>your shade <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 25:4</char></note>at your right hand.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 16:8</char></note>The sun shall not strike you by day,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor the moon by night.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> shall preserve you from all evil;</para>
	<para style="q2">He shall <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 91:5; Is. 49:10; Jon. 4:8; Rev. 7:16</char></note>preserve your soul.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> shall <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 41:2</char></note>preserve your going out and your coming in</para>
	<para style="q2">From this time forth, and even forevermore.</para>
	<chapter number="122" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Joy of Going to the House of the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="d">A Song of Ascents. Of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />I was glad when they said to me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 28:6; (Prov. 2:8; 3:6)</char></note>“Let us go into the house of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Our feet have been standing</para>
	<para style="q2">Within your gates, O Jerusalem!</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />Jerusalem is built</para>
	<para style="q2">As a city that is <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 2:3; Mic. 4:2); Zech. 8:21</char></note>compact together,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 5:9</char></note>Where the tribes go up,</para>
	<para style="q2">The tribes of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">To <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 23:17; Deut. 16:16</char></note>the Testimony of Israel,</para>
	<para style="q2">To give thanks to the name of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 16:34</char></note>For thrones are set there for judgment,</para>
	<para style="q2">The thrones of the house of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 17:8; 2 Chr. 19:8</char></note>Pray for the peace of Jerusalem:</para>
	<para style="q2">“May they prosper who love you.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Peace be within your walls,</para>
	<para style="q2">Prosperity within your palaces.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />For the sake of my brethren and companions,</para>
	<para style="q2">I will now say, “Peace <char style="it">be</char> within you.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />Because of the house of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> our God</para>
	<para style="q2">I will <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 51:18</char></note>seek your good.</para>
	<chapter number="123" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Prayer for Relief from Contempt</para>
	<para style="d">A Song of Ascents.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Unto You <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Neh. 2:10;  Esth. 10:3</char></note>I lift up my eyes,</para>
	<para style="q2">O You <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 121:1; 141:8</char></note>who dwell in the heavens.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Behold, as the eyes of servants <char style="it">look</char> to the hand of their masters,</para>
	<para style="q2">As the eyes of a maid to the hand of her mistress,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 2:4; 11:4; 115:3</char></note>So our eyes <char style="it">look</char> to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> our God,</para>
	<para style="q2">Until He has mercy on us.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />Have mercy on us, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, have mercy on us!</para>
	<para style="q2">For we are exceedingly filled with contempt.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Our soul is exceedingly filled</para>
	<para style="q2">With the scorn of those who are at ease,</para>
	<para style="q2">With the contempt of the proud.</para>
	<chapter number="124" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> the Defense of His People</para>
	<para style="d">A Song of Ascents. Of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />“If it had not been the <char style="sc">Lord</char> who was on our <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 25:15</char></note>side,”</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 118:6; (Rom. 8:31)</char></note>Let Israel now say—</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />“If it had not been the <char style="sc">Lord</char> who was on our side,</para>
	<para style="q2">When men rose up against us,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Then they would have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 129:1</char></note>swallowed us alive,</para>
	<para style="q2">When their wrath was kindled against us;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Then the waters would have overwhelmed us,</para>
	<para style="q2">The stream would have gone over our soul;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Then the swollen waters</para>
	<para style="q2">Would have gone over our soul.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />Blessed <char style="it">be</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who has not given us <char style="it">as</char> prey to their teeth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 16:30; Ps. 56:1, 2; 57:3; Prov. 1:12</char></note>Our soul has escaped <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 91:3</char></note>as a bird from the snare of the fowlers;</para>
	<para style="q2">The snare is broken, and we have escaped.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 6:5; Hos. 9:8</char></note>Our help <char style="it">is</char> in the name of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 121:2)</char></note>Who made heaven and earth.</para>
	<chapter number="125" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> the Strength of His People</para>
	<para style="d">A Song of Ascents.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Those who trust in the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Are</char> like Mount Zion,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Which</char> cannot be moved, <char style="it">but</char> abides forever.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />As the mountains surround Jerusalem,</para>
	<para style="q2">So the <char style="sc">Lord</char> surrounds His people</para>
	<para style="q2">From this time forth and forever.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 1:1; Ps. 134:3</char></note>the scepter of wickedness shall not rest</para>
	<para style="q2">On the land allotted to the righteous,</para>
	<para style="q2">Lest the righteous reach out their hands to iniquity.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />Do good, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, to <char style="it">those</char> <char style="it">who</char> <char style="it">are</char> good,</para>
	<para style="q2">And to <char style="it">those</char> <char style="it">who</char> <char style="it">are</char> upright in their hearts.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />As for such as turn aside to their <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 22:8; Is. 14:5</char></note>crooked ways,</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> shall lead them away</para>
	<para style="q2">With the workers of iniquity.</para>
	<para style="q1"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 2:15; Is. 59:8</char></note>Peace <char style="it">be</char> upon Israel!</para>
	<chapter number="126" style="c" />
	<para style="s">A Joyful Return to Zion</para>
	<para style="d">A Song of Ascents.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />When <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 128:6; (Gal. 6:16)</char></note>the <char style="sc">Lord</char> brought back the captivity of Zion,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 85:1; Jer. 29:14; Hos. 6:11; Joel 3:1</char></note>We were like those who dream.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Then <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Acts 12:9</char></note>our mouth was filled with laughter,</para>
	<para style="q2">And our tongue with singing.</para>
	<para style="q2">Then they said among the nations,</para>
	<para style="q2">“The <char style="sc">Lord</char> has done great things for them.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> has done great things for us,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> we are glad.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />Bring back our captivity, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">As the streams in the South.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 8:21</char></note>Those who sow in tears</para>
	<para style="q2">Shall reap in joy.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />He who continually goes forth weeping,</para>
	<para style="q2">Bearing seed for sowing,</para>
	<para style="q2">Shall doubtless come again with <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 35:10; 51:11; 61:7; Jer. 31:9; (Gal. 6:9)</char></note>rejoicing,</para>
	<para style="q2">Bringing his sheaves <char style="it">with</char> <char style="it">him.</char></para>
	<chapter number="127" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Laboring and Prospering with the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="d">A Song of Ascents. Of Solomon.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Unless the <char style="sc">Lord</char> builds the house,</para>
	<para style="q2">They labor in vain who build it;</para>
	<para style="q2">Unless <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 61:3</char></note>the <char style="sc">Lord</char> guards the city,</para>
	<para style="q2">The watchman stays awake in vain.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><char style="it">It</char> <char style="it">is</char> vain for you to rise up early,</para>
	<para style="q2">To sit up late,</para>
	<para style="q2">To <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 121:3–5)</char></note>eat the bread of sorrows;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">For</char> so He gives His beloved sleep.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />Behold, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Gen. 3:17, 19)</char></note>children <char style="it">are</char> a heritage from the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Gen. 33:5; Josh. 24:3, 4; Ps. 113:9)</char></note>The fruit of the womb <char style="it">is</char> a <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 7:13; 28:4; Is. 13:18</char></note>reward.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Like arrows in the hand of a warrior,</para>
	<para style="q2">So <char style="it">are</char> the children of one’s youth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 113:9)</char></note>Happy <char style="it">is</char> the man who has his quiver full of them;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 128:2, 3</char></note>They shall not be ashamed,</para>
	<para style="q2">But shall speak with their enemies in the gate.</para>
	<chapter number="128" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Blessings of Those Who Fear the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="d">A Song of Ascents.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Blessed <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 5:4; Prov. 27:11</char></note><char style="it">is</char> every one who fears the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who walks in His ways.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:1</char></note>When you eat the labor of your hands,</para>
	<para style="q2">You <char style="it">shall</char> <char style="it">be</char> happy, and <char style="it">it</char> <char style="it">shall</char> <char style="it">be</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 3:10</char></note>well with you.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Your wife <char style="it">shall</char> <char style="it">be</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 4:40</char></note>like a fruitful vine</para>
	<para style="q2">In the very heart of your house,</para>
	<para style="q2">Your <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ezek. 19:10</char></note>children <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 127:3–5</char></note>like olive plants</para>
	<para style="q2">All around your table.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Behold, thus shall the man be blessed</para>
	<para style="q2">Who fears the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 52:8; 144:12</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> bless you out of Zion,</para>
	<para style="q2">And may you see the good of Jerusalem</para>
	<para style="q2">All the days of your life.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Yes, may you <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 134:3</char></note>see your children’s children.</para>
	<para style="q1"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 48:11; 50:23; Job 42:16; Ps. 103:17; (Prov. 17:6)</char></note>Peace <char style="it">be</char> upon Israel!</para>
	<chapter number="129" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Song of Victory over Zion’s Enemies</para>
	<para style="d">Song of Ascents.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />“Many a time they have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 125:5</char></note>afflicted me from <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Jer. 1:19; 15:20); Matt. 16:18; 2 Cor. 4:8, 9</char></note>my youth,”</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ezek. 23:3; Hos. 2:15</char></note>Let Israel now say—</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />“Many a time they have afflicted me from my youth;</para>
	<para style="q2">Yet they have not prevailed against me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />The plowers plowed on my back;</para>
	<para style="q2">They made their furrows long.”</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> righteous;</para>
	<para style="q2">He has cut in pieces the cords of the wicked.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />Let all those who hate Zion</para>
	<para style="q2">Be put to shame and turned back.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Let them be as the <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 124:1</char></note>grass <char style="it">on</char> the housetops,</para>
	<para style="q2">Which withers before it grows up,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />With which the reaper does not fill his hand,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor he who binds sheaves, his arms.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Neither let those who pass by them say,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 37:2</char></note>“The blessing of the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">be</char> upon you;</para>
	<para style="q2">We bless you in the name of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!”</para>
	<chapter number="130" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Waiting for the Redemption of the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="d">A Song of Ascents.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Out <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ruth 2:4</char></note>of the depths I have cried to You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Lord, hear my voice!</para>
	<para style="q2">Let Your ears be attentive</para>
	<para style="q2">To the voice of my supplications.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lam. 3:55</char></note>If You, <char style="sc">Lord</char>, should mark iniquities,</para>
	<para style="q2">O Lord, who could <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 143:2)</char></note>stand?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />But <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Nah. 1:6; Mal. 3:2); Rev. 6:17</char></note>forgiveness with You,</para>
	<para style="q2">That <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 34:7; Neh. 9:17; Ps. 86:5; Is. 55:7; Dan. 9:9)</char></note>You may be feared.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Kin. 8:39, 40; Jer. 33:8, 9)</char></note>I wait for the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, my soul waits,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 27:14)</char></note>in His word I do hope.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:81</char></note>My soul <char style="it">waits</char> for the Lord</para>
	<para style="q2">More than those who watch for the morning—</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Yes, more than</char> those who watch for the morning.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:147</char></note>O Israel, hope in the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 131:3</char></note>with the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> mercy,</para>
	<para style="q2">And with Him <char style="it">is</char> abundant redemption.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 86:5, 15; Is. 55:7)</char></note>He shall redeem Israel</para>
	<para style="q2">From all his iniquities.</para>
	<chapter number="131" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Simple Trust in the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="d">A Song of Ascents. Of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" /><char style="sc">Lord</char>, my heart is not haughty,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor my eyes lofty.</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 103:3, 4); Luke 1:68; Titus 2:14</char></note>Neither do I concern myself with great matters,</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor with things too profound for me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" />Surely I have calmed and quieted my soul,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 45:5; (Rom. 12:16)</char></note>Like a weaned child with his mother;</para>
	<para style="q2">Like a weaned child <char style="it">is</char> my soul within me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Matt. 18:3; 1 Cor. 14:20)</char></note>O Israel, hope in the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="q2">From this time forth and forever.</para>
	<chapter number="132" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Eternal Dwelling of God in Zion</para>
	<para style="d">A Song of Ascents.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" /><char style="sc">Lord</char>, remember David</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> all his afflictions;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />How he swore to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 130:7)</char></note><char style="it">And</char> vowed to <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 65:1</char></note>the Mighty One of Jacob:</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />“Surely I will not go into the chamber of my house,</para>
	<para style="q2">Or go up to the comfort of my bed;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />I will <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 49:24; Is. 49:26; 60:16</char></note>not give sleep to my eyes</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Or</char> slumber to my eyelids,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Until I <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 6:4</char></note>find a place for the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">A dwelling place for the Mighty One of Jacob.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />Behold, we heard of it <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 8:17; 1 Chr. 22:7; Ps. 26:8; Acts 7:46</char></note>in Ephrathah;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 17:12</char></note>We found it <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 7:1</char></note>in the fields of the woods.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Let us go into His tabernacle;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 13:5</char></note>Let us worship at His footstool.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 5:7; 99:5</char></note>Arise, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, to Your resting place,</para>
	<para style="q2">You and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 10:35</char></note>the ark of Your strength.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />Let Your priests <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 78:61</char></note>be clothed with righteousness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And let Your saints shout for joy.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" />For Your servant David’s sake,</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not turn away the face of Your Anointed.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 29:14</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> has sworn <char style="it">in</char> truth to David;</para>
	<para style="q2">He will not turn from it:</para>
	<para style="q2">“I will set upon your throne <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 89:3, 4, 33; 110:4)</char></note>the fruit of your body.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />If your sons will keep My covenant</para>
	<para style="q2">And My testimony which I shall teach them,</para>
	<para style="q2">Their sons also shall sit upon your throne forevermore.”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 7:12; (1 Kin. 8:25; 2 Chr. 6:16; Luke 1:69; Acts 2:30)</char></note>For the <char style="sc">Lord</char> has chosen Zion;</para>
	<para style="q2">He has desired <char style="it">it</char> for His dwelling place:</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />“This<note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 48:1, 2)</char></note> <char style="it">is</char> My resting place forever;</para>
	<para style="q2">Here I will dwell, for I have desired it.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 68:16; Matt. 23:21</char></note>I will abundantly bless her provision;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will satisfy her poor with bread.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 147:14</char></note>I will also clothe her priests with salvation,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Chr. 6:41; Ps. 132:9; 149:4</char></note>And her saints shall shout aloud for joy.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 4:5; Hos. 11:12</char></note>There I will make the horn of David grow;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ezek. 29:21; Luke 1:69</char></note>I will prepare a lamp for My Anointed.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />His enemies I will <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 11:36; 15:4; 2 Kin. 8:19; 2 Chr. 21:7; Ps. 18:28</char></note>clothe with shame,</para>
	<para style="q2">But upon Himself His crown shall flourish.”</para>
	<chapter number="133" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Blessed Unity of the People of God</para>
	<para style="d">A Song of Ascents. Of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Behold, how good and how pleasant <char style="it">it</char> <char style="it">is</char></para>
	<para style="q2">For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 8:22; Ps. 35:26</char></note>brethren to dwell together in unity!</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" /><char style="it">It</char> <char style="it">is</char> like the precious oil upon the head,</para>
	<para style="q2">Running down on the beard,</para>
	<para style="q2">The beard of Aaron,</para>
	<para style="q2">Running down on the edge of his garments.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><char style="it">It</char> <char style="it">is</char> like the dew of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 13:8; Heb. 13:1</char></note>Hermon,</para>
	<para style="q2">Descending upon the mountains of Zion;</para>
	<para style="q2">For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 4:48</char></note>there the <char style="sc">Lord</char> commanded the blessing—</para>
	<para style="q2">Life forevermore.</para>
	<chapter number="134" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Praising the <char style="sc">Lord</char> in His House at Night</para>
	<para style="d">A Song of Ascents.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Behold, bless the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">All <char style="it">you</char> servants of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who by night stand in the house of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 25:21; Deut. 28:8; Ps. 42:8</char></note>Lift up your hands <char style="it">in</char> the sanctuary,</para>
	<para style="q2">And bless the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> who made heaven and earth</para>
	<para style="q2">Bless you from Zion!</para>
	<chapter number="135" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Praise to God in Creation and Redemption</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q1">Praise the name of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(1 Tim. 2:8)</char></note>Praise <char style="it">Him,</char> O you servants of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 113:1</char></note>You who stand in the house of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">In <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Luke 2:37</char></note>the courts of the house of our God,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, for <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 116:19</char></note>the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> good;</para>
	<para style="q2">Sing praises to His name, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 119:68)</char></note>for <char style="it">it</char> <char style="it">is</char> pleasant.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 147:1</char></note>the <char style="sc">Lord</char> has chosen Jacob for Himself,</para>
	<para style="q2">Israel for His special treasure.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />For I know that <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 19:5); Mal. 3:17; (Titus 2:14; 1 Pet. 2:9)</char></note>the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> great,</para>
	<para style="q2">And our Lord <char style="it">is</char> above all gods.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 95:3; 97:9</char></note>Whatever the <char style="sc">Lord</char> pleases He does,</para>
	<para style="q2">In heaven and in earth,</para>
	<para style="q2">In the seas and in all deep places.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 115:3</char></note>He causes the vapors to ascend from the ends of the earth;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 10:13</char></note>He makes lightning for the rain;</para>
	<para style="q2">He brings the wind out of His <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 28:25, 26; 38:24–28</char></note>treasuries.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 51:16</char></note>He destroyed the firstborn of Egypt,</para>
	<para style="q2">Both of man and beast.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 12:12; Ps. 78:51</char></note>He sent signs and wonders into the midst of you, O Egypt,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 7:10; Deut. 6:22; Ps. 78:43</char></note>Upon Pharaoh and all his servants.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 136:15</char></note>He defeated many nations</para>
	<para style="q2">And slew mighty kings—</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />Sihon king of the Amorites,</para>
	<para style="q2">Og king of Bashan,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 21:24; Ps. 136:17</char></note>all the kingdoms of Canaan—</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Josh. 12:7–24</char></note>And gave their land <char style="it">as</char> a heritage,</para>
	<para style="q2">A heritage to Israel His people.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 78:55; 136:21, 22</char></note>Your name, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <char style="it">endures</char> forever,</para>
	<para style="q2">Your fame, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, throughout all generations.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 3:15; Ps. 102:12)</char></note>For the <char style="sc">Lord</char> will judge His people,</para>
	<para style="q2">And He will have compassion on His servants.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 32:36</char></note>The idols of the nations <char style="it">are</char> silver and gold,</para>
	<para style="q2">The work of men’s hands.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />They have mouths, but they do not speak;</para>
	<para style="q2">Eyes they have, but they do not see;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />They have ears, but they do not hear;</para>
	<para style="q2">Nor is there <char style="it">any</char> breath in their mouths.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" />Those who make them are like them;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">So</char> <char style="it">is</char> everyone who trusts in them.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 115:4–8)</char></note>Bless the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, O house of Israel!</para>
	<para style="q2">Bless the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, O house of Aaron!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />Bless the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, O house of Levi!</para>
	<para style="q2">You who fear the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, bless the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />Blessed be the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 115:9)</char></note>out of Zion,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who dwells in Jerusalem!</para>
	<para style="q1">Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<chapter number="136" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Thanksgiving to God for His Enduring Mercy</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Oh, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 134:3</char></note>give thanks to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, for <char style="it">He</char> <char style="it">is</char> good!</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 106:1</char></note>For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Oh, give thanks to <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Chr. 16:34; Jer. 33:11</char></note>the God of gods!</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Oh, give thanks to the Lord of lords!</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever:</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />To Him <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 10:17)</char></note>who alone does great wonders,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 6:22; Job 9:10; Ps. 72:18</char></note>To Him who by wisdom made the heavens,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 1:1, 6–8; Prov. 3:19; Jer. 51:15</char></note>To Him who laid out the earth above the waters,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 1:9; Ps. 24:2; (Is. 42:5); Jer. 10:12</char></note>To Him who made great lights,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever—</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 1:14–18</char></note>The sun to rule by day,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />The moon and stars to rule by night,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 1:16</char></note>To Him who struck Egypt in their firstborn,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 12:29; Ps. 135:8</char></note>And brought out Israel from among them,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 12:51; 13:3, 16</char></note>With a strong hand, and with an outstretched arm,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 6:6; Deut. 4:34; 5:15; 7:19; 9:29; 11:2; 2 Kin. 17:36; 2 Chr. 6:32; Jer. 32:17</char></note>To Him who divided the Red Sea in two,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />And made Israel pass through the midst of it,</para>
	<para style="q1">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 14:21</char></note>But overthrew Pharaoh and his army in the Red Sea,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 14:27</char></note>To Him who led His people through the wilderness,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 13:18; 15:22; Deut. 8:15</char></note>To Him who struck down great kings,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 135:10–12</char></note>And slew famous kings,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever—</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 29:7</char></note>Sihon king of the Amorites,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 21:21</char></note>And Og king of Bashan,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever—</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Num. 21:33</char></note>And gave their land as a heritage,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" />A heritage to Israel His servant,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="23" style="v" />Who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Josh. 12:1</char></note>remembered us in our lowly state,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" />And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 8:1; Deut. 32:36; Ps. 113:7</char></note>rescued us from our enemies,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="25" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 44:7</char></note>Who gives food to all flesh,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="26" style="v" />Oh, give thanks to the God of heaven!</para>
	<para style="q2">For His mercy <char style="it">endures</char> forever.</para>
	<chapter number="137" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Longing for Zion in a Foreign Land</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />By the rivers of Babylon,</para>
	<para style="q2">There we sat down, yea, we wept</para>
	<para style="q2">When we remembered Zion.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />We hung our harps</para>
	<para style="q2">Upon the willows in the midst of it.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />For there those who carried us away captive asked of us a song,</para>
	<para style="q2">And those who <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 104:27; 145:15</char></note>plundered us <char style="it">requested</char> mirth,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Saying,</char> “Sing us <char style="it">one</char> of the songs of Zion!”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" />How shall we sing the <char style="sc">Lord</char>’s song</para>
	<para style="q2">In a foreign land?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />If I forget you, O Jerusalem,</para>
	<para style="q2">Let my right hand forget <char style="it">its</char> <char style="it">skill!</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />If I do not remember you,</para>
	<para style="q2">Let my <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 79:1</char></note>tongue cling to the roof of my mouth—</para>
	<para style="q2">If I do not exalt Jerusalem</para>
	<para style="q2">Above my chief joy.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />Remember, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, against <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 29:10; Ps. 22:15; Ezek. 3:26</char></note>the sons of Edom</para>
	<para style="q2">The day of Jerusalem,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who said, “Raze <char style="it">it,</char> raze <char style="it">it,</char></para>
	<para style="q2">To its very foundation!”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />O daughter of Babylon, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 49:7–22; Lam. 4:21; Ezek. 25:12–14; 35:2; Amos 1:11; Obad. 10–14</char></note>who are to be destroyed,</para>
	<para style="q2">Happy the one <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 13:1–6; 47:1</char></note>who repays you as you have served us!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />Happy the one who takes and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 50:15; Rev. 18:6</char></note>dashes</para>
	<para style="q2">Your little ones against the rock!</para>
	<chapter number="138" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The <char style="sc">Lord</char>’s Goodness to the Faithful</para>
	<para style="d">A <char style="it">Psalm</char> of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />I will praise You with my whole heart;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Kin. 8:12; Is. 13:16; Hos. 13:16; Nah. 3:10</char></note>Before the gods I will sing praises to You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:46</char></note>I will worship <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 28:2</char></note>toward Your holy temple,</para>
	<para style="q2">And praise Your name</para>
	<para style="q2">For Your lovingkindness and Your truth;</para>
	<para style="q2">For You have <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 8:29</char></note>magnified Your word above all Your name.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />In the day when I cried out, You answered me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> made me bold <char style="it">with</char> strength in my soul.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 42:21</char></note>All the kings of the earth shall praise You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">When they hear the words of Your mouth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Yes, they shall sing of the ways of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">For great <char style="it">is</char> the glory of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 102:15</char></note>Though the <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> on high,</para>
	<para style="q2">Yet <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 113:4–7)</char></note>He regards the lowly;</para>
	<para style="q2">But the proud He knows from afar.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 3:34; (Is. 57:15); Luke 1:48; (James 4:6; 1 Pet. 5:5)</char></note>Though I walk in the midst of trouble, You will revive me;</para>
	<para style="q2">You will stretch out Your hand</para>
	<para style="q2">Against the wrath of my enemies,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Your right hand will save me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 23:3, 4)</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> will perfect <char style="it">that</char> <char style="it">which</char> concerns me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Your mercy, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <char style="it">endures</char> forever;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 57:2; (Phil. 1:6)</char></note>Do not forsake the works of Your hands.</para>
	<chapter number="139" style="c" />
	<para style="s">God’s Perfect Knowledge of Man</para>
	<para style="d">For the Chief Musician. A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 10:3, 8</char></note>You have searched me and known <char style="it">me.</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 17:3; Jer. 12:3</char></note>You know my sitting down and my rising up;</para>
	<para style="q2">You <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Kin. 19:27</char></note>understand my thought afar off.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 66:18; Matt. 9:4</char></note>You comprehend my path and my lying down,</para>
	<para style="q2">And are acquainted with all my ways.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />For <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> not a word on my tongue,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">But</char> behold, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 14:16; 31:4</char></note>You know it altogether.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />You have hedged me behind and before,</para>
	<para style="q2">And laid Your hand upon me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Heb. 4:13)</char></note><char style="it">Such</char> knowledge <char style="it">is</char> too wonderful for me;</para>
	<para style="q2">It is high, I cannot <char style="it">attain</char> it.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 42:3; Ps. 40:5</char></note>Where can I go from Your Spirit?</para>
	<para style="q2">Or where can I flee from Your presence?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Jer. 23:24; Amos 9:2–4)</char></note>If I ascend into heaven, You <char style="it">are</char> there;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Amos 9:2–4)</char></note>If I make my bed in hell, behold, You <char style="it">are</char> <char style="it">there.</char></para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><char style="it">If</char> I take the wings of the morning,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> dwell in the uttermost parts of the sea,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />Even there Your hand shall lead me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Your right hand shall hold me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />If I say, “Surely the darkness shall fall on me,”</para>
	<para style="q2">Even the night shall be light about me;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />Indeed, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Job 26:6; Prov. 15:11)</char></note>the darkness shall not hide from You,</para>
	<para style="q2">But the night shines as the day;</para>
	<para style="q2">The darkness and the light <char style="it">are</char> both alike <char style="it">to</char> <char style="it">You.</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" />For You formed my inward parts;</para>
	<para style="q2">You covered me in my mother’s womb.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />I will praise You, for I am fearfully <char style="it">and</char> wonderfully made;</para>
	<para style="q2">Marvelous are Your works,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">that</char> my soul knows very well.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 26:6; 34:22; (Dan. 2:22; Heb. 4:13)</char></note>My frame was not hidden from You,</para>
	<para style="q2">When I was made in secret,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> skillfully wrought in the lowest parts of the earth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />Your eyes saw my substance, being yet unformed.</para>
	<para style="q2">And in Your book they all were written,</para>
	<para style="q2">The days fashioned for me,</para>
	<para style="q2">When <char style="it">as</char> <char style="it">yet</char> <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">were</char> none of them.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="17" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 10:8, 9; Eccl. 11:5</char></note>How precious also are Your thoughts to me, O God!</para>
	<para style="q2">How great is the sum of them!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" /><char style="it">If</char> I should count them, they would be more in number than the sand;</para>
	<para style="q2">When I awake, I am still with You.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" />Oh, that You would <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 40:5; Rom. 11:33)</char></note>slay the wicked, O God!</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 11:4)</char></note>Depart from me, therefore, you bloodthirsty men.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" />For they <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:115</char></note>speak against You wickedly;</para>
	<para style="q2">Your enemies take <char style="it">Your</char> <char style="it">name</char> in vain.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jude 15</char></note>Do I not hate them, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, who hate You?</para>
	<para style="q2">And do I not loathe those who rise up against You?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="22" style="v" />I hate them with perfect hatred;</para>
	<para style="q2">I count them my enemies.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="23" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Chr. 19:2</char></note>Search me, O God, and know my heart;</para>
	<para style="q2">Try me, and know my anxieties;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="24" style="v" />And see if <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">any</char> wicked way in me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 31:6; Ps. 26:2</char></note>lead me in the way everlasting.</para>
	<chapter number="140" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Prayer for Deliverance from Evil Men</para>
	<para style="d">To the Chief Musician. A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Deliver me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, from evil men;</para>
	<para style="q2">Preserve me from violent men,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Who plan evil things in <char style="it">their</char> hearts;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 5:8; 143:10</char></note>They continually gather together <char style="it">for</char> war.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />They sharpen their tongues like a serpent;</para>
	<para style="q2">The <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 56:6</char></note>poison of asps <char style="it">is</char> under their lips.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 58:4; Rom. 3:13; James 3:8</char></note>Keep me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, from the hands of the wicked;</para>
	<para style="q2">Preserve me from violent men,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who have purposed to make my steps stumble.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />The proud have hidden a <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 71:4</char></note>snare for me, and cords;</para>
	<para style="q2">They have spread a net by the wayside;</para>
	<para style="q2">They have set traps for me.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />I said to the <char style="sc">Lord</char>: “You <char style="it">are</char> my God;</para>
	<para style="q2">Hear the voice of my supplications, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />O G<char style="sc">OD</char> the Lord, the strength of my salvation,</para>
	<para style="q2">You have covered my head in the day of battle.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Do not grant, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, the desires of the wicked;</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not further his <char style="it">wicked</char> scheme,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:7; Jer. 18:22</char></note><char style="it">Lest</char> they be exalted.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />“<char style="it">As</char> <char style="it">for</char> the head of those who surround me,</para>
	<para style="q2">Let the evil of their lips cover them;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 32:27</char></note>Let burning coals fall upon them;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let them be cast into the fire,</para>
	<para style="q2">Into deep pits, that they rise not up again.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />Let not a slanderer be established in the earth;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let evil hunt the violent man to overthrow <char style="it">him.</char>”</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />I know that the <char style="sc">Lord</char> will <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 11:6</char></note>maintain</para>
	<para style="q2">The cause of the afflicted,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> justice for the poor.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />Surely the righteous shall give thanks to Your name;</para>
	<para style="q2">The upright shall dwell in Your presence.</para>
	<chapter number="141" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Prayer for Safekeeping from Wickedness</para>
	<para style="d">A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" /><char style="sc">Lord</char>, I cry out to You;</para>
	<para style="q2">Make haste to me!</para>
	<para style="q2">Give ear to my voice when I cry out to You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Let my prayer be set before You <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Kin. 8:45; Ps. 9:4</char></note><char style="it">as</char> incense,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 30:8); Luke 1:10; (Rev. 5:8; 8:3, 4)</char></note>The lifting up of my hands <char style="it">as</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 134:2; (1 Tim. 2:8)</char></note>the evening sacrifice.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />Set a guard, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, over my <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 29:39, 41; 1 Kin. 18:29, 36; Dan. 9:21</char></note>mouth;</para>
	<para style="q2">Keep watch over the door of my lips.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Do not incline my heart to any evil thing,</para>
	<para style="q2">To practice wicked works</para>
	<para style="q2">With men who work iniquity;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Prov. 13:3; 21:23)</char></note>And do not let me eat of their delicacies.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Prov. 23:6</char></note>Let the righteous strike me;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">It</char> <char style="it">shall</char> <char style="it">be</char> a kindness.</para>
	<para style="q2">And let him rebuke me;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">It</char> <char style="it">shall</char> <char style="it">be</char> as excellent oil;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let my head not refuse it.</para>
	<para style="q1">For still my prayer <char style="it">is</char> against the deeds of the wicked.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Their judges are overthrown by the sides of the cliff,</para>
	<para style="q2">And they hear my words, for they are sweet.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Our bones are scattered at the mouth of the grave,</para>
	<para style="q2">As when one plows and breaks up the earth.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" />But <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Prov. 9:8; Eccl. 7:5; Gal. 6:1)</char></note>my eyes <char style="it">are</char> upon You, O G<char style="sc">OD</char> the Lord;</para>
	<para style="q2">In You I take refuge;</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not leave my soul destitute.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" />Keep me from <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Chr. 20:12; Ps. 25:15</char></note>the snares they have laid for me,</para>
	<para style="q2">And from the traps of the workers of iniquity.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:110</char></note>Let the wicked fall into their own nets,</para>
	<para style="q2">While I escape safely.</para>
	<chapter number="142" style="c" />
	<para style="s">A Plea for Relief from Persecutors</para>
	<para style="d">A <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:8</char></note>Contemplation of David. A Prayer <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 32:title</char></note>when he was in the cave.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />I cry out to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> with my voice;</para>
	<para style="q2">With my voice to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> I make my supplication.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />I pour out my complaint before Him;</para>
	<para style="q2">I declare before Him my trouble.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />When my spirit was <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 22:1; Ps. 57:title</char></note>overwhelmed within me,</para>
	<para style="q2">Then You knew my path.</para>
	<para style="q2">In the way in which I walk</para>
	<para style="q2">They have secretly <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 77:3</char></note>set a snare for me.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Look on <char style="it">my</char> right hand and see,</para>
	<para style="q2">For <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> no one who acknowledges me;</para>
	<para style="q2">Refuge has failed me;</para>
	<para style="q2">No one cares for my soul.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />I cried out to You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>:</para>
	<para style="q2">I said, “You <char style="it">are</char> my refuge,</para>
	<para style="q2">My portion in the land of the living.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />Attend to my cry,</para>
	<para style="q2">For I am brought very low;</para>
	<para style="q2">Deliver me from my persecutors,</para>
	<para style="q2">For they are stronger than I.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Bring my soul out of prison,</para>
	<para style="q2">That I may <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 141:9</char></note>praise Your name;</para>
	<para style="q2">The righteous shall surround me,</para>
	<para style="q2">For You shall deal bountifully with me.”</para>
	<chapter number="143" style="c" />
	<para style="s">An Earnest Appeal for Guidance and Deliverance</para>
	<para style="d">A Psalm of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Hear my prayer, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">Give ear to my supplications!</para>
	<para style="q2">In Your faithfulness answer me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> in Your righteousness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Do not enter into judgment with Your servant,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 34:1, 2</char></note>For in Your sight no one living is righteous.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />For the enemy has persecuted my soul;</para>
	<para style="q2">He has crushed my life to the ground;</para>
	<para style="q2">He has made me dwell in darkness,</para>
	<para style="q2">Like those who have long been dead.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 34:7); Job 4:17; 9:2; 25:4; Ps. 130:3; Eccl. 7:20; (Rom. 3:20–23; Gal. 2:16)</char></note>Therefore my spirit is overwhelmed within me;</para>
	<para style="q2">My heart within me is distressed.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 77:3</char></note>I remember the days of old;</para>
	<para style="q2">I meditate on all Your works;</para>
	<para style="q2">I muse on the work of Your hands.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" />I spread out my hands to You;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 77:5, 10, 11</char></note>My soul <char style="it">longs</char> for You like a thirsty land.</para>
	<para style="p"><char style="qs">Selah</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />Answer me speedily, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">My spirit fails!</para>
	<para style="q2">Do not hide Your face from me,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 63:1</char></note>Lest I be like those who go down into the pit.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Cause me to hear Your lovingkindness <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 28:1</char></note>in the morning,</para>
	<para style="q2">For in You do I trust;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 46:5</char></note>Cause me to know the way in which I should walk,</para>
	<para style="q2">For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 5:8</char></note>I lift up my soul to You.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />Deliver me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, from my enemies;</para>
	<para style="q2">In You I take shelter.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 25:1</char></note>Teach me to do Your will,</para>
	<para style="q2">For You <char style="it">are</char> my God;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 25:4, 5</char></note>Your Spirit <char style="it">is</char> good.</para>
	<para style="q2">Lead me in <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Neh. 9:20</char></note>the land of uprightness.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 26:10</char></note>Revive me, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, for Your name’s sake!</para>
	<para style="q2">For Your righteousness’ sake bring my soul out of trouble.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />In Your mercy <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 119:25</char></note>cut off my enemies,</para>
	<para style="q2">And destroy all those who afflict my soul;</para>
	<para style="q2">For I <char style="it">am</char> Your servant.</para>
	<chapter number="144" style="c" />
	<para style="s">A Song to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> Who Preserves and Prospers His People</para>
	<para style="d"><char style="it">A</char> <char style="it">Psalm</char> of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Blessed <char style="it">be</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char> my Rock,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 54:5</char></note>Who trains my hands for war,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> my fingers for battle—</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />My lovingkindness and my fortress,</para>
	<para style="q2">My high tower and my deliverer,</para>
	<para style="q2">My shield and <char style="it">the</char> <char style="it">One</char> in whom I take refuge,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who subdues my people under me.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">2 Sam. 22:35; Ps. 18:34</char></note><char style="sc">Lord</char>, what <char style="it">is</char> man, that You take knowledge of him?</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Or</char> the son of man, that You are mindful of him?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 7:17; Ps. 8:4; Heb. 2:6</char></note>Man is like a breath;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 39:11</char></note>His days <char style="it">are</char> like a passing shadow.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 8:9; 14:2; Ps. 102:11</char></note>Bow down Your heavens, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>, and come down;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 18:9; Is. 64:1</char></note>Touch the mountains, and they shall smoke.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 104:32</char></note>Flash forth lightning and scatter them;</para>
	<para style="q2">Shoot out Your arrows and destroy them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />Stretch out Your hand from above;</para>
	<para style="q2">Rescue me and deliver me out of great waters,</para>
	<para style="q2">From the hand of foreigners,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Whose mouth <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 18:13, 14</char></note>speaks lying words,</para>
	<para style="q2">And whose right hand <char style="it">is</char> a right hand of falsehood.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="9" style="v" />I will <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 12:2</char></note>sing a new song to You, O God;</para>
	<para style="q2">On a harp of ten strings I will sing praises to You,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" /><char style="it">The</char> <char style="it">One</char> who gives salvation to kings,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 33:2, 3; 40:3</char></note>Who delivers David His servant</para>
	<para style="q2">From the deadly sword.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="11" style="v" />Rescue me and deliver me from the hand of foreigners,</para>
	<para style="q2">Whose mouth speaks lying words,</para>
	<para style="q2">And whose right hand <char style="it">is</char> a right hand of falsehood—</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />That our sons <char style="it">may</char> <char style="it">be</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 18:50</char></note>as plants grown up in their youth;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">That</char> our daughters <char style="it">may</char> <char style="it">be</char> as pillars,</para>
	<para style="q2">Sculptured in palace style;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><char style="it">That</char> our barns <char style="it">may</char> <char style="it">be</char> full,</para>
	<para style="q2">Supplying all kinds of produce;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">That</char> our sheep may bring forth thousands</para>
	<para style="q2">And ten thousands in our fields;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" /><char style="it">That</char> our oxen <char style="it">may</char> <char style="it">be</char> well laden;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">That</char> <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">be</char> no breaking in or going out;</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">That</char> <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">be</char> no outcry in our streets.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 128:3</char></note>Happy <char style="it">are</char> the people who are in such a state;</para>
	<para style="q2">Happy <char style="it">are</char> the people whose God <char style="it">is</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<chapter number="145" style="c" />
	<para style="s">A Song of God’s Majesty and Love</para>
	<para style="d"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 33:29; (Ps. 33:12; Jer. 17:7)</char></note>A Praise of David.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />I will extol You, my God, O King;</para>
	<para style="q2">And I will bless Your name forever and ever.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Every day I will bless You,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I will praise Your name forever and ever.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 100:title</char></note>Great <char style="it">is</char> the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, and greatly to be praised;</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 147:5)</char></note>His greatness <char style="it">is</char> unsearchable.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 5:9; 9:10; 11:7; Is. 40:28; (Rom. 11:33)</char></note>One generation shall praise Your works to another,</para>
	<para style="q2">And shall declare Your mighty acts.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />I will meditate on the glorious splendor of Your majesty,</para>
	<para style="q2">And on Your wondrous works.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><char style="it">Men</char> shall speak of the might of Your awesome acts,</para>
	<para style="q2">And I will declare Your greatness.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />They shall utter the memory of Your great goodness,</para>
	<para style="q2">And shall sing of Your righteousness.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 38:19</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> gracious and full of compassion,</para>
	<para style="q2">Slow to anger and great in mercy.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ex. 34:6, 7; Num. 14:18); Ps. 86:5, 15</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> good to all,</para>
	<para style="q2">And His tender mercies <char style="it">are</char> over all His works.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 100:5); Jer. 33:11; Nah. 1:7; (Matt. 19:17; Mark 10:18)</char></note>All Your works shall praise You, O <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Your saints shall bless You.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />They shall speak of the glory of Your kingdom,</para>
	<para style="q2">And talk of Your power,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />To make known to the sons of men His mighty acts,</para>
	<para style="q2">And the glorious majesty of His kingdom.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 19:1</char></note>Your kingdom <char style="it">is</char> an everlasting kingdom,</para>
	<para style="q2">And Your dominion <char style="it">endures</char> throughout all generations.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="14" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> upholds all who fall,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Dan. 2:44; 4:3; (1 Tim. 1:17; 2 Pet. 1:11)</char></note>raises up all <char style="it">who</char> <char style="it">are</char> bowed down.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="15" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 146:8</char></note>The eyes of all look expectantly to You,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 104:27</char></note>You give them their food in due season.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" />You open Your hand</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 136:25</char></note>And satisfy the desire of every living thing.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="17" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> righteous in all His ways,</para>
	<para style="q2">Gracious in all His works.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 104:21, 28</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <char style="it">is</char> near to all who call upon Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">To all who call upon Him <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Deut. 4:7)</char></note>in truth.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="19" style="v" />He will fulfill the desire of those who fear Him;</para>
	<para style="q2">He also will hear their cry and save them.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(John 4:24)</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> preserves all who love Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">But all the wicked He will destroy.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="21" style="v" />My mouth shall speak the praise of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">And all flesh shall bless His holy name</para>
	<para style="q2">Forever and ever.</para>
	<chapter number="146" style="c" />
	<para style="s">The Happiness of Those Whose Help Is the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q1"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 31:23)</char></note>Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, O my soul!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 103:1</char></note>While I live I will praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>;</para>
	<para style="q2">I will sing praises to my God while I have my being.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 104:33</char></note>Do not put your trust in princes,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">Nor</char> in a son of man, in whom <char style="it">there</char> <char style="it">is</char> no help.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Is. 2:22)</char></note>His spirit departs, he returns to his earth;</para>
	<para style="q2">In that very day <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Eccl. 12:7)</char></note>his plans perish.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 33:10; 1 Cor. 2:6)</char></note>Happy <char style="it">is</char> <char style="it">he</char> who <char style="it">has</char> the God of Jacob for his help,</para>
	<para style="q2">Whose hope <char style="it">is</char> in the <char style="sc">Lord</char> his God,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Jer. 17:7</char></note>Who made heaven and earth,</para>
	<para style="q2">The sea, and all that <char style="it">is</char> in them;</para>
	<para style="q2">Who keeps truth forever,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 1:1; Ex. 20:11; Acts 4:24; Rev. 14:7</char></note>Who executes justice for the oppressed,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 103:6</char></note>Who gives food to the hungry.</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 107:9</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> gives freedom to the prisoners.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 107:10; Is. 61:1</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> opens <char style="it">the</char> <char style="it">eyes</char> <char style="it">of</char> the blind;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Matt. 9:30; (John 9:7, 32, 33)</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> raises those who are bowed down;</para>
	<para style="q2">The <char style="sc">Lord</char> loves the righteous.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Luke 13:13</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> watches over the strangers;</para>
	<para style="q2">He relieves the fatherless and widow;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 10:18; Ps. 68:5</char></note>But the way of the wicked He turns upside down.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 147:6</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> shall reign forever—</para>
	<para style="q2">Your God, O Zion, to all generations.</para>
	<para style="q1">Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<chapter number="147" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Praise to God for His Word and Providence</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q2">For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 15:18; Ps. 10:16; (Rev. 11:15)</char></note><char style="it">it</char> <char style="it">is</char> good to sing praises to our God;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 92:1</char></note>For <char style="it">it</char> <char style="it">is</char> pleasant, <char style="it">and</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 135:3</char></note>praise is beautiful.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 33:1</char></note>builds up Jerusalem;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 102:16</char></note>He gathers together the outcasts of Israel.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 30:3; Is. 11:12; 56:8; Ezek. 39:28</char></note>He heals the brokenhearted</para>
	<para style="q2">And binds up their wounds.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 51:17); Is. 61:1; Luke 4:18</char></note>He counts the number of the stars;</para>
	<para style="q2">He calls them all by name.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 40:26</char></note>Great <char style="it">is</char> our Lord, and <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 48:1</char></note>mighty in power;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Nah. 1:3</char></note>His understanding <char style="it">is</char> infinite.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 40:28</char></note>The <char style="sc">Lord</char> lifts up the humble;</para>
	<para style="q2">He casts the wicked down to the ground.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />Sing to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> with thanksgiving;</para>
	<para style="q2">Sing praises on the harp to our God,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 146:8, 9</char></note>Who covers the heavens with clouds,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who prepares rain for the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2">Who makes grass to grow on the mountains.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 38:26; Ps. 104:13</char></note>He gives to the beast its food,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 38:41</char></note>to the young ravens that cry.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="10" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Matt. 6:26)</char></note>He does not delight in the strength of the horse;</para>
	<para style="q2">He takes no pleasure in the legs of a man.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />The <char style="sc">Lord</char> takes pleasure in those who fear Him,</para>
	<para style="q2">In those who hope in His mercy.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="12" style="v" />Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>, O Jerusalem!</para>
	<para style="q2">Praise your God, O Zion!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="13" style="v" />For He has strengthened the bars of your gates;</para>
	<para style="q2">He has blessed your children within you.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 33:16, 17</char></note>He makes peace <char style="it">in</char> your borders,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 54:13; 60:17, 18</char></note>fills you with the finest wheat.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="15" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 132:15</char></note>He sends out His command <char style="it">to</char> <char style="it">the</char> earth;</para>
	<para style="q2">His word runs very swiftly.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="16" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">(Ps. 107:20)</char></note>He gives snow like wool;</para>
	<para style="q2">He scatters the frost like ashes;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="17" style="v" />He casts out His hail like morsels;</para>
	<para style="q2">Who can stand before His cold?</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="18" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 37:6</char></note>He sends out His word and melts them;</para>
	<para style="q2">He causes His wind to blow, <char style="it">and</char> the waters flow.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="19" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 37:10</char></note>He declares His word to Jacob,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 33:4; Ps. 103:7</char></note>His statutes and His judgments to Israel.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="20" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Mal. 4:4</char></note>He has not dealt thus with any nation;</para>
	<para style="q2">And <char style="it">as</char> <char style="it">for</char> <char style="it">His</char> judgments, they have not known them.</para>
	<para style="q1">Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<chapter number="148" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Praise to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> from Creation</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q1">Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char> from the heavens;</para>
	<para style="q2">Praise Him in the heights!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="2" style="v" />Praise Him, all His angels;</para>
	<para style="q2">Praise Him, all His hosts!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" />Praise Him, sun and moon;</para>
	<para style="q2">Praise Him, all you stars of light!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Praise Him, <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 4:32–34; (Rom. 3:1, 2)</char></note>you heavens of heavens,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 10:14; 1 Kin. 8:27; (Neh. 9:6)</char></note>you waters above the heavens!</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />Let them praise the name of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 1:7</char></note>He commanded and they were created.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Gen. 1:1, 6</char></note>He also established them forever and ever;</para>
	<para style="q2">He made a decree which shall not pass away.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="7" style="v" />Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char> from the earth,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 89:37; (Jer. 31:35, 36; 33:20, 25)</char></note>You great sea creatures and all the depths;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />Fire and hail, snow and clouds;</para>
	<para style="q2">Stormy wind, fulfilling His word;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 43:20</char></note>Mountains and all hills;</para>
	<para style="q2">Fruitful trees and all cedars;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="10" style="v" />Beasts and all cattle;</para>
	<para style="q2">Creeping things and flying fowl;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="11" style="v" />Kings of the earth and all peoples;</para>
	<para style="q2">Princes and all judges of the earth;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="12" style="v" />Both young men and maidens;</para>
	<para style="q2">Old men and children.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="13" style="v" />Let them praise the name of the <char style="sc">Lord</char>,</para>
	<para style="q2">For His <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Is. 44:23; 49:13</char></note>name alone is exalted;</para>
	<para style="q2">His glory <char style="it">is</char> above the earth and heaven.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="14" style="v" />And He <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 8:1</char></note>has exalted the horn of His people,</para>
	<para style="q2">The praise of <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">1 Sam. 2:1; Ps. 75:10</char></note>all His saints—</para>
	<para style="q2">Of the children of Israel,</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 149:9</char></note>A people near to Him.</para>
	<para style="q1">Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<chapter number="149" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Praise to God for His Salvation and Judgment</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q1"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Lev. 10:3; Eph. 2:17</char></note>Sing to the <char style="sc">Lord</char> a new song,</para>
	<para style="q2"><char style="it">And</char> His praise in the assembly of saints.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" />Let Israel rejoice in their Maker;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let the children of Zion be joyful in their <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 33:3</char></note>King.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="3" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Judg. 8:23; Zech. 9:9; Matt. 21:5</char></note>Let them praise His name with the dance;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let them sing praises to Him with the timbrel and harp.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />For <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ex. 15:20; Ps. 81:2</char></note>the <char style="sc">Lord</char> takes pleasure in His people;</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 35:27</char></note>He will beautify the humble with salvation.</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="5" style="v" />Let the saints be joyful in glory;</para>
	<para style="q2">Let them <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 132:16; Is. 61:3</char></note>sing aloud on their beds.</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="6" style="v" /><char style="it">Let</char> the high praises of God <char style="it">be</char> in their mouth,</para>
	<para style="q2">And <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Job 35:10</char></note>a two-edged sword in their hand,</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="7" style="v" />To execute vengeance on the nations,</para>
	<para style="q2">And punishments on the peoples;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="8" style="v" />To bind their kings with chains,</para>
	<para style="q2">And their nobles with fetters of iron;</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="9" style="v" /><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Heb. 4:12; Rev. 1:16</char></note>To execute on them the written judgment—</para>
	<para style="q2"><note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Deut. 7:1, 2; Ezek. 28:26</char></note>This honor have all His saints.</para>
	<para style="q1">Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<chapter number="150" style="c" />
	<para style="s">Let All Things Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char></para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="1" style="v" />Praise<note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 148:14; 1 Cor. 6:2</char></note> the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>
	<para style="q1">Praise God in His sanctuary;</para>
	<para style="q2">Praise Him in His mighty firmament!</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="2" style="v" />Praise Him for His mighty acts;</para>
	<para style="q2">Praise Him according to His excellent <note style="x" caller="-"><char style="xt" closed="false">Ps. 145:5, 6</char></note>greatness!</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="3" style="v" />Praise Him with the sound of the trumpet;</para>
	<para style="q2">Praise Him with the lute and harp!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="4" style="v" />Praise Him with the timbrel and dance;</para>
	<para style="q2">Praise Him with stringed instruments and flutes!</para>
	<para style="q2"><verse number="5" style="v" />Praise Him with loud cymbals;</para>
	<para style="q2">Praise Him with clashing cymbals!</para>
	<para style="q1"><verse number="6" style="v" />Let everything that has breath praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>.</para>
	<para style="q1">Praise the <char style="sc">Lord</char>!</para>

</usx>